title: vinegar pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and place in unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Will thicken.

title: italian spaghetti sauce and meatballs
directions: Slowly cook sauce until onions are tender (approximately 1 hour).
Simmer for 2 more hours.
Water may be added for desired consistency.
Add 1 teaspoon sugar during last 1/2 hour.
Add the drained, chopped mushrooms last.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Drain carrots well.
Cut up onion and pepper; mix with carrots.
Mix everything and heat until it is dissolved.
Pour over carrots and let set overnight.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Boil sugar and water for 2 1/2 minutes, then add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Drop by teaspoon on waxed paper.

title: pheasant with brown gravy
directions: Place pheasant in ungreased square 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish. Mix soup, cider, Worcestershire sauce, salt, onion, garlic and mushrooms; pour over pheasant.
Sprinkle generously with paprika. Cook, uncovered, in a 350° oven, spooning sauce onto pheasant occasionally until done, 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
After cooking pheasant 1 hour, sprinkle again with paprika.

title: egg 'n cheese strata
directions: Butter bread and cut into cubes.
Alternate layers of bread cubes and cheese in buttered 2-quart casserole.
Blend together eggs, milk and seasonings.
Pour egg mixture over bread-cheese mixture.
Cover.
Refrigerate several hours or overnight.
Bake at 350° until golden brown, 70 minutes.
This is good for dinner, too, with a big salad!

title: chow mein hot dish
directions: Brown onion and hamburger together.
Mix in remaining ingredients.
Bake in greased casserole, covered, for 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°.
Sprinkle with chow mein noodles and bake 15 minutes more.

title: chicken pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta; rinse with cold water and drain.
Thaw vegetables under cold water; drain.
Combine pasta, veggies, cheese and chicken in a large bowl.
Toss with salad dressing.
Chill.
Serve on a bed of lettuce.

title: un-fried chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Coat a baking sheet with 3 sprays of vegetable cooking spray.
Put the chicken in a large bowl with the ice water.
Put the yogurt into a medium bowl.
Remove 2 pieces of chicken from the ice water.
Roll each piece in yogurt.
Place chicken in breading mix*, reseal and shake to coat thoroughly. Place on baking sheet.
Repeat until all 12 pieces are breaded. Spray chicken lightly with vegetable oil spray.
Place baking sheet on bottom shelf of oven and bake for 1 hour, turning pieces every 20 minutes.
Serve hot or at room temperature.

title: hot bean dip
directions: Mix all ingredients with mixer.
Pour into baking dish.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 375° until cheese melts.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: apple pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour over apples.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: shoo-fly pie
directions: Mix together the first 4 ingredients until crumbly. Take out 2 cups of crumbs for top of pies.
To remainder of crumbs, add the eggs, molasses and water.
Mix well.
Dissolve the soda in the 1/2 cup hot water.
Add to mixture.
Pour in the unbaked shells. Top with reserved crumbs. Bake at 450° for 10 minutes. Reduce heat to 375° and bake for 30 minutes or until top is dry and done.

title: butter rolls
directions: Make up your favorite biscuit dough, omitting shortening. Divide dough and roll out on a floured surface to 3/4-inch thick. Spread margarine over rolled dough and sprinkle with sugar to cover and a few drops of vanilla. Roll up like a jelly roll.
Cut in biscuit size pieces and arrange in a pan, cut side down. Continue until all dough is used.
Add a few drops of vanilla to enough milk to nearly cover rolls and pour over them.
Cover tops with sugar, about 1 cup.

Bake at 350° until slightly brown. If rolls tend to get too dry, add a few drops of vanilla, 3/4 cup sugar (and cinnamon, if desired) to 2 cups of milk, heat in a saucepan until slightly thick, then pour over rolls.
Serve warm or cold.

title: corned beef casserole
directions: Cook onion until tender in butter.
Combine corned beef (broken in small pieces), potatoes, 1/2 cup milk, 1/2 teaspoon salt and 1/8 teaspoon pepper.
Press against sides and bottom of a quart casserole.
Spread remaining butter in skillet and blend in flour and remaining salt and pepper.
Add liquid from corn and rest of milk gradually, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Add corn and pour in lined casserole.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: tomato zip beverage
directions: Stir all ingredients together in pitcher.
Serve over ice with celery garnish.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Break angel food cake into small pieces.
Mix the vanilla pudding and stir in with cake pieces.

Spread in bottom of pan. Top cake mixture with both packages of jello. When mixing jello, add hot water as called for, but instead of adding cool water, use one large bag of frozen strawberries. Chill in refrigerator.
Top with Cool Whip and decorate with fresh berries.

title: four-layer dessert
directions: Combine flour, nuts and margarine; mix well.
Press onto bottom of 11 3/4 x 7 1/2-inch baking dish.
Cook at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cool.

title: super doughnuts(filled)
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Mix all ingredients except yeast and flour.
Stir in enough flour until cake batter consistency.
Add dissolved yeast mixture; stir in rest of flour. Knead; dough should not be too thick.

title: holiday chocolate butter cookies
directions: Beat all but flour and cocoa; add last slowly.
Roll into ball (1 to 2 teaspoons dough); fill with half a glazed cherry. Bake at 375° for 7 to 9 minutes; cool.
Spoon melted chocolate chips over center.
Let stand to harden.
Makes 45 cookies.

title: corn fritters
directions: Sift dry ingredients; add egg.
Add milk and butter.
Stir all ingredients until smooth.
Let stand 15 minutes.
Drop by teaspoonful into deep fat (360°).
Serve with hot syrup or honey.

title: spiedies
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well and refrigerate.
Mix spiedies well every day for 5 to 14 days before using.
Spiedies will not spoil if kept cold.

title: asparagus quick lunch(low calorie)
directions: Drain asparagus and place in pie pan.
Cover with grated cheese.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs and bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Serves 2.

title: one-bowl buttercream frosting
directions: In small mixer bowl cream butter.
Add cocoa and confectioners sugar alternately with milk.
Beat to spreading consistency (additional
milk
may
be
needed).
Blend
in vanilla. Makes about 2 cups frosting.

title: cheese cake
directions: At high speed on mixer, mix cream cheese.
Gradually add sugar.
Add eggs and beat well.
Then turn mixer on low and add cornstarch, flour, vanilla and lemon juice.
By hand, mix in melted butter and sour cream until smooth.
Pour into spring pan and bake 1 hour and 10 minutes at 325°.
Turn off heat.
Let cake stay in oven 2 hours or overnight (when I bake in the evening, I keep it in overnight).
Then refrigerate.

title: noodles for machine
directions: Mix well and process through noodle maker.

title: shereen's chicken
directions: In bowl, mix chicken soup, onion soup and milk.
Measure out 1/2 cup and set aside.
Stir rice, peas and carrots into remaining mixture.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Bury chicken pieces into rice mixture.
Pour reserved soup mixture over top. Sprinkle with paprika.
Cover tightly with foil.
Bake at 375° for 1 1/4 hours.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: french toast sandwiches with creamed dried beef
directions: Melt butter in skillet.
Add beef and cook for 2 to 3 minutes. Blend in flour; add 2 cups milk.
Cook, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Add seed, rosemary and pepper to taste.
Keep hot.
Next, beat eggs.
Add remaining milk.
Dip bread into mixture and fry in hot butter until golden brown on both sides. Serve beef between and over toast.
Excellent!

title: candy cookies
directions: Melt butter in heavy 1 1/2-quart saucepan.
Stir in sugar, salt, cocoa and milk.
Bring to a boil and boil exactly 2 minutes. Remove from heat and stir in peanut butter, then oats.
Mix thoroughly and drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper. Cool, then chill.

title: cocoa syrup
directions: Combine cocoa, sugar and salt in a medium saucepan.
Gradually stir in water until mixture is smooth.
Bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Continue to cook and stir 3 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla.
Pour into container. Cool, cover and refrigerate.
Use to prepare cold drinks or serve as a topping for ice cream.
Makes 2 cups syrup.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Dissolve jellos in boiling water.
Add cold water.
Add pie filling and mix well.
Refrigerate until thickened.
Beat together sugar, cream cheese and whipping cream until creamy and forms peaks.
Add marshmallows.
Frost on set jello.
Garnish with slivered almonds or chopped walnuts.
"Pretty in a clear bowl."

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix well.
Bake at 350° for 2 hours.

title: potato soup
directions: In large pan, combine potatoes, celery, onions, water, bouillon cubes and salt.
Cover and cook until tender, about 15 minutes.
Add 1 cup milk.
Heat good.
In bowl, blend sour cream and flour.
Gradually add remaining 1 cup milk.
Pour about 1/3 of hot potato mixture in sour cream mixture; stir.
Pour back into pan and cook until thick.
Be sure potatoes have cooked down good or soup will be too thin and watery.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: hot spiced tea
directions: Bring water
to
a
boil in a large pot and remove from heat. Add
tea bags and let stand for 5 minutes.
Then remove tea
bags. Squeeze
oranges
and lemons (save rinds).
Return tea to heat and add sugar, lemon rinds and cloves in a cheesecloth bag
and add
to
tea.
Simmer
for
about
10 minutes. Remove cheesecloth bag and discard.
Serve hot.

title: zesty potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes and cut into 1/2 to 1/4-inch pieces.
Boil until tender, but not soft.
Drain; put into shallow baking dish.
Top with dots of butter and sprinkle with seasoning salt.
(The more the better.)
Bake, uncovered, in oven at 350° until desired tenderness.

title: northern fish bouillon
directions: Put 1-inch of water in kettle.
Add potatoes, onion and salt pork.
When potatoes are done, add fish and butter.
When fish and potatoes are finished, add milk.
Don't boil; just heat to eat. May be frozen in fish shanty overnight.
When reheating, don't boil.

title: balloon blobs
directions: Blow up a balloon.
Keep it inflated for at least 1 minute, then let the air out.
Using a funnel, put as much flour in the balloon as possible.
Remove the funnel.
Tie a knot in the top of the balloon.
Wash and dry the balloon blob.
Draw a funny face and stretch it into different shapes.

title: marinated chicken livers
directions: Wash and put livers in bowl. Break 1 egg with livers and sprinkle garlic salt over livers. Pour soy sauce over livers to cover. Mix really well. Cover and let set overnight in refrigerator.

title: pound cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake 1 1/2 hours at 300° in tube pan.

title: rice pilaf
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Add pasta and saute until limp or slightly browned.
Do not burn butter.
Add rice and bouillon dissolved in hot water.
Add garlic pepper.
Reduce heat, put lid on pot and simmer on low 25 minutes without peeking.
May be baked in oven instead of on cooktop.
Onions, mushrooms, artichoke hearts or whatever your heart desires may be added and cooked with rice.

title: chicken mushroom casserole
directions: Sprinkle chicken with salt, pepper and paprika.
Brown in half the butter and remove to a casserole or shallow baking dish. Add remaining butter to drippings and saute mushrooms until tender.
Sprinkle flour over mushrooms and stir in chicken broth, sherry and rosemary.
Cook until thickened, then pour over chicken.
Cover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
If refrigerated ahead of time, cook for 1 hour.
I usually make more gravy, it's great over potatoes.

title: corn and potato chowder
directions: In large saucepan over medium heat, saute the onion and garlic in the oil until tender. Do not brown. Add the potatoes, bell pepper and seasoning. Bring to a boil; reduce heat to low and simmer approximately 20 minutes or until potatoes are tender, stirring occasionally. Stir in the remaining ingredients and heat for another 2 to 5 minutes, stirring constantly. Remove bay leaf before serving. Makes 6 to 7 cups.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw spinach and squeeze out water. Mix all ingredients. Yields 3 cups.

title: mexican squash
directions: Peel (optional) squash and slice.
Cook squash with the onion until just tender.
Drain squash.
In large bowl, gently combine squash with 4 tablespoons of melted butter, cheese, tomatoes and chilies.
If desired, add salt and pepper to taste.
Pour into lightly greased casserole dish.
Drizzle with 2 tablespoons melted butter and top with crumbled cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.
Yield: 6 to 8 servings.
Freezes well.

title: blackberry pie
directions: Bring blackberries to boil in enough water to cover and sugar to taste.
Mix sugar and flour; cut in butter.
(Do not melt butter.)
Beat egg separately.
Add to flour mixture.
Drop mixture into hot blackberries and bake about 35 minutes at 350° until brown.

title: cabbage soup
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a large Dutch oven; bring to a boil. Cover, reduce heat and simmer 15-20 minutes. Stir in whipping cream, butter, salt and pepper; cook, stirring constantly until butter melts and mixture is thoroughly heated. Spoon into serving bowls; sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Yield: about 3 qt.

title: 5-minute fruit 'n yogurt pie
directions: Fold yogurt into whipped topping; blend well.
Fold into strawberries and spoon into crust.
Freeze until firm, 4 hours or overnight.
Remove from freezer 30 minutes before serving and keep chilled in refrigerator.

title: ham and cheese biscuits(low-fat)
directions: Coat a medium-size nonstick skillet with cooking spray; place over medium heat until hot.
Add ham; saute 3 minutes.
Combine ham, flour and next 3 ingredients in a bowl.
Add milk, stirring just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Drop batter by heaping tablespoons onto a baking sheet coated with cooking spray.
Bake at 400° for 22 minutes.
Yield:
1 dozen (serving size:
1 biscuit).
Calories:
Fat grams:

title: dump cake
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Preheat oven to 325°.
Mix cherry pie filling and pineapple together.
Pour in pan.
Spread coconut evenly over mixture, sprinkle on nuts.
Take dry cake mix and sprinkle on top.
Dot with oleo and bake 1 hour or until done.

title: easy hamburger dish
directions: Fry hamburger.
Take the dish and layer 1/2 of the hamburger, 1/2 of the onion on top and layer Tater Tots.
Then again with the meat and onions.

title: meatballs
directions: Mix hamburger with garlic powder and shape into small balls. Pan-fry until well cooked; drain.
Mix chili sauce and grape jelly; add meatballs.
Heat mixture.
Serve warm in sauce. Makes 12 servings as an appetizer.

title: monster cookies
directions: Mix above ingredients together.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on cookie sheet.
Bake 12 minutes in 350° oven.
Cool on rack.

title: chopped ham and cheese rolls
directions: Boil together the butter, onion and mustard for 2 or 3 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Split top off of rolls in one slice. Spread butter mixture over bottom half, crumble ham over this, then grated cheese last.
Put top of rolls back on and heat at 325° until cheese melts, about 7 to 10 minutes.

title: instant spiced tea
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Place in jar; cover tightly.
Place 2 teaspoons in cup of boiling water to serve.
Yield:
30 servings.

title: muffins
directions: Sift
dry ingredients together.
Add milk to beaten egg and stir
liquid into dry ingredients.
Blend in oil.
Bake in greased muffin tins for 25 minutes at 400°.

title: microwave pumpkin bread(yield: 2 loaves)
directions: Combine flour, cinnamon, sugar and salt.
Add eggs, pumpkin and water.
Add to flour mixture.
Mix well.
Add raisins and nuts.
Pour into glass loaf pan that has been lightly greased and bottom lined with paper towel or wax paper.
Elevate in microwave on saucer or small dish.
Microwave on High 8 to 9 minutes, rotating every 2 minutes.

title: vinegar pie pastry by aunt nuvelle
directions: In a large bowl, combine flour, sugar and
salt with pastry blender (or two knives used scissor fashion).
Cut in shortening until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.

title: mexican dip
directions: Mix refried beans and taco seasoning.
Spread in bottom of 10 x 12-inch baking dish.
Layer following ingredients in order: sour cream, thawed guacamole, chilies, black olives and mixed together cheese.
Top with green onions and tomatoes.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: ranch oyster crackers
directions: Mix all ingredients; pour over crackers and mix again to cover crackers.
Pour onto a baking sheet and bake for 15 to 20 minutes at 275°.
Allow to cool before storing.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Mix all but peanuts. Bring to a boil, about 2 to 3 minutes. Add peanuts.

title: wilda's easy frosting
directions: Mix shortening, oleo and vanilla together.
Beat well.
Blend in salt, milk and confectioners sugar and beat well (the longer the better).

title: turban of sole
directions: In a 1-quart bowl or casserole, combine butter, celery, onion, seasonings and lemon juice.
Cook, covered, 3 minutes, stirring once.
Mix bread cubes with mixture.
Butter four 6 ounce custard cups.
Line sides and bottoms with thin pieces of fish, reserving small scraps for top.
(You may have to cut thick pieces in half.) Evenly divide stuffing between the 4 custard cups (about 1/2 cup each).
Top with any leftover pieces of fish.
Place custard cups on a dinner plate.
Cook, covered with dinner plate, 4 minutes or until fish flakes easily.
When done, with both hands, invert dinner plate with custard cups between them.
Let stand, covered, while making sauce.
Combine soup, pimiento or 1 teaspoon ripe olives and milk for sauce.
Cook, uncovered, 1 minute and 30 seconds or until mixture bubbles.
Remove top plate and custard cups.
Spoon sauce over Turbans and serve.
Makes 4 servings.

title: funnel cakes
directions: Heat 2 inches of salad oil to 360° in deep skillet.
Beat ingredients; mix well.
Hold finger on bottom of funnel and pour 1/4 cup batter into funnel.
Start in center; drop batter in hot oil, moving funnel to make coil of rings.
Fry cake, turning once with slotted spoon (about 2 minutes on each side).
Drain. Sprinkle with confectioners sugar.

title: oatmeal bread
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a saucepan and warm to 110°. Add yeast and stir to dissolve.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Bring sugar, water and butter to boil. Place apples into crescent rolls and roll up, beginning with big end. Place rolls into 8 x 8-inch baking dish and pour sugar mixture over rolls. Bake until brown in 350° oven. Sprinkle sugar and cinnamon over rolls when done. Be sure to pinch around rolls to seal shut. Enjoy!

title: cranberry-apple sauce
directions: Pare, core and slice apples.
Pick over cranberries, discard soft ones.
Place in large Dutch oven.
Add water, cover tightly and cook until both fruits are tender, 20 to 30 minutes.
Add sugar, stirring just enough to distribute.
Cook 3 to 4 minutes longer.
Remove from heat.
May be eaten warm or chilled before serving.

title: cool whip pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well and pour into graham cracker crust. Better when chilled overnight.

title: pineapple pound cake
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Cream together shortening, butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add flour alternately with milk mixed with vanilla.
Add pineapple.
Bake in a tube pan for 1 1/2 hours.

title: salmon patties
directions: Combine ingredients together and mix well.
Press into patties.
Fry until cooked.

title: turkey onion burgers
directions: In a large bowl, combine soup mix, ground turkey and water; shape into 4 patties.
Grill or broil until done.
Serve with toppings.
Makes 4 servings.

title: ham rolls
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
Heat, all in melted butter.
Slice bread.
Spread sauce on rolls.
Place ham and cheese on each and close.
Wrap tight with foil and refrigerate overnight.
Next day heat oven to 325° and bake 15 to 20 minutes.
Good eating!

title: mexican chicken and rice
directions: Boil chicken breasts (with stalk of celery, a carrot and a small onion) about 30 to 45 minutes.
Tear chicken apart (save broth).
Brown rice in skillet with oil added.
Stir frequently as it will burn quickly.
If needed, you can add more oil.
After rice is browned, add broth and water to make 6 cups, chicken, bouillon and salt.
Chop tomato and add to rice as it cooks.
When rice begins to boil, cover and turn burner down to simmer about 10 to 15 minutes until rice is done and water absorbed.
If rice is not done, add a little more water and cook until rice is done.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix together first 4 ingredients.
Add oil and eggs to mixture.
Add bananas and walnuts last.
Grease loaf pan.
Pour in pan and cook 45 minutes at 350°.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In baking pan (9-inch square or 7 x 11-inch loaf pan), mix all ingredients except peaches.
Next, pour peaches and juice over top.
Bake until golden brown.

title: ice tea drink
directions: Put tea bags in boiling water.
After a few minutes remove tea bags.
Add water, orange juice, lemonade and sugar.
The tea looks cloudy due to the orange juice and lemonade.
Makes 4 quarts.

title: pork tenderloin with fig preserves
directions: Preheat oven to 325°. Sprinkle salt and pepper over pork loin, then place in middle of flat baking dish. Sprinkle the onions, garlic and mushrooms around the meat. Spread the fig preserves over the meat until it is completely covered. Pour the wine around the meat; cover with foil and bake until done, 2 to 3 hours. Adjust baking time for less meat.

title: roast pork(flaeskesteg)
directions: Score the pork and rub with salt, mustard powder and little pepper.
Place on a grid and roast at 480° for about 1/2 hour or until the crackling turns white.

title: ham and cheese rolls
directions: Slice top off rolls.
Place ham and cheese and put top back on.
Mix butter and other ingredients and pour over rolls.
Bake at 350° until cheese melts.

title: sweet hot mustard
directions: Be careful in your selection.
Do not choose too young, and take only such varieties as has been reared in a good moral atmosphere.

title: prize winning chili
directions: Place ground
meat
and onions in a large pot and brown the meat
until
done.	Stir
frequently
to prevent burning. When the meat is browned, drain excess grease.
Add remaining ingredients except
for
chili powder and Pace picante sauce. Heat slowly
to a simmer being careful not to burn the chili. Add chili
powder and picante sauce a little at a time and mix well.	Taste
your chili
at
each
point
and adjust to your likings.

title: toffee
directions: Combine brown sugar, butter and nuts in saucepan.
Boil for 2 minutes.
Place sauce over graham crackers in 15 x 10-inch jelly roll pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Place Hershey bars on top immediately when taking out of oven.
Spread when melted.
(Do not put Hershey bars in oven.)
Cut while warm.
Refrigerate.

title: pumpkin muffins
directions: Sift dry ingredients into bowl.
Cut in shortening.
Combine egg, pumpkin and milk.
Add to dry ingredients.
Mix only until moist.
Add raisins and pecans.

title: "sock it to me" cake
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients; beat well.
Pour half of batter into greased Bundt pan.

title: mark's favorite soup(homemade chicken noodle)
directions: Cook chicken and bone.
Cook noodles in the chicken broth until tender.
Put chicken and soup in with noodles.
Add salt, pepper and celery salt to taste.
Simmer.

title: pumpkin banana bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In large mixer, combine sugar, butter and eggs.
Beat at medium speed, scraping bowl often, until mixture is light and fluffy.
Add pumpkin and bananas.
Continue beating until well mixed.
Mixture will have curdled appearance. Add remaining ingredients, except nuts.
Mix just until moistened. Stir in nuts and spread into 2 greased 8 x 4-inch loaf pans.
Bake for 50 to 60 mintues, until wooden pick comes out clean.
Cool upright.

title: brownies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° in a greased 11 x 14-inch pan until done in center.

title: raisin rice with curry
directions: Saute onion in margarine until tender.
Add water and bouillon cube.
Bring to boil and stir in remaining ingredients.
Return to boil, cover and remove from heat.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: lilly's pound cake
directions: Have cheese, butter and eggs at room temperature.
Cream the cream cheese, butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add flour slowly to mixture.
Scrape bowl down and then add vanilla while still beating.
Pour into well-greased and floured tube pan. Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 45 minutes.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients in a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish. Microwave on High for 4 minutes.
Stir well and microwave for 4 more minutes.
Add butter and vanilla; mix well.
Microwave 1 more minute.
Add baking soda, stir until light and foamy.
Pour onto ungreased cookie sheet and let set until cold.
Break into pieces and store in airtight container.

title: cucumber mint relish
directions: Peel cucumbers and cut lengthwise into quarters, then crosswise into 1/4-inch thick slices.
Place in bowl with 1/2 cup water and remaining ingredients.
Toss with fork to mix.
Cover and refrigerate.
Serve with hot or cold meat, fish or poultry.

title: dutch apple cake
directions: Mix and sift flour, baking powder, salt and 1/2 cup sugar. Add beaten egg and melted butter to milk.
Combine 2 mixtures and blend well.
Spread dough evenly in well-buttered pan.
Let rise 10 minutes in warm place.
Lay sliced apples in rows on dough, pressing in.
Sprinkle with sugar, dot with butter (melted) and dust with cinnamon.
Bake at 350° about 30 minutes or until center is done.
Serve hot or cold or with milk.

title: rice pudding
directions: Wash the rice.
Place in individual casserole.
Pout 1/2 cup of milk over the rice.
Set the dish in a pan of water.
Bake in moderate oven.
Allow to bake until brown crust forms.
As the milk is absorbed by the cooking rice, pour the remaining milk into the dish.
During the last part of the cooking, add the vanilla and cinnamon.
As soon as the rice is soft, remove from the oven and chill.
Raisins can be added with the cinnamon.
Yield: 1 serving. Carbohydrate 22 g, protein 10 g, fat 10 g, calories 218.
One serving = 1 fruit exchange, 1 milk exchange.
Add 1 fruit exchange if raisins are added.

title: dad's quick corn chowder
directions: In a small saucepan, heat altogether to boiling point.
Stir. Makes 2 servings of 1 cup each.

title: christmas relish
directions: Pour juice from a jar of whole dill pickles, but keep the juice.

title: chocolate banana nut cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 300°. In medium bowl, combine flour, baking soda and salt. Mix well.

Set aside. In a large bowl with an electric mixer, blend sugar at medium speed. Add butter and mix while scraping down the sides of the bowl. Add eggs, extract and bananas. Beat at medium speed until smooth. Add the flour mixture, 1 c. of the chocolate chips and the walnuts and blend at low speed until just combined.

title: double chocolate chip cookies
directions: Melt semi-sweet and unsweetened chocolates together with butter over low heat, stirring until smooth.
Cool.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt; set aside.
Beat eggs, sugar and vanilla until slightly thickened.
Add the chocolate mixture and mix well.
Add flour mixture mixing well.
Stir in chocolate chips, pecans and walnuts.
(If batter is thin, allow to stand for 10 minutes.)
Drop by heaping tablespoonfuls onto lightly greased cookie sheets, spacing cookies 3-inches apart.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Remove to rack to cool.
Do not overbake.

title: dave's shrimp dip
directions: Combine ingredients with mixer, except shrimp.
Add shrimp last.
Chill.
Makes 2 1/2 to 3 cups.

title: whole wheat carrot cake
directions: Heat
oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Beat eggs, sugars,	oil
and
vanilla.
Stir
in flours, baking soda, baking
powder, salt, cinnamon and allspice.	Mix in carrots and walnuts.
Pour	into
pan.
Bake
until
light brown and top springs
back when touched lightly in center, 50 to 55 minutes.

title: taco casserole
directions: Brown ground beef with onion.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chocolate chip pie
directions: Melt butter.
Mix butter with flour, sugar and vanilla.
Add beaten eggs and mix well.
Add chocolate chips, coconut and pecans.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake slowly in 300° oven until knife inserted in center comes out clean (1 to 1 1/2 hours).

title: shrimp creole
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Blend in rest of ingredients except shrimp.
Cook slowly, stirring occasionally.
Devein shrimp; add to sauce.
Cook 30 minutes.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Season to taste with salt, pepper and oregano.

title: quick biscuits
directions: Mix and shape into biscuits. Put in greased iron skillet. Bake at 450° until brown.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Mix
all
the ingredients and put in bell peppers.
Set them in
large deep pan that will go in the oven.
Before you bake them,
put
a large can of shredded kraut on top of them and
pour a
large
can
of tomato juice over the peppers and kraut.
Bake at 350° for about 1 1/2 hours.

title: brandied sweet potatoes
directions: Grease shallow baking dish.
Boil potatoes or yams in the skins until soft.
Remove and cool.
Peel and slice in crosswise slices about 1 1/2 inches thick.
Place in baking dish and dot with butter or margarine.
Combine sugar, nutmeg, cinnamon and salt and sprinkle over potatoes.
Pour brandy or sherry over all and bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Grind cranberries, apples, and oranges; add sugar and stir.

title: barbecue beef loaf
directions: Shape into 8 loaves.
Place in oiled baking dish.
Pour barbecue sauce over loaves.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: strawberry pretzel dessert
directions: Mix first layer.
Put in bottom of 9 X 13-inch pan and bake in 400 degree oven for 8 minutes.
Cool.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Boil chicken; cut up.
Save juice.
Melt butter.
Add flour, salt, pepper and 2 cups of broth gradually.
When blended, add chicken and cook until sauce thickens.
Add the heavy cream; blend in.
Keep warm over low heat.

title: banana dumplings
directions: Combine coconut milk (grind coconut and water together and strain), salt, garlic and pepper in a large pot.
Bring to a boil to get soup-like mixture.
Peel green bananas and dip into boiling soup (above).
Cut up the fish of your choice (i.e. snapper) and also dip into mixture.
Let bananas (and fish) get tender (test with fork).
Serve hot.

title: sugar-free strawberry ice cream
directions: Chill milk.
Beat eggs until frothy. Add sugar replacement, salt and lemon juice to the eggs and beat well. Gradually pour in the cold milk.
Pour mixture into 1 gallon freezer can. Freeze as directed. Add strawberries and food coloring when ice cream begins to thicken.
Makes 8 servings. Exchange 1 serving:
1 nonfat milk, 1/3 fat.
Calories per serving:

title: spanish rice
directions: Brown ground beef.
Add onion, green pepper, rice, tomato juice and salt.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer for 1 hour or until rice is tender.

title: mayonnaise rolls
directions: Mix flour and mayonnaise.
Add milk (batter will be thin). Spoon into greased muffin pans.
Makes 6 large rolls.

title: sugarless pear and date pie
directions: Combine pears and raisins in large bowl.
Combine dates, pineapple juice, cornstarch, cinnamon and nutmeg in saucepan; mix well.
Cook over medium heat until thickened, stirring constantly. Pour into pear and raisin mixture; mix until well coated.
Spoon into pastry-lined deep dish pie plate.
Top with remaining pastry, sealing edge and cutting vents.
Brush with a small amount of milk.
Cover edge of pastry with foil.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.
Remove foil.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes longer.
Do not use chopped sugar-coated pitted dates.
May substitute favorite fruit for pears and unsweetened orange or apple juice for pineapple juice.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: polish sausage casserole
directions: Layer in Dutch oven as listed. Cover and cook on medium heat 45 minutes. Serve with cornbread.

title: rice pudding
directions: Put water and rice in pan and bring to a boil, then add sugar. Put it on low heat and let it cook down.
Add milk and salt and cook until thick.
Add remaining ingredients and cook 5 minutes.

title: fish with yellow rice and hollandaise sauce
directions: Prepare rice as directed on bag; place in oblong baking dish when cooked. Prepare Hollandaise Sauce as directed on package. Place fish fillets on top of yellow rice; pour all Hollandaise Sauce over fillets. Bake 15 minutes in 350° oven and serve.

title: honey bun cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°. Mix first four ingredients by hand. Pour half of the batter into a greased 13 x 9 inch pan. Mix brown sugar and cinnamon. Sprinkle half over batter. Add rest of batter and sprinkle remaining sugar and cinnamon over top. Use fork and swirl through batter. Bake for 35 minutes. Mix powdered sugar, vanilla and milk. Spread over cake as soon as it comes out of the oven. You may pierce the cake with a fork to let icing to be absorbed.

title: black beans and rice
directions: Simmer ingredients for 30 minutes or until rice is done. Serve over bed of lettuce, onions and tomatoes.
Top everything with Zesty Italian salad dressing.

title: noodle pudding(kugel)
directions: Cook noodles to package directions.
Drain and place in large bowl.
Add margarine.
After margarine is melted, add remaining ingredients.
Place in 13 x 9 x 2-inch casserole.
Sprinkle cinnamon on top.
Bake uncovered one hour in 350° oven.
Serves 20.
Can freeze before cooking.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Fill level; cover with foil and bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: About 30 minutes before serving:
In a pie plate, combine flour, salt and pepper.
Dip tomato slices in mixture to coat both sides.

title: julienne
directions: Brown ground beef and onions in electric skillet; drain excess grease.
Spread potatoes evenly over beef; spread carrots over potatoes.
Spread celery over carrots.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Sprinkle oregano generously.
Cover and cook 15 minutes at 350°.
Spread green beans over mixture.
Spread cream of mushroom soup over green beans.
Cover and cook an additional 15 minutes.

title: fantastic focaccia bread
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Dip roller in flour and evenly roll dough into a circle on a flat, round pizza pan.
Press garlic and spread evenly over crust.
Grate 1/2 of Romano cheese over crust. Sprinkle 1 cup of Mozzarella and 1 teaspoon oregano over crust. Slice tomatoes thinly.
Layer tomatoes in a single layer over cheese.
Sprinkle remaining Mozzarella and oregano over tomatoes, grate remaining Romano on top.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cut into squares.
Serve hot.
Yields 16 appetizer servings.

title: original toll house cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine and mix all ingredients.
Place 1-inch size balls of dough onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Remove from oven and let stand 5 to 10 minutes. Remove from cookie pan.

title: italian beef bake
directions: Arrange long sheet of foil on shallow baking pan. Cut steak into strips and arrange in pan, slightly overlapping strips. Sprinkle onion soup mix, pepper and onion over meat. Drain and chop tomatoes; reserve liquid. Add tomatoes, salt and pepper to meat. Combine tomato liquid, steak sauce and cornstarch and pour over meat. Cover all with foil. Secure tightly. Bake at 350° for 2 hours.

title: 5 cup salad
directions: Drain fruit, mix together and let stand in refrigerator several hours or overnight.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Season pork chops with salt and pepper.
Brown on both sides in skillet.
Layer vegetables in 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish. Pour soup over vegetables.
Remove chops from skillet; set aside. Remove fat from skillet and add water to rinse and scrape particles from bottom of skillet.
Pour this over vegetables. Sprinkle with thyme.
Place pork chops on top.
Lay piece of foil over top and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Remove foil long enough to let chops brown or firm up on tops.

title: oatmeal breakfast cake
directions: Grease a 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Mix oil, eggs and sugar. Add oatmeal, baking powder and milk; mix well and add raisins. Pour into prepared pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Serve warm with peaches and cream.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except cheese.
Alternate chicken mix and cheese.
Bake at 400° until hot and bubbly!

title: layered salad deluxe
directions: Layer first five ingredients in order listed in a large salad bowl.
Combine mayonnaise, sour cream and dressing mix; mix well. Spread over top of vegetables, sealing to edge of bowl.
Cover tightly and refrigerate several hours or overnight.
Toss gently before serving.
Serves 10 to 15.

title: kansas cornbread casserole
directions: Saute onion and hamburger; drain grease.
Stir in soup and seasonings, then add green beans. Spread in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix cornbread according to package directions and pour over meat mixture.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until cornbread is brown.

title: apple crisp
directions: Mix together sugar, oil, eggs and vanilla.
Sift flour before measuring.
Sift together flour, soda, baking powder, salt and cinnamon.
Mix together both mixtures.
Stir in walnuts and apples.

title: tournedos diane with marchandde vin sauce
directions: Melt butter in skillet.
Sear steaks on each side in hot skillet.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper, if desired.
Put in baking dish with a layer of onion and then tomato, topping with mushrooms.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Brown hamburg, pork and diced onion in pan; before draining add uncooked rice then drain.
Shred cabbage and layer in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Once cabbage is in pan, layer meat and rice mixture on top of cabbage.
Pour diluted tomato soup over meat and cabbage mixture.
Cover pan with aluminum foil and bake at 350° for 1 hour (check after 1 hour to see if cabbage is tender).

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix well the first 3 ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients. Bake at 375° for 35 minutes.
Makes its own crust.

title: crazy cake
directions: Mix first three ingredients.
Add next four.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
No need for frosting.
Enjoy.

title: good punch
directions: Dissolve Kool-Aid and sugar in hot water.
Fill up with water to make a gallon.

title: scrambled squash
directions: Chop all vegetables.
Mix with flour, salt, and pepper.
Heat oil in skillet.
Add vegetables, brown, and turn until done. Very good with eggs.

title: 7 layer salad
directions: In large glass bowl (diameter at top and bottom of bowl must be same as this salad is to be served straight down from top to bottom so all layers are served to each person), put approximately 4-inches of lettuce for bottom layer.
This may or may not take the full head of lettuce.
Spread onion over lettuce for 2nd layer. Spread green peas over onion for 3rd layer.
Mix mayonnaise and sugar; beat until smooth and spread over peas for 4th layer.
Cut boiled eggs in round slices and cover dressing layer for the 5th layer.
Cover eggs with shredded cheese for the 6th layer.
Cover the entire salad with bacon for the 7th layer.
This salad should be sealed with Saran Wrap and refrigerated for 24 hours to allow the flavor of each layer to go through the salad.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream the sugars with butter.
Add eggs.
Stir in oil and vanilla.
Mix dry ingredients and mix well.
Make into balls.
Dip in granulated sugar and flatten with bottom of glass.
Bake at 350° until lightly brown.

title: raisin bar
directions: Mix all ingredients in order.
Pour in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° until done, about 30 minutes.

title: pork chops oniondine
directions: Slash the fat around each pork chop. Fry chops until brown on both sides. Pour rice into a 2-quart baking dish. Cover with water. Arrange the pork chops over the rice. Cover all with undiluted onion soup. Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.

title: ellen's deviled crab
directions: Mix ingredients all together and mold into clam shells or spread in greased casserole and bake at 425° until brown.
If desired, tops may be coated with 1 cup mayonnaise plus 2 egg yolks. Serves 6.

title: strawberry dessert
directions: Mix jello with 1 cup boiling water.
Add frozen strawberries and set aside.
Line bottom of oblong dish with half of the cake, sliced thin.
Pour jello mixture over cake.
Add rest of cake as next layer.
Make pudding with 4 cups milk and pour over cake. Top with Cool Whip and nuts with fresh strawberry slices.
Serves 8 to 12.

title: flour dumplings
directions: Cream butter and salt, then add the egg and beat until foamy. In another bowl, sift flour, baking powder and add, alternating with milk, to creamed butter mixture.
Let stand 30 minutes.
Drop by spoonfuls into chicken broth or boiling water.
Cook eight to ten minutes.
The inside should be dry, not mushy.
You can half the recipe.

title: apple and cheddar corn muffins(low-cal)
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Line 12 muffin pan cups with paper baking cups.
Set aside.

title: chocolate-topped strawberries
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a small bowl; stir well.
Cover and chill.
Divide strawberries evenly among 4 individual dessert dishes, reserving 4 strawberries for garnish.
Spoon 1/4 cup chocolate mixture over individual serving dishes of strawberries. Garnish with a reserved strawberry.

title: jello salad
directions: Mix Jell-O and Cool Whip.
Stir in cottage cheese and pineapple.
Refrigerate all day or overnight.

title: minutemen macaroons
directions: Combine coconut, milk and vanilla; mix well.
Drop from teaspoon 1 inch apart onto well-greased baking sheets.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes or until lightly golden brown.
Remove at once.
Makes 30.

title: rice pudding
directions: Put ingredients in a 2-quart baking dish.
Bake at 325° for approximately 1 hour.
Stir occasionally.

title: cincinnati chili
directions: In a nonreactive kettle (stainless steel), combine all ingredients, except meat.
Cover and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat to simmer and crumble in meat.
Simmer, uncovered, for 1 to 2 hours, until chili is as thick as you like it.
Discard bay leaves and serve.

title: audreyce's shepherd pie
directions: Put Hamburg into baking dish.
Cover with Peas (I use some of the pea juice too).
Sprinkle with Cheese.
Top with Mashed Potatoes.
Sprinkle with Paprika.
Bake at 425 until heated through.

title: red snapper(with sesame vegetables)
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In large nonstick skillet over high heat, heat oils.
Add ginger root and garlic; saute 30 seconds. Add onion and saute 30 seconds.
Add peppers and cook 1 minute. Reduce heat to medium and stir in snow peas, vinegar and soy sauce.
Let bubble 1 minute.
Stir in sesame seed and remove from heat.
Arrange snapper fillets in baking pan.
Evenly spoon vegetable mixture over fish.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes until fish are just cooked through.
Contains 229 calories per serving.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Melt butter and cocoa together. Remove from heat. Add sugar and eggs and mix well. Add flour and vanilla. Add nuts. Bake at 350° until done. Put marshmallows on hot cake. Spread icing over marshmallows. You may add a little milk to icing to thin down.

title: chocolate cookies
directions: Combine chocolate morsels and butter in a large mixing bowl. Melt in frying pan.
Stir halfway through cooking time.
Add sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Beat until well blended.
Stir in ingredients. Chill dough 3 hours.
Roll into balls.
Place nuts in.
Keep dough 2-inches apart on waxed paper.
Microwave on High (100%).

title: deep-fried corn
directions: Heat oil on medium heat. Drop corn in hot oil. When corn floats to the top, it is done. Remove corn and drain on paper towel. Salt and pepper to taste.

title: pistachio pudding salad
directions: Dissolve the instant pudding right from the box into the pineapple (juice and all).
Combine the Cool Whip and marshmallows, mixing thoroughly.
Add to the pudding mix.
Add nuts.
Makes a 2-quart bowl.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Cook macaroni and cheese dinner according to box instructions. Combine all ingredients and mix well in casserole dish or baking pan.
Cover and bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: sour cream rolls
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Put in ungreased muffin pan. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Dough will keep in refrigerator for about a week.
Yields 12 rolls.

title: tater-tot casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Drain liquid off corn or green beans.
Cut Velveeta cheese in slices.
Layer in square baking dish in the following order:
ground beef, soup, beans or corn, cheese and Tater Tots.
(May not need entire package of Tater Tots.)
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes or until cheese is melted and Tater Tots are golden brown.
This casserole is also good without the corn or green beans.

title: onion casserole
directions: Amount varies based on size of dish.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Cook chicken and salt in water until tender.
Remove from broth and remove bones.
Set aside broth.
Coarsely chop chicken. Cook spaghetti as directed on package.
Drain.
Saute pepper, onions and celery in margarine until tender.
Add chicken, spaghetti, 1/2 cup broth or more and soup (undiluted).
Add peas (drained), cheese, sliced olives, Worcestershire, tomato sauce, sugar, hot sauce and black pepper.
Stir well.
Spoon into casserole dish.
Cover and bake at 350° for about 40 minutes. Serve while warm.

title: vanilla ice cream
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients thoroughly in ice cream churn can. Fill with 2% skim milk.

title: fried rice
directions: Fry bacon.
Put on a plate to cool.
Keep fire on high.
To bacon grease, add onion, cooked until clear.
Add cooked rice and bacon, crumbled up.
Also add scrambled egg, 1/2 cup water and soy sauce.
Cook on high for 15 minutes.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix apples and sugar in a large bowl. Set aside. Mix oil, vanilla, nuts and eggs. Add to apple mixture. Mix flour, soda, salt, cinnamon and raisins. Add to apple mixture. Place in greased and floured 9 x 13 x 2 pan. Bake at 325° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
May be kept on shelf and used as needed.
Combine with boiling water for a great cup of hot chocolate!

title: helpful health drink
directions: Mix and store in refrigerator.
Drink 1/4 cup daily to reduce cholesterol and arthritis.

title: hush puppies
directions: Combine cornmeal mix, sugar and onion in a bowl.
Add milk and egg to dry ingredients.
Stir.
Drop by heaping teaspoonfuls into hot deep fat fryer (375°) until golden brown and drain on paper towels.

title: creamy cheese sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients and heat on top of stove.
Serve over broccoli, cauliflower and asparagus, etc.

title: apple nut cake
directions: Chop apples into bowl.
Add eggs and stir well.
Add remaining ingredients in order given and pour into 8-inch square pan or small loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes, depending on type of pan.
Can be served with whipped cream or make a glaze with a little powdered sugar and water.

title: chicken continental
directions: Line casserole dish with dried beef.
Place chicken on top of beef.
Combine soup and sour cream in a bowl; pour over chicken. Bake at 350° for 1 hour, covered with foil.
Uncover and bake 30 minutes.

title: corn fritters
directions: Pour by spoonfuls on a hot griddle, turning once.

title: sixty minute buns
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water, then add cool milk.
Put the 5 cups of flour in another bowl; add salt and sugar.
Add oil, then add yeast mixture.
Work into rolls.
Let rise until double in volume.
Bake at 400° until done.

title: banana cake
directions: Cream the sugar and shortening; add eggs, bananas, soda, baking powder, salt, sour milk, flour, vanilla and nutmeats.
Bake at 350°.

title: icebox rolls
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar; add boiling water.
Cool to lukewarm and add yeast, egg and salt.
Stir in enough flour to make a soft dough.
Cover and place in refrigerator overnight or until needed. Make rolls into desired shape; dip in melted butter.
Place in pan and let rise 1 to 2 hours.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: In saucepan, cook pudding mix and milk over medium heat until thickened and bubbly.
Remove from heat; cool slightly.
In bowl, cut peanut butter into confectioners sugar until small balls form. Add additional powdered sugar if needed.
Set aside about 2 tablespoons of crumb mixture.
Sprinkle remaining mixture into pie shell.
Pour pudding over crumbs.
Chill until set.
Top with whipped cream or Cool Whip.
Sprinkle reserved crumbs on top.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Boil chicken until done.
Cut into chunks.
Put in baking dish, then add cream of celery, cream of chicken, water chestnuts and 1/2 cup of chicken broth.
Put bread crumbs on top, then put butter on top.
Cook for 30 minutes.

title: curry sauce(this is a vegetable dip.)
directions: Mix together until well blended.
Store in jar in refrigerator.
Use with fresh vegetables as a dip.

title: six-minute pecan pie
directions: In a large bowl, stir together first 5 ingredients until well blended. Stir in nuts. Pour into pastry shell. Bake in 350° oven 50 to 55 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean. Cool. Serves 8.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello and sweetener in boiling water.
Add strawberries and pineapple, including juice.
Pour half of mixture into an 8 x 8 x 2-inch bowl.
Refrigerate 1/2 hour or until set. Spread sour cream on top of jello.
Add remaining strawberry mixture.
Refrigerate.
Makes 8 servings.

title: missouri state fair grilled turkey tenderloins
directions: Place all ingredients except turkey in a Ziploc bag (or shallow pan) for marinade, mix well.
Add turkey and marinate in refrigerator several hours, turning occasionally.
Grill turkey over hot coals for 4 to 8 minutes per side, depending on thickness, until done.
Baste with remaining marinade while grilling.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown ground beef, onion and celery; drain.
Add spices, corn, beans and tomato sauce.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Place cheese and chips on top and bake for 5 minutes longer.

title: rice crispy treats
directions: Bring syrup, peanut butter to a light boil.
Stir into rice crispies.
Put into 15 x 10 inch pan.
Melt 1 package butterscotch chips and 1 package chocolate chips.
Pour over mixture.

title: taco salad
directions: Mix taco mix and sour cream together.
Layer ingredients in a pizza dish in order:
spread bean dip, spread sour cream with taco mix on top of bean dip and top with cheese and other ingredients. Serve with chips.

title: chicken scallopini
directions: Saute chicken in oil.
Add onion, celery and garlic.
Cook until vegetables are tender.
Add tomatoes and saute until soft. Add sugar and basil to taste. Simmer 15 minutes.
Serve over spaghetti.

title: mrs. cook's swedish cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg.
Mix well.
Add almond extract.
Add flour.
Mix well.
Run through a cookie press, using the star plate.
Shape in circles.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes in 350° oven.
Cool on wire rack.

title: swiss steak
directions: Salt, pepper & flour meat on all sides.
Brown meat in a little oil.
Use heavy pan or Dutch oven.
Drain off all fat in pan.
Wipe out with paper towels if necessary.
Pour the soup and water over the meat.
Cover tightly with lid or foil.
Bake in slow oven, 325° for 2 hours or till meat is tender.
Check occasionally and add more water if gravy gets too thick.

title: lime punch
directions: Mix jello as directed on package.
Add water, sugar, lemon juice and pineapple juice.
Add enough water to make 1 gallon. Freeze in two cartons or Ziploc freezer bags.

title: dirt cake
directions: Cream margarine, cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Combine milk with pudding.
Add Cool Whip.
Combine the 2 mixtures.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown meat and onion together.
Cook macaroni.
Drain off water.
Mix meat with noodles.
Mix other stuff together.
Top with grated cheese.
Cook for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: easy tootsie rolls
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Knead like you would for bread.
I find it easier to knead together to a point then break into three or four balls and knead.
Roll into rope shapes and cut into desired lengths.
These are softer than the ones you buy. Makes about 2 dozen.
You can get 15 dozen if you make the smaller ones.

title: play dough
directions: Mix all ingredients together (except food coloring) in saucepan and stir vigorously.
Cook for approximately 3 minutes, stirring constantly.
The mixture will congeal and you'll immediately know when its finished.
When dough is cool enough to handle, knead the food coloring into it.
Will keep for several months.
Store in a sealed container.

title: sweet potato pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients in order.
Bake for 1 hour at 300°.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Add all ingredients except cheeses to hamburger.
Mix well.
Layer meat mixture, then cheese, then meat until gone.
Cover with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: better than robert redford
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients.
Press in bottom and on sides of a 9 x 13-inch oblong pan.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.
Let cool.

title: fresh spinach salad
directions: Break spinach into small pieces and wash thoroughly. Dry between a couple of towels.
Roll towels and place in refrigerator preferably overnight.

title: wham croquettes
directions: Cook rice.
Mix together celery soup, ground Ham Style Entree, rice, onion, green pepper and mustard.
Chill in refrigerator. Shape into croquettes, using about 1/4 cup per croquette.
Dip in beaten egg, then into bread crumbs.
Let stand a few minutes.
Fry 2 or 3 at a time in deep, hot fat (365°) for 3 to 5 minutes or until brown.
Drain on paper towels.
Prepare frozen peas according to package directions; pour over croquettes and serve.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Mix pretzels, margarine and sugar together.
Press into a 13 x 9-inch
dish.
Bake
at 400° for 8 minutes.
Mix cream cheese and 1 cup of sugar together.
Add Cool Whip;
spread on cooled bottom crust.
Dissolve Jell-O in water and add frozen strawberries.
Let stand
10 minutes.
Pour over cream cheese mixture.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts.
Place in refrigerator. When congealed, cut into squares to serve.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Drain pineapple and save the juice.
Place pineapple in greased baking dish.
Melt oleo and mix with crumbled crackers and cheese.
Mix sugar and cornstarch into pineapple juice.
Cook until it thickens.
Pour over pineapple chunks.
Top with crumb mixture.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: nacho chicken casserole
directions: Mix
cut up deboned chicken or turkey, soup, tomatoes, pepper and onion.
Break up part of chips in bottom of greased dish. Layer with chicken mix and nacho chips.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: raisin cupcakes
directions: Cover raisins with water; boil for 10 minutes, or until half the water is left.
Cream shortening and sugar.
Add egg and vanilla; beat.
Mix flour, soda, salt and cinnamon together; add to the creamed mixture.
Add the raisins and juice and fold in. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Makes 1 dozen.
They stay moist.

title: simple fajitas
directions: Bake pork roast according to weight until cooked.
Let cool and cut/slice into chunks.
Warm corn/flour tortillas.
Roll meat, chopped cilantro, chopped green onion, lemon and salsa together.
Enjoy!

title: baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake about 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: stuffed steak
directions: Salt and pepper steak.
Make stuffing by package ingredients. Spread stuffing over steak.
Roll up; place in toothpicks to hold together.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until desired doneness.

title: egg salad sandwich spread
directions: Mix ingredients until blended.
Spread 1/4 of mixture on a slice of bread.
Makes enough filling for 4 sandwiches.
Contains 115 calories each.

title: escalloped pineapple
directions: Place well drained pineapple in a 1 to 1 1/2-quart greased casserole.
Beat eggs, then mix in flour, sugar and salt.
Pour over pineapple.
In a large skillet, melt margarine and coat bread cubes.
Place buttered cubes on top of pineapple mixture and bake, uncovered, in a 400° oven for 30 minutes.
Good with any meat entree or for a salad luncheon.

title: fried chicken
directions: Beat eggs and milk with fork and add salt, pepper and paprika. Dip chicken into egg mixture. Dip into flour. Fry in hot oil. Brown on one side; turn and brown on other. Cover pan and cook on low heat for 20 minutes.

title: cheddar crisps
directions: In large bowl mix flour, cornmeal, baking soda, sugar and salt. With pastry blender or two knives used scissor-fashion, cut in margarine until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
With fork, stir in shredded cheese, vinegar, Tabasco and 1/2 cup cold water, just until mixture forms a soft dough.
Shape dough into a ball; wrap with plastic wrap and refrigerate 1 hour or until dough is firm enough to handle.
(Or place dough in freezer 30 minutes.)

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Combine all ingredients in a bowl and beat for 2 minutes. Pour into 2 greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake for 1 hour and 10 minutes at 350°.
Glaze while cake is warm.
Remove cake from pans while still warm.
When cooled completely, wrap in foil.

title: homemade chocolate ice cream
directions: Mix well.
Pour into ice cream churn.
Fill the rest with whole milk and churn until hard.

title: pineapple cheese casserole
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and pour in buttered casserole dish. Crush Ritz crackers and sprinkle on top.
Melt butter and pour over crackers.
Bake at 350° for 25-30 minutes.

title: tamale pie
directions: Cook corn meal, water and salt in top of double boiler for 45 minutes.
Chop onions and pepper and fry in oil.
Add tomatoes, meat, salt and pepper or chili powder and cook until thick.

title: yogurt cream cheese
directions: Line a strainer with a double thickness of cheesecloth or 3 layers of paper towels.
Spoon 2 cups yogurt into the strainer. Place a bowl beneath but not touching the strainer, to catch the liquid from the yogurt.
Cover and refrigerate 24 hours.
Use drained yogurt as a replacement for cream cheese.

title: quick chicken stroganoff
directions: Cut chicken into strips.
Melt butter in skillet over medium heat.
Add chicken and scallions and sprinkle with salt.
Cook 6-8 minutes, stirring occasionally, until chicken pieces are opaque. Add mushrooms with liquid, add 1/4 cup water.
Heat to boiling, stirring until mixture is smooth.
Reduce heat, Blend in sour cream and heat through, but do not boil.
Serve over hot cooked noodles or rice.
*I use boneless chicken breasts.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Add taco seasoning according to package directions.
Set aside to cool slightly.
In large, clear glass bowl, layer lettuce, meat, cheese and tomatoes.
Pour Ranch dressing over top.
Add crushed Doritos when ready to serve.
Does not refrigerate well.

title: lemon pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into a baked pie crust.

title: georgia peanut soup
directions: Combine chicken stock, celery, salt, onion, butter and peanut butter in slow cooking pot.
Cover and cook on high for 2 to 3 hours.
Add flour and milk that has been dissolved in 1/4 cup of water.
Cook on high for 15 minutes or is slightly thickened, stirring several times.
Sprinkle peanuts over each serving. Makes 4 servings.

title: norwegian pizza
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together, spread on round platter and chill.
Spread 1 bottle of chili sauce.
Layer shrimp and top with cheese.
Sprinkle with oregano to taste.

title: chilaquiles casserole(assemble no more than 4 hours beforehand.)
directions: Put 1/2 chips in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spoon beans over chips; sprinkle 1/2 chicken over beans.
Mix salsa and sour cream together and pour 1/2 mixture over chicken.
Repeat with layer of chips, chicken and salsa.
Sprinkle cheese over top.
Bake uncovered for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: lasagna
directions: Cook meat, sauce and water.
Combine cheese, egg and seasonings.
Layer sauce, noodles, cheese and Parmesan.
Cook on full power 8 minutes.
Simmer 30 minutes.
Stand covered 15 minutes.

title: party punch
directions: Mix Kool-Aid according to directions on package.
(Color may be chosen to suit occasion.)
Chill all ingredients.
Add together at serving time in punch bowl.

title: white cake icing
directions: Mix together and beat 5 minutes.
Add 1 c. sugar.
Beat another 5 minutes.
Scrape bowl often.
Add mixture to butter, crisco, sugar, 1 tsp. vanilla and a pinch of salt.
Beat for 5 minutes more.
I like lots of frosting so I double this recipe.

title: glazed fruit salad
directions: Drain fruit and place in a mixing bowl.
Blend thoroughly the pie mixture and lemon juice.
Chill for several hours before serving.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: low country chicken bogg
directions: Cook chicken, sausage and ham in 8 cups of water until the chicken is done.
Debone chicken removing all skin and fat.
Add onions, rice and pepper and cook on low until rice is done, approximately 1 hour.
Add water, if needed, and salt if desired. Remove from heat and let sit for at least 1 hour.
Makes 5 quarts.

title: 3 bean bake
directions: Cook ground beef; drain.
In 1 teaspoon vegetable oil (or less), saute onion and green pepper.
Combine onion mixture, ground beef and remaining ingredients; stir well.
Spoon mixture into a greased 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour.
This mixture may be placed in a crock-pot.
Bake on high 1 hour; turn to low and let simmer until ready to eat.

title: basic french dressing
directions: Pour all ingredients into a pint jar; shake well.
Store in refrigerator.
Yields 2 cups.

title: chess pie
directions: Mix sugar and flour.
Beat egg yolks.
Add milk and butter. Mix in flour and sugar.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes or until firm.
Add meringue and brown. Best served warm.
Serves 8.

title: brownies
directions: Melt butter and dissolve cocoa. Set aside. Beat eggs and sugar until light and fluffy. Beat in flour, salt and vanilla. Add butter mixture. Add chocolate chips. Put in 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: apple rolls
directions: Stir together apples, nuts and sugar.
Let stand, stirring often, until juicy, about 1 hour.
Mix flour, soda, salt and spices together.
Add apple mixture and stir well.
Blend in butter and vanilla.
Add eggs.
Turn into two greased and floured 1 pound coffee cans.
Tie 2-inch wide band of double foil around top.
Bake at 325° for about 1 hour and 15 minutes, or until tester comes out clean.
Cool on rack 10 minutes.
Remove foil; turn out.
Serve warm with pudding sauce or cold as cake or tea bread.

title: pineapple cheese casserole
directions: Drain pineapple.
Mix pineapple and cheese together.
Mix sugar and flour together.
Combine these and put in greased casserole.
Mix cracker crumbs and melted butter together.
Spread over pineapple mixture.
Bake 350° for 30 minutes.

title: low-fat chocolate brownies
directions: You will also need vegetable cooking spray.

title: mexican dip
directions: Mix all together and heat until cheese is melted.
Serve with your choice of chips.

title: apricot salad
directions: Bring pineapple and juice to a boil.
Add jello, stirring until well mixed.
Cool.
Mix buttermilk, Cool Whip, banana and pecans, adding to jello mixture.
Mix thoroughly.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Chill and serve.

title: graham cracker pecan sponge cake
directions: Beat the egg yolks until thick and lemon colored, gradually beat in 1/2 cup sugar and vanilla.
Add finely crushed cracker crumbs combined with the baking powder.
Fold into the egg mixture.
Add chopped nuts.
Beat egg whites until stiff, add remaining sugar slowly, plus 1/8 teaspoon salt.
Fold into the egg mixture, blending carefully.
Pour into 3 greased wax paper lined pans, bake in moderate oven, 350° for about 30 minutes.
When cool, frost with the following: 1/2 pint whipped cream, 4 tablespoons confectioner's sugar, 1 teaspoon vanilla, 1 cup chopped pecans.

title: michael's mini meat loaves
directions: Mix all together; put in muffin pans (sprayed with Pam).
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until done in middle.
Don't overcook.
Will be dry.
Makes 6 to 8 large ones or 12 small ones.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together except bacon.
Place in meat loaf pan with bacon on top.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Unroll breadsticks; place on waxed paper.
Brush with melted butter.
Combine sugar and cinnamon.
Sprinkle over dough.
Press raisins into dough.
Roll as you would cinnamon rolls.
Place on greased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Drizzle with orange or your favorite icing.

title: poor man's stroganoff
directions: Brown ground beef; drain well.
Add mushrooms, onion, sour cream, salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Add dash of pickapper and Kitchen Bouquet to taste.
Simmer 15 to 30 minutes.
Cook noodles; drain.
Serve stroganoff over noodles.

title: coconut delight
directions: Mix
flour,
cup pecans and margarine.
Press into baking dish to form crust;
bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cool completely.
Mix
cream
cheese
with confectioners sugar; add one box of Cool Whip.
Mix thoroughly; spread over crust.
Mix instant pudding with milk;
stir
until
thick.
Spread
this mixture over the cream cheese
layer.
Sprinkle a small amount of shredded coconut on the pudding
layer.
Spread
one box of Cool Whip on top, then sprinkle
the
remaining
coconut and 1 cup of pecans on top of the Cool Whip.
Chill before serving.

title: cranberries mellow
directions: Mix cranberries, pineapple and sugar; let stand 2 hours.
Add Cool Whip and marshmallows.
Let stand 2 hours.

title: oreo cookie dessert
directions: Crush Oreo cookies and add melted butter; pat into bottom of dish.
Add powdered sugar to soft cream cheese.
Add 1/2 of Cool Whip and stir, then put on top of Oreo crust.
Mix pudding and milk.
Add on top of cream cheese layer, then add remaining Cool Whip on top of pudding layer.
Sprinkle cookie crumbs on top for decoration.
Keep in refrigerator overnight.

title: smoked sausage and dip
directions: Brown sausage in oven at about 350°.
Mix sauce and jam in small pan.
Heat on low until preserves or jam is melted.
Use sausage to dip.

title: barbe-cups
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Brown seasoned beef in small amount of grease; drain.
Stir in barbecue sauce, onion and brown sugar. Place 1 biscuit in each of 10 ungreased muffin cups; press dough up sides to edge of cup.
Spoon hot meat mixture into cups. Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes until golden. Refrigerate any leftovers.

title: rhubarb crunch
directions: Mix flour, oatmeal, brown sugar, butter and cinnamon until crumbly.
Press 1/2 of mixture in 9-inch square greased baking pan.
Combine sugar, cornstarch, water and vanilla and cook until thick and clear.
Place rhubarb on crumbs and cover with sauce. Cover with remaining crumbs.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Serve warm with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: 7 minute frosting
directions: Mix sugar, water and Karo; cook over heat in heavy saucepan until it starts to boil, stirring constantly until boiling starts. Let cook until the syrup strings off like a fine hair.
Have the 4 egg whites beaten stiff; slowly add the syrup mixture to the egg whites.
Beat until cool.
Add marshmallows; beat until melted. Add vanilla.

title: sparkle punch
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well, gradually adding Cool Whip.
Pour into crust.
Let stand in refrigerator for 2 hours before serving.

title: fruit cake cookies
directions: Dredge fruit in cup of flour.
Then mix all ingredients together and drop a teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 270° for 20 minutes.

title: cocoons
directions: Cream butter with sugar and vanilla until light and fluffy. Add 1/2 cup nuts and stir.
Blend flour and remaining nuts and add to mix.
Shape like cocoons on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.
When cool, roll in confectioners sugar. Yields 32 cocoons.

title: shell's cheese log
directions: Mix well the cream cheese and smoked cheese; add mustard, garlic and Worcestershire and mix well.
Add olives and grated Cheddar and mix all ingredients by hand.
Shape into logs on plastic wrap and roll in chopped pecans.
Serve on crackers at room temperature.
Best if let set one day.

title: lime jello salad
directions: Dissolve the jello and cream cheese in the hot water; let set. Add the remaining ingredients together.
Add this mixture to the first mixture; refrigerate until firm.

title: hungarian goulash
directions: Cook macaroni and drain.
Cook ground beef, onions and spices. Add kidney beans and macaroni.
Let simmer together 15 to 20 minutes.

title: potato casserole
directions: Spray pan and mix all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Fat-free ingredients may be used.

title: zucchini appetizer squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Mix ingredients together.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes.
Can be frozen before or after baking.

title: gramps waffles(serves 4)
directions: Beat eggs and milk together.
Add dry ingredients and mix together well.
Stir in melted shortening.
(We use vegetable oil.) Bake in preheated waffle iron.

title: summer punch
directions: Pour all ingredients into punch bowl and stir until Kool-Aid is dissolved.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash, green pepper and onion in water until tender. Drain and mash.
Add margarine and 2 cups cheese (reserving 1 cup to sprinkle on top).
Add eggs, milk and crackers.
Mix well; season to taste.
Place in a shallow 2-quart greased casserole dish. Top with remaining cheese and bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pineapple zucchini
directions: Put zucchini in large bowl and sprinkle pineapple oil over chunks.
Toss well.
On stove combine pineapple juice, sugar and lemon juice.
Heat until sugar is dissolved.
Loosely fill pint jars and put syrup over.
Seal and process in hot water bath 5 minutes.
Do not process over 5 minutes or it will get too soft.

title: cold strawberry soup
directions: Place strawberries in blender or food processor bowl.
Process until well blended.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Chill several hours or overnight.
Makes 8 (1/2 cup) servings.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water; set aside.
Combine milk, sugar, shortening and salt.
Allow to cool.
When cool, add 1 1/2 cups flour.
Then add yeast and egg.
Gradually add 2 cups flour and make soft dough.
Beat well.
Place in greased bowl and let rise until doubled.
Punch down; shape and put in greased pans.
Let rise until doubled.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: breakfast pie
directions: Combine sausage, 2 eggs, cottage cheese, Cheddar cheese and cream cheese together; set aside.
Combine biscuit mix and onions in a bowl.
Combine 2 eggs and milk; pour over biscuit mix.
Stir only until mixture is moistened.
Spoon half of batter into a greased 9-inch dish or pie pan.
Spoon in cheese mixture.
Top with remaining batter.
Sprinkle with toasted sesame seed.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes or until a knife inserted in the center comes out clean.
Let stand 5 minutes before cutting.

title: corn bread salad
directions: Prepare corn bread as directed; break up.
In a large bowl, mix onions, celery, corn, cheeses and mayonnaise.
Chill.

title: elephant stew
directions: Cut elephant into small bite-size pieces.
(This usually takes about 2 months.)
Add enough brown gravy to cover.
Cook over kerosene fire for about 5 weeks at 450°.
This will serve about 4000.
If more are expected, 2 rabbits may be added, but do this only if necessary, as most people do not like hare in their stew.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Brown and drain hamburger and chopped onion.
Place in greased pie pan.
Sprinkle with Cheddar cheese.
Mix Bisquick, milk and eggs together.
Pour over hamburger mixture.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.

title: fruit cake
directions: Put into a large bowl the crumbs, cinnamon, nutmeg, cloves, raisins, dates, walnuts and candied fruits.
Add milk mixture. Mix with spoon, then with hands until crumbs are moistened.
Press firmly into pan lined with wax paper (bottom and side) of a 9-inch tube pan or loaf pan holding about 6 cups.
Cover tightly.
Chill for 2 or 3 days before slicing.
Keep in a cool place at all times.
Makes 3 1/2 pounds.

title: gingerbread
directions: Beat eggs and add to sugar and shortening creamed together. Add molasses and soda.
Add flour and spices alternately with hot water.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: southern rice pudding
directions: Cook rice in 2 cups water.
Cut off heat; add sugar, cinnamon and vanilla and mix.
Turn on heat; add beaten eggs, milk and whipping cream.
Cook over medium heat, stirring until it boils; when it boils, it will thicken.
Remove from heat (will be slightly runny). Garnish with nutmeg.

title: never fail chocolate cake
directions: Mix
butter,
hot
water
and cocoa well.
Add vanilla, white sugar,
sour milk with soda, salt and flour;
mix well. Add unbeaten
eggs
last and beat well.
Batter will be thin. Bake at 375° about 45 minutes.
Frost with Caramel Icing.

title: cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Place oil in a 10-inch black iron frypan; heat in oven 10 minutes.
Combine cornmeal, baking powder and baking soda in medium size mixing bowl.
Beat together the egg and buttermilk carefully.
Stir into dry ingredients; do not overmix.
Stir in hot oil.
Pour batter into hot frypan.
Bake for 30 to 40 minutes, or until golden brown.
Remove from frypan to serving plate.
Cut in pie shaped wedges.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: twice baked potatoes
directions: Bake or microwave potatoes. When done, cut in half lengthwise. Scoop potatoes into a bowl. Add butter and sour cream. Mash with a fork. Add enough milk for mashed potato consistency. Salt and pepper to taste. Put potato mixture back into shells and top with cheese. Microwave until cheese melts or put in 325° oven for 10 minutes.

title: quick and easy candy
directions: Combine sugar and milk in sauce pan. Boil 4 minutes. Stir in cracker crumbs and peanut butter. Drop by spoonful onto waxed paper. Cool until firm.

title: daddy's peanut butter candy
directions: Stir together sugar and milk.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly throughout cooking time.
Cook to soft ball stage, checking in water, for approximately 15-17 minutes.
Reduce heat after a few minutes but maintain a good boil.
When candy is done, remove from heat and add vanilla, salt and peanut butter.
Mix well and pour into buttered 15 x 10 inch pan.
Let cool and cut into pieces.
If thicker pieces are desired, use smaller pan.

title: amish sugar cookies
directions: Cream oil, margarine and sugars until fluffy.
Add vanilla and eggs.
Stir in dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Chill slightly.
Make small balls and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Press with bottom of glass dipped in sugar.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until very lightly browned at 350°.
Makes 100 plus cookies.

title: roast beef gravy
directions: Brown flour in iron skillet that has bottom covered with hot melted Crisco.
Stir in cold water to make a medium gravy.
Add roast beef that has been broken up and onion.
Simmer until onion is tender.
Serve over rice with biscuits and lettuce salad. (Some people like it better over biscuits.)

title: noodle goulash
directions: Brown meat and
onion.
Mix
all ingredients together and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: surprise cheese dip
directions: Saute onion in oleo.
Add tomatoes and simmer 10 minutes.
Add other ingredients and simmer until well blended (about 15 minutes).
Serve hot with tostados.
This can be cooked in crock-pot and keeps hot for several hours.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Wash and hull mushrooms. Cut up stems and fry with sausage, chopped onion and garlic.
Drain. Add sage and cream cheese while hot.
Mix well.
In a large skillet, melt butter.
Place mushrooms in, hulled side down.
Warm gently.
While turning over mushrooms, stuff each.
After stuffing, remove from skillet and drain on wire rack. Top with cheese.
Place under broiler until cheese is bubbly brown (1 to 2 minutes), optional.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Combine all ingredients, except chips.
Reserve some of the cheese and water chestnuts to be mixed with the crushed chips for the top.
Place in large casserole.
Top with chips, cheese and nuts.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake in 400 degree oven for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: squirrel dumplings(southwest missouri's special)
directions: Cut squirrel into serving pieces, season and brown in hot fat. Put in pressure cooker and cover with one (No. 2 1/2) can of sauerkraut.
Add 1/2 cup water and cook for 20 minutes.
This is also delicious with rabbit or chicken.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Mix sugar, oil, eggs and milk.
Add rest of ingredients.
Pour into lightly greased and floured loaf or tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 2 loaves or 1 tube cake.

title: nuts 'n bolts
directions: Melt margarine and mix in corn oil, garlic salt, onion salt and Worcestershire sauce with melted margarine.
Pour over dry ingredients, except the Cheese Tid-Bits.
Add these after the solution is poured over all.
(If oil mixture is poured over the Cheese Tid-Bits, they may get too brown.)
Bake 3 to 4 hours at 200° to 225° in 2 oblong pans.
Stir once half way through the baking time.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Place crescent rolls in jelly roll pan and sprinkle with sugar.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.

title: lime-pineapple salad mold
directions: Sprinkle gelatin powder over cream cheese and mash with a fork.
Add the boiling water.
Beat well with fork or electric mixer.
Add the crushed pineapple and stir until blended.
Pour into mold or glass bowl and chill.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together.
Form a ball and roll in pecans.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: heaton's scalloped potatoes
directions: Cut up potatoes.
Cover a cookie sheet, 1 layer deep.
Cut up butter and cheese; put over potatoes.
Salt and pepper to taste. Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 30 minutes, or until done. Crumble bacon on top and serve.

title: chicken parisienne
directions: Prepare 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Lay washed chicken flat in pan.
Combine soup, mushrooms, sour cream and wine until blended and pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° about 1 1/2 hours.
Serve over steamed rice or noodles.

title: quick pecan pie
directions: Place pecan pieces in pie shell, saving a few whole ones for the top.
Beat eggs, butter, sugar and vanilla together.
