Pour over the pecans and place remaining pecans on top.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Do not double this recipe as it will not cook as well.

title: japanese fruit cake #2
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Add flour and baking powder alternately with the milk.
Divide batter into 2 equal parts.
To one bowl, add vanilla; to the other bowl, add spices and raisins.
Bake in 4 greased cake pans, 2 dark layers and 2 white layers. Put together with filling.
Cover with white icing. Sprinkle with coconut, if desired.

title: sante fe burrito bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large skillet over medium heat, cook meat until no longer pink.
Drain well.
Stir in water, chilies and seasoning mix.
Add cereal, stirring until well combined.
Set aside.
Roll bread dough into a 15 x 10-inch rectangle.
Spread 2 cups reserved meat mixture in a 4-inch wide strip lengthwise down center of bread.
Top with cheese.
Cover with remaining meat mixture.
Bring sides of dough up over filling.
Seal top and edges well.
Place seam side down on baking sheet.
Brush with margarine.
Sprinkle with chili powder.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes or until golden brown.
Slice and serve with salsa, guacamole, sour cream, black olives.
Great with Fajita Style Nachos.
Serves 6.

title: boiled cookies
directions: Bring sugar, milk and butter to a boil.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter, oats, coconut, cocoa, vanilla and salt.
Add nuts, if desired.
Mix and spread in a buttered dish or drop on waxed paper.

title: east salad
directions: Mix cottage cheese and jello together.	Fold in pineapple
and then Cool Whip.
Flavor improves if it
sets
a
few hours before serving.

title: pesto
directions: Put in food processor.

title: crustless egg custard
directions: Mix margarine, sugar, eggs, milk, vanilla and flour together. Cook at 300° until firm in middle.

title: onion soup dip
directions: Blend, chill and serve with chips.

title: soupa
directions: In saucepan, saute onion in butter.
Add chilies, soup and milk.
Bring to a bubble; stir in chicken.
Layer chips, soup and cheese in a casserole dish.
Repeat layers.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: sausage and rice casserole
directions: Brown sausage, onion and pepper.
Drain.
Cook rice by directions on box.
Add rice, meat mixture and soups.
Pour into casserole dish and top with grated cheese.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: king ranch chicken casserole
directions: Saute onion and bell pepper in hot oil in a large skillet over medium heat 5 minutes until tender.
Stir in chicken and next 6 ingredients.
Remove from heat.
Tear tortillas into 1-inch pieces. Layer 1/3 of tortilla pieces in bottom of lightly greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Top with 1/3 of chicken mixture and 2/3 cup cheese.
Repeat layers twice.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes. Yield:
6 to 8 servings.

title: perfect pie crustmakes 5 shells
directions: Place first three ingredients in a large bowl, mix well with a fork. Add shortening, mix until ingredients are crumbly. In a small bowl, beat together with a fork; water vinegar, and egg. Combine 2 mixtures, stirring with a fork until all ingredients are moistened. Divide into 5 portions. Shape each portion into a round flat patty ready for rolling. Wrap each in plastic wrap and chill at least 1/2 hour in refrigerator before rolling. When ready to roll pie crust, lightly flour both sides and roll lightly on floured board. Place in pie pans. Makes 2 double crusts and one pie shell. Prick if for a shell and bake at 450° for 15 to 20 minutes. For double crust, bake as directed in individual recipe. Patties can be frozen.

title: crab puffs
directions: Bring water to a boil and add margarine.
Return to boil.
Add flour all at once.
Remove from heat and beat in 1 egg at a time. Then add the scallions, crabmeat, Cheddar cheese, dry mustard and Worcestershire sauce.
Drop on cookie sheets by spoonfuls.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Can be frozen.

title: beef and bacon casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and place in casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: becca's chicken chow mein
directions: Heat oil, salt, & pepper in deep skillet or Dutch oven.
Add cabbage, celery, bean sprouts, water chestnuts, & sugar.
Stir in chicken broth; cook about 10 minutes.
Mix cornstarch, water, & soy sauce; add to vegetable mixture. stir until mixture thickens.
Add chicken and heat.

title: chili con carne
directions: Saute onion in shortening, soup and beans.
Cover and simmer slowly 30 minutes.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Place hash browns in a 9 x 13 pan.
Pour soups and sour cream on top.
Top with cheeses.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour to1 1/2 hours.

title: swiss vegetable medley
directions: Combine all ingredients, except 1/2 cup cheese and 1/2 cup onions.
Pour into shallow 1-quart casserole dish.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 30 minutes or until vegetables are done.
Top with remaining cheese and onions.
Bake, uncovered, 5 minutes or until onions are golden.
Makes 6 servings.

title: mixed olive relish
directions: Mix all together. Use as appetizer spread or as an addition to sandwiches.

title: down east fish chowder
directions: Fry salt pork in deep kettle.
When crisp, remove pieces of pork and put fish, potatoes and onions in kettle.
Cover with the boiling water.
Simmer 1/2 hour or until the potato is tender. Add the milk and cook 5 minutes longer.
Thicken with flour when milk is added.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Mix together; pour into 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: taco skillet
directions: Cook sausage links as directed on package, using a 10-inch skillet; drain and remove from skillet.
Heat margarine in skillet until hot.
Cook onion until tender.
Stir in seasoning mix and water.
Heat to boiling, stirring occasionally, until liquid is absorbed and rice is tender.
Stir in tomatoes, pepper, beans and olives.
Arrange sausage on top.
Sprinkle with cheese and cover and heat through.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: swedish pancakes
directions: Combine eggs, milk and butter.
Beat well.
Add sifted dry ingredients gradually, beating constantly during addition.
Pour 3 tablespoons batter onto hot griddle for each cake.
Bake until top is bubbly.
Turn and brown remaining side.
Fill with jelly or fruit and roll.
Roll again in confectioners sugar.
May be served with butter and syrup if desired.
Yield:
16 to 18 pancakes.

title: dump it cake
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Dump applesauce and pineapple into pan.
On top of this spread the package of dry yellow cake, do not stir.
Melt butter, pour on top of cake mix.
Sprinkle nuts over batter.
Do not stir.

title: mexican dip
directions: Spread cream cheese evenly in bottom of 9 x 11-inch glass pan. Spread chili over cream cheese, then pour picante sauce over. Cover top with cheese.
Microwave on High for 8 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Cook broccoli; drain and set aside. Drain mushrooms; set aside. Saut butter or margarine, onions and chopped cheese. When cheese is melted, add soup and all ingredients. Place mixture in casserole dish. Crush 1 sleeve Ritz crackers and sprinkle on top. Bake until crackers brown.

title: garden marinade
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients in a large, shallow pan.
Combine remaining ingredients, mixing well.
Pour marinade over vegetables; toss lightly.
Cover and chill 8 to 10 hours or overnight.
Drain before serving.

title: "must-have" m&m cookies
directions: Blend shortening and both sugars in bowl. Beat in vanilla and eggs. Sift dry ingredients together. Add to sugar mixture; blend well. Drop by teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet; put candy on top. Bake at 375° for 10 minutes. Makes about 40 (2-inch) cookies.

title: frosted meat loaf
directions: Mix thoroughly beef, 1/2 cup soup, bread, onion, egg, salt and pepper.
Shape firmly into loaf; place in shallow baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Frost loaf with mashed potatoes; bake 15 minutes more.
Blend remaining soup, water and drippings.
Heat. Serve over loaf.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: "the best" brownies
directions: Blend oil, sugar and vanilla in a mixing bowl.
Add eggs; beat well with spoon.
Combine flour, cocoa, baking powder and salt. Gradually add to egg mixture until well blended.
Stir in nuts (optional).
Spread in greased 9-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool in pan.
Frost, if desired.
Makes 16 brownies! Double the recipe, brownies disappear quickly!

title: triple chocolate cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 10-inch Bundt cake pan and dust with unsweetened cocoa powder
Combine cake mix, pudding mix, eggs, sour cream, oil, water, mayonnaise and liqueur in large bowl of electric mixer.
Beat on medium speed until smooth, about 2 minutes.
Stir in chocolate chips and almonds.
Pour batter into prepared pan.
Bake until tester inserted near center comes out clean, about 55 to 60 minutes.
Cool in pan for 5 minutes. Invert onto wire rack.
Let rest 10 minutes before removing pan. Let cool.

title: lemon pie
directions: Mix first two ingredients together, then add lemonade and cream cheese.
Pour into graham cracker crust; chill.
You may use cherry pie mix over top.
Makes 2 large pies or 3 small.

title: strawberry yogurt salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Drain strawberries, reserving juice; set strawberries aside.

Combine gelatin, reserved strawberry juice and yogurt in container of electric blender; blend until smooth. Pour mixture into a bowl; fold in strawberries. Pour into a 12 x 8 x 2-inch dish and chill until firm.
Yields 12 servings.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients
and
add crushed corn flakes last. Bake for about one hour
at
This
makes one large meat loaf or two small ones.

title: shrimp ball
directions: Mix together and roll in chopped pecans.
Chill overnight.

title: brown rice
directions: Place all ingredients in glass baking dish. Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: christmas punch
directions: Combine lime drink mix, sugar, water and pineapple juice. Just before serving, add to ginger ale.
Pour the entire mixture over ice cubes.
A sprig of mint or bits of cherries may be added. Serves 75.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Mix together cake mix, pudding mix, eggs, milk and corn oil in large mixing bowl and beat 5 minutes.
Add 1 tablespoon vanilla. Gently stir in milk chocolate morsels and German sweet chocolate (grated).
Pour in greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.
Sprinkle powdered sugar over cake.

title: mexicali soup
directions: Saute onion and garlic in oil till tender.
Add ground beef and cook until browned.
Drain.
Add broth, water, corn, tomatoes, zucchini, celery and oregano.
Bring to a boil.
Add rice and flavor packet.
Reduce heat and simmer for 20 minutes.
Serve and sprinkle with cheese.

title: brunswick stew
directions: Mix all together and cook until done.
This stew is good with slaw and cornbread.

title: potato chip tuna casserole
directions: Cover bottom of casserole dish with crushed potato chips.
Add layer of green peas, layer of flaked tuna, layer of potato chips and layer of green peas.
Add another layer of flaked tuna and top off with a layer of crushed chips.
Cover whole casserole with can of cream of mushroom soup.
Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: sea burgers
directions: Drain and flake seafood.
Cut cheese into cubes.
Combine all ingredients.
Fill 12 buns.
Wrap in foil.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: mindy's lemon bars
directions: Mix eggs, sugar, dash of salt, lemon juice, flour and baking soda.
Beat with beater and pour onto hot crust.
Bake 25 minutes longer.
Cut into squares and sprinkle with confectioners sugar.

title: shrimp pies(garidopites)
directions: Whip cream cheese with an electric mixer.
Beat in egg yolk. With a spatula mix in the parsley, scallions, lemon juice, salt, shrimp and cheese.
Chill one hour.
Stack 2 filo sheets together. Cutting through both sheets, cut into strips 2 inches wide by 16 inches long.
Brush with melted butter.
Place a teaspoon of filling on one end of the strip.
Fold one corner of the strip to the opposite side, forming a triangle and enclosing the filling. Continue folding to end of the strip.
Fold one corner of the strip to the opposite side, forming a triangle and enclosing the filling.
Continue folding to end of strip maintaining the triangular shape.
Brush with melted butter.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet and bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Serve hot.
Makes 30 appetizers.

title: butter syrup
directions: Mix all ingredients in medium saucepan.
Bring to a boil, stirring occasionally; boil for 7 minutes.
After boiling for 7 minutes, add vanilla; stir to mix well.
Serve warm with pancakes or waffles.

title: spiced cereal balls
directions: Cream butter, sugar and vanilla.
Sift flour and cinnamon; combine with crushed cereal.
Add to creamed mixture.
Add nuts and shape into balls.
Bake on greased cookie sheet at 350° for 25 minutes.
Remove and roll in powdered sugar.

title: south pacific chicken
directions: In a small saucepan, melt margarine.
Stir in onion soup and cornstarch, then reserved pineapple juice and lemon juice. Arrange chicken and pineapple chunks in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour onion mixture over chicken and bake 45 minutes until chicken is tender.
Serve with hot vegetables or over rice.
Makes 6 servings.

title: cabbage supreme casserole
directions: Cut cabbage in small wedges and cook in boiling, salted water until tender.
Drain cabbage and place in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch casserole.
To prepare white sauce, melt butter in saucepan; blend in flour, salt and pepper.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly. Pour white sauce over cabbage; bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: strawberry crumb cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Set aside 1/2 c of dry cake mix.
Mix together cream cheese and strawberries on low for 1 minute, slowly mix in cake mix.
Beat 2 minutes on medium speed.
Spread into a 13 x 9 pan that has been sprayed with Pam.
Sprinkle 1/2 c reserved cake mix on top.
Bake 30 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Serves 15.

title: chicken fried steak
directions: Take cutlets and salt lightly on both sides.
Blend egg and milk into bowl.
Put flour on foil so that you can dip meat into flour.
Take cutlets and dip in flour, then in egg mixture, then back into the flour.
Put in frying pan and cook until meat is golden brown.

title: coffee cake
directions: Mix together cake mix, puddings, oil, water and eggs.
Pour 1/2 batter in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix brown sugar, cinnamon and walnuts.
Spoon half the mixture over cake mix.
Spoon remaining cake mix on top and sprinkle rest of brown sugar mix on top of this.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: peanut butter squares
directions: Pat by hand in a 9 x 9-inch pan.

title: "7" minute white frosting
directions: Beat while boiling.
Cook in double boiler until thick.
Wait until removed from stove to add flavoring.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix ingredients well, adding one at a time, in a buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour or until firm and golden brown.

title: country captain
directions: Sprinkle chicken with garlic salt and paprika.
Brown over medium heat.
Set chicken aside.
Add onion, peppers, and garlic powder to skillet.
Cook about 4 minutes, or until vegetables begin to wilt.
Add next 10 ingredients, stir well.
Add chicken, and cook covered about 40 minutes on medium heat, or until chicken is tender.
Divide evenly and serve each portion over 1/2 c. rice. Makes 2 servings.

title: baked beans with ground chuck(club member: ben steadman)
directions: Brown ground chuck, onion and garlic; pour off grease. Mix together with beans, brown sugar, ketchup, Worcestershire sauce, barbecue sauce, vinegar and lemon juice. Pour into 9 x 12-inch casserole. Bake, covered, for 1 hour at 350°.

title: chicken and stuffing casserole
directions: Layer chicken, stuffing, sour cream and soup in a casserole. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 40 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: chicken and noodle casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients (except last three) in large bowl.

title: ice box fruit pie
directions: Cut fruit, nuts and marshmallows.
Mix with cream and crackers.
Crush crackers.
Mix marshmallows with fruit mixture. Pack in pan.
Place in refrigerator one day before cutting.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar.
Melt oleo and add other ingredients. Pour into 2 pie crusts.
Bake at 300° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: roast beef
directions: Put beef on a large piece of foil. Sprinkle salt and dry onion soup on roast. Add mushroom soup. Close the foil tight and cook for about 1 1/2 hours. Then open up the foil and add potatoes and carrots. Cover again and cook about 1 1/2 hours.

title: lemon pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Cream margarine and shortening.
Add sugar and flavoring.
Add one egg at a time.
Sift flour, salt, and baking powder together.
Then add flour and milk alternately. Grease and slightly flour Bundt or pound cake pan.
Pour mixture in pan and bake for 1 hour and 20 minutes at 325°.

title: mom's super potato casserole
directions: Peel cooked potatoes and cube.
Add cheese and melted butter. Mix lightly.
Add onion, salt and pepper.
Add sour cream.
Mix lightly.
Dot with butter.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.
Makes 8 servings.

title: pigs in a blanket
directions: Split hot dogs lengthwise.
Pat cheese inside slit.
Wrap each hot dog with 1 crescent roll.
Bake as directed on roll package.

title: louisiana red beans with white rice
directions: Soak beans overnight; drain and rinse.
Put beans and ham in kettle, then add water and salt.
Bring to a boil, then reduce heat and cook slowly for 45 minutes.
Add other ingredients and cook slowly for 2 hours.
Serve over hot rice.
For the working person, this can be made in the crock-pot.
Soak the beans overnight; drain and rinse, then place all the ingredients in the crock-pot on low. Cook for at least 10 hours, then serve over hot rice.

title: strawberry cookies
directions: Combine eggs and shortening.
Add 1/2 dry cake mix.
Beat well.
Add rest of dry cake mix, nuts and coconut; mix well (maybe by hand).
Drop by teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: layered salad
directions: Break lettuce in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Layer celery and layer onion.
Mix the sour cream, sugar, mayonnaise and vinegar.
Pour over the layers, then crumble bacon over.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Cover tightly and refrigerate for at least 3 hours before serving.

title: peach bete or apple
directions: Put apples or peaches in casserole.
Mix together oatmeal, brown sugar, cinnamon, melted butter and chopped walnuts.
Put on top of peaches.
Press down evenly with hands. Bake at 375° for 1 1/2 hours until Bete is brown and is dry, not wet.
Very good.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Spread raw rice on bottom of 9 x 13-inch glass pan.
Arrange chicken pieces on top of rice.
Mix remaining ingredients together.
Pour over chicken.
Bake uncovered at 325° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: spiral macaroni salad
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients well.
Add choice of raw vegetables, chopped very fine:
onions, celery, zucchini, tomatoes, peas, red and green peppers, parsley, etc.

title: peanut butter chewie
directions: Put syrup in a large boiler (4 quarts).
Sprinkle sugar over it and slowly bring to a boil over low heat.
Do not stir much.
When it comes to a rolling boil, add margarine, peanut butter and corn flakes.
Pour on buttered pan, about 11 x 16-inch.
Press evenly over pan.
Cut in desired size when partly cool.

title: oatmeal sheet cake
directions: Mix all ingredients well. Pour into greased & floured sheet pan. Bake at 350° for 35-40 minutes. When cooled, sprinkle top with powdered sugar.

title: california paella
directions: Combine all ingredients in medium saucepan, stirring to blend. Bring to a boil, cover, lower heat and simmer 5 minutes.
Turn off heat, leaving pan on stove.
Let stand, tightly covered, for 10 minutes.

title: chicken a la king
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Rinse peas to separate.
Heat peas, mushrooms, chicken, soup, sour cream, milk, salt and pepper to boiling, stirring frequently.

title: scalloped turkey
directions: Make sauce of eggs, flour, milk and broth.
Spoon dressing in a greased 9 x 13-inch dish.
Arrange cubed turkey or chicken over the dressing.
Pour sauce over it.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs. Garnish with pimento strips.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 30 minutes.

title: crispy baked chicken
directions: Remove all skin from chicken.
Rinse and dry thoroughly.
Dip in milk.
Mix corn flake crumbs with spices.
Roll chicken in crumbs.
Let stand briefly so coating will adhere.
Place chicken in an oiled pan (line pan with foil for easy cleanup).
Pieces should not touch.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes or more.
Makes 4 servings.
Contains 270 calories.

title: blueberry cake
directions: Place blueberries in bottom of casserole.
Sprinkle sugar, cake mix and nuts over blueberries.
Pour melted oleo over top. Bake at 350° until well browned.

title: rainbow punch
directions: Combine juices in punch bowl and add sherbet. Pour ginger ale over just before serving. Makes approximately 25 (6-ounce) servings.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix stuffing, water and 1 stick margarine.
Combine and press 1/2 mixture on bottom of greased baking dish.
Mix rest of ingredients and place over stuffing, then put rest of stuffing on top.
Beat 2 eggs with 1/2 cup milk and pour over mixture.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Remove from refrigerator 1 hour before baking.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: lemon lush
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter in pan.
Combine melted butter, flour and nuts; mash in pan and bake for 12 to 15 minutes. Cool.
Combine sugar, cream cheese and 1 cup Cool Whip (reserving one cup for top layer).
Spread on cooled crust layer.
Mix pudding and milk.
Spread on cream cheese and sugar layer.
Top with remaining Cool Whip.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: chicken with mushroom cream sauce
directions: Melt butter in deep frying pan.
Season chicken with salt and pepper and cook until lightly brown and slightly firm.
Remove chicken and add mushrooms and onion to pan.
Saute until golden. Sprinkle flour over mushrooms and onion and stir over medium heat for 2 minutes.
Add broth, cream and rosemary.
Boil gently until slightly thickened.
Return chicken to pan and simmer for 10 to 15 minutes.
Serve hot with your favorite rice and vegetable.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix together and store in jar.
Use 3 to 4 teaspoons per cup of boiling water.

title: sausage cheese bites
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Brown, crumble and drain sausage. Combine Bisquick mix with milk; add cheese and sausage.
Add more milk to whip to drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.
Brown in 350° oven for 8 minutes.
Serve hot or cold.

title: mini cheesecakes
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients to make graham crumbs; place enough in each cup to fill bottom.
Mix last 4 ingredients and fill each cup half full.
Use foil baking cups and bake in oven at 375° for 12 minutes.
Cool and top with cherry or blueberry pie filling or crushed pineapple.

title: potato hash browns
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients together and place in a casserole baking dish.
Top with a little grated cheese and crushed corn flakes.
Dribble melted butter over the corn flakes (optional).

title: whole wheat pizza(makes two 12-inch pizzas.)
directions: Set aside 1 cup all-purpose flour.
In large bowl, mix remaining flours, undissolved yeast and salt.
Heat water and oil until hot to touch (125° to 130°); stir
into dry mixture.
Mix in enough reserved flour to make stiff dough.
Knead on lightly floured surface until smooth and elastic, about 5 minutes.
Cover; let rest 10 minutes.
Divide dough in half.
Roll and stretch each piece to a 13-inch circle.
Place on 2 (12-inch) round pizza pans or 2 baking sheets, coated with Pam and sprinkled with cornmeal (if desired).
Shape edge into standing rim of dough.
Top with favorite pizza sauce and toppings, dividing evenly.
Bake at 400° until crust is golden, about 20 to 30 minutes.
Cut into wedges to serve.

title: walnut peacherino salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in water.
Add lemon juice and peach syrup; cool until thickened.
Add walnuts.
Arrange peaches and cherries in an 8 x 4 x 4-inch loaf pan.
Cover with 1 cup gelatin; chill until firm.
To remaining gelatin, add sour cream.
Pour over fruit layer; chill.
Unmold and serve with mayonnaise.

title: egg brunch
directions: Place bread in bottom of 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Place sausage on top of bread.
Sprinkle with cheese.

title: sheehan's cranberry salad
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into a pie plate or round cake pan. Freeze.
Let thaw 1/2 hour before serving.
Cut into pie slices and serve on lettuce.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Melt margarine slightly and cool.
Mix sugar and flour. Stir in
margarine
and
eggs, one at a time, beating lightly with a spoon after each addition.
Add buttermilk and vanilla. Mix thoroughly.
Pour into an unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: strawberry heaven
directions: Pour strawberries, lemon juice and milk into large serving bowl and mix well.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Break up cake into bite size pieces, and fold into strawberry mixture.
Refrigerate at least 3 hours before serving.

title: quick and easy casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In heavy skillet cook beef with salt until browned, stirring to break into small pieces.
With slotted spoon, transfer beef into large bowl.
Add potatoes, soup, sour cream, cheese and chopped onion.
Mix well.
Spread into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake 30 minutes. Top with fried onions. Bake 15 minutes more or until bubbly.
Makes 8 servings.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish, pressing into the dish.
Bake at 350° for 5 minutes; cool.

title: brown bread(yields 3 cans or 2 loaves)
directions: Cook raisins in water for 5 minutes; cool.
Cream shortening and sugar; beat in egg.
Add raisin mixture.
Sift flour, soda and salt together.
Add to raisin mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour in cans or loaf pans.

title: hot tater salad
directions: Cook and peel taters.
Cube cheese and taters.
Mix with onions and mayonnaise.
Saute bacon.
Sprinkle on top of tater mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: sue's baked onions
directions: Place onions, carrots and potatoes into a lightly greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix soups, starch, chicken flavor and soy milk. Pour mixture over the top.
Dot with butter.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese over all.
Sprinkle with parsley.
Add pepper to taste. Cover with foil.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: women's retreat treats
directions: Put the first 6 ingredients in a bowl; mix together.
Melt the almond bark; pour over mixture and stir until well coated.
Spread on wax paper until hard.
Break up and put in bowl.

title: buns
directions: Stir milk, yeast, eggs, cold water, salt, butter and sugar together.
Add flour, one cup at a time, until texture is consistent.
Let rise for about 1 hour.
Divide into loaves or biscuits.
Let rise.
Bake at 350° until golden.

title: chicken divan
directions: Drain broccoli and place in dish.
Add cut up chicken.
Mix soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry powder.
Pour over chicken and broccoli.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Mix butter and cracker crumbs.
Sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: potato chip chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Melt butter in a small pot.
Add garlic to it and let it cool slightly.
Crumble potato chips in food processor by pulsing for 30 seconds, or place paper towel over chips and roll back and forth with a rolling pin until chips resemble crumbs.
Mix in black pepper.
You will have 1/2 cup. Place crumbs on a large plate.
Cover a large baking sheet with aluminum foil.
Dip one chicken cutlet into butter garlic mixture. Place cutlet on potato chip crumbs and press down slightly to insure crumbs stick.
Turn cutlet over and repeat on other side.

title: chili
directions: Chop onions, bell pepper and celery.
Cook these in oil for 2 to 3 minutes.
Add meat and cook until meat crumbles.
Add all remaining ingredients and cook on low heat for 1 hour.
If chili is too thick, add a little more water.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: apple stuffing(health conscious)
directions: Cook onions and celery in margarine for 5 minutes, or until tender.
Combine onions and celery with all other dry ingredients. Add broth; toss lightly.
Stuffs a 10 to 12-pound turkey.

title: hawaiian graham cracker cake
directions: Cream the butter and sugar; add eggs and beat well.
Add cracker crumbs and baking powder and beat well.
Add milk, vanilla, coconut and nuts.
Beat until blended.
Pour into 2 buttered 9-inch cake pans.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: cry baby cookies
directions: In a bowl, cream together butter and sugar.
Add and beat in egg and molasses in a separate bowl.
Mix flour, soda, cloves, allspice, cinnamon and ginger thoroughly.
Slowly add to wet mixture until completely mixed together.
Chill dough.
Roll into 1/2-inch balls.
Dip into sugar.
Place balls sugar side up on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake in a preheated oven at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix corn
and
eggs.
Stir
in sugar, onion and seasonings. Add
milk
and cheese.
Mix well.
Pour into buttered 3 quart casserole.
Dot
with butter.
Bake, uncovered, in 400° oven 1 hour
or until knife comes out clean.
Stir once after 30 minutes cooking.
Serves 8.

title: margarita
directions: Fill blender with 1-inch crushed ice.
Pour slightly thawed daiquiri mix over ice.
Add full can of tequila and 1/2 can of Triple Sec.
Add egg white, cover blender and turn on high for 3 minutes.
Serve in glasses whose rim is dipped in lime juice and salt.
Chill glasses if you have time.

title: sweet potato souffle(magic topping)
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put into greased baking dish; cover with topping.

title: chocolate rum balls
directions: Mix all together (except powdered sugar)
and shape into round bite size balls.
Roll in powdered sugar.
Store in refrigerator 5 to 7 days, in covered container, before eating. Makes 6 to 7 dozen.

title: pasta and cream sauce
directions: Cook fresh vegetables to desired tenderness.
Cook onion. Mix all ingredients together, except milk.
Stir, adding a little milk at a time, until you reach the desired consistency.
For a complete dish, you can add cooked salmon or cooked chicken.

title: chicken creole bake
directions: Bake chicken 30 minutes uncovered at 350°.
Mix all ingredients; pour over chicken and bake another 30 minutes.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Mix in shortening and milk. Roll out as pie crust.
Cut into 6 squares.
Place an apple in center of each square.
Divide sugar evenly and fill center of each apple with sugar and cinnamon.
Bring dough up around apple; seal well and place in 2-inch deep baking dish.

title: zucchini parmesan
directions: Wash and cut spears 1/2 x 4-inches small, crisp zucchini.
Dip in mixture of eggs, beaten with a little milk.
Roll in flour, salt and pepper generously.

title: 6 cup salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together well and chill.

title: coconut pecan cream pie
directions: Mix ingredients.
Cook until thick.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Sprinkle with nutmeg, pecan chips, and coconut.
Bake at 325° for 10 minutes.

title: hershey's light chocolate brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Lightly spray 8-inch square baking pan with light vegetable spray.
In medium saucepan over low heat, melt spread.
Add sugar; stir until well blended.
Remove from heat.
Stir in cocoa and vanilla.
Add egg substitute; stir to blend.
Stir in flour and walnuts.
Pour batter into prepared pan. Bake 25 minutes or until edges begin to pull away from sides of pan.
Cool in pan on wire rack.
Sprinkle powdered sugar over top. Cut into 16 squares.
Per square:
Calories 100, fat 3 g, cholesterol 1 mg, sodium 55 mg.

title: stir and roll crust(double crust)
directions: Mix flour.
Pour Wesson oil and milk into measuring
cup (don't stir).
Add this mixture to flour. Stir until
mixed
well. Press into smooth ball.
Cut into halves.
Flatten slightly and roll.

title: beas salad(dessert)
directions: Mix all ingredients except jello.
After mixing pour jello on top.
Stir into other ingredients until well mixed.
Pour in large pan.
Keep covered and refrigerate.

title: fried okra
directions: Place pan drippings or shortening in a large skillet.
Wash the raw okra.
Add the salt and pepper to the cornmeal (or flour). Mix well.
Cut the okra into thick, circular rounds.
Roll each okra round in the cornmeal or flour mixture.
Fry each piece (as many as you can fit in a pan without the sides touching each other) in the hot grease.

title: taco roll-ups
directions: Drain pimentos, chiles and olives.
Mix everything, except tortillas, together.
Spread on tortillas.
Roll up.
Wrap in plastic wrap.
Chill 2 hours.
Slice and serve.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Beat all ingredients together quickly; pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake 35 minutes at 350°.

title: texas brag cake
directions: Pour cherry pie filling and pineapple in a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Crumble dry cake mix over the fruit.
Drizzle melted butter over the cake mixture.
Add pecans on top.
Bake at 350°
or 40 minutes, uncovered.
Cover with foil and bake 20 minutes more.

title: magic fruit cake
directions: Combine mincemeat, nuts, candied fruit, condensed milk and egg.

Combine flour and baking soda. Stir into other ingredients. Line 10-inch tube pan with waxed paper and grease with shortening. Pour batter into pan and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or until center springs back.

title: dumplings
directions: Mix well.
Drop by teaspoon into boiling soup.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Cook milk and sugar for 5 minutes.
Add Marshmallow Creme, peanut butter, butter and vanilla.
Beat and pour into greased pan.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs with 1/2 cup margarine.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan and bake 5 to 8 minutes in 350° oven.
Cool.

title: williamsburg orange cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour baking pan(s), 13 x 9 x 2-inch, or two 8 or 9-inch round pans.
Mix all ingredients in large bowl.
Blend a half-minute at low speed, scraping bowl constantly.
Beat 3 minutes at high speed, scraping bowl occasionally.

title: broccoli-cauliflower casserole
directions: Baking Temperature: 350°.
Baking Time: 30 minutes.

title: beef 'n' tater casserole
directions: Brown beef and spread in pan.
Top with onion and Tater Tots. Mix soups together and spoon over Tater Tots.
Sprinkle with green chilies.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake for 20 to 30 minutes at 350° or until bubbly.

title: six can tuna bake
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large casserole.
Bake for 35 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: crock-pot swiss steak
directions: Dredge meat with the flour, salt and pepper mixture.
In a large Dutch oven heat oil and brown steak on both sides.
Remove meat to crockpot.
Add onion, celery, Worcestershire sauce, sherry, soup and water.
Cover and cook on HIGH
for 6 hours or on LOW for 8 hours.
Makes 4 servings.

title: macadamia nut pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Combine eggs, sugar, flour, butter, corn syrup, nuts and vanilla.
Pour into pie shell and bake for 15 minutes.
Reduce oven temperature to 350° and bake an additional 40 minutes or until golden brown.

title: sausage pinwheels
directions: Mix Bisquick according to directions.
Roll out dough to 1/4-inch thickness.
Spread sausage over dough.
Starting at one side, gently roll dough as if making a jelly roll.
Wrap rolled dough with foil and freeze overnight.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix the pudding mix with the crushed pineapple and juice.
Mix in rest of ingredients.
Refrigerate for a couple of hours before serving.

title: chocolate morsel pie
directions: Combine sugar and flour, mixing well.
Stir in eggs and butter. Add pecans, chocolate morsels and vanilla.
Mix well.
Pour into pastry shell.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: bran muffins
directions: Mix all dry ingredients together.
Add eggs, buttermilk and oil.
Add nuts, if desired.

title: pizza dough
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Add oil.
Combine flour, salt and sugar in second bowl and mix.
Add dry ingredients to wet ingredients.

title: sock-it-to-me-cake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. For filling, combine 2 tablespoons of cake mix, with brown sugar, cinnamon and pecans. Set aside.

title: grated sweet potato pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients in large bowl.
Grease with margarine or spray Pam on 2-quart casserole dish.
Pour all ingredients in casserole dish.
Bake in 350° preheated oven for 30 minutes or microwave on full power 12 to 14 minutes.
Let stand 20 minutes before serving.
Great Thanksgiving dinner dish!!!

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Layer 1/2 of crumbs on bottom of Pyrex dish, 9 x 9-inch.
Mix ingredients.
Spoon over crumbs.
Add remaining crumbs on top. Dot with butter or oleo.
Bake, uncovered, 30 minutes at 350°.

title: mom's baked chicken
directions: Cut chicken up into equal pieces and place in casserole dish. Combine soups with water and pour over chicken.
Cover with foil and bake in preheated 350° oven for 1 1/2 hours.
Remove cover and allow chicken to brown.
Baked chicken, vegetable salad and rice make an easy meal.

title: sunday glazed carrots(microwave)
directions: Wash and cut carrots into 1/2 inch diagonal slices.
Place in 1 quart casserole with butter and brown sugar.
Cover and microwave at High 9 to 11 minutes, stirring after 5 minutes.

title: carrots au gratin
directions: Combine corn flake crumbs and 2 Tbsp. margarine; set aside. Add onion to remaining margarine and saute over low heat.
Add flour, salt and pepper.
Stir in milk.
Increase heat to medium, cook until bubbly and thickened, stirring constantly.
Add cheese and stir until smooth.
Stir in carrots and parsley.
Spread in shallow 1 1/2 quart baking dish and sprinkle with crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until crumbs are brown.
Serves 8.

title: orange slice cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Mix pecans, coconut and orange slices in 1/2 cup flour; set aside.
Mix in remaining flour alternately with buttermilk (in which soda has been added) into butter and sugar mixture.
Stir in floured candy mixture. Bake in greased Bundt pan at 250° for 2 1/2 hours.

title: beef and asparagus stir-fry
directions: In small bowl, combine water, soy sauce, cornstarch and garlic powder.
Blend well. Set aside.

title: meat balls
directions: Make meatballs in 1-inch diameter.
Brown and drain off excess fat.
Add
chopped onion and brown.
Add Worcestershire and tomato juice.
Bring
to
a
boil and lower heat.	Stir in taco seasoning.	Pour
into
slow cooker and let cook all day. When you are
ready to eat, add cornstarch (2 to 3 tablespoons mixed with a
small
amount of water).
Stir until thickened. Serve alone or on spaghetti.

title: outrageous chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Beat sugars, margarine, peanut butter, vanilla and eggs in large bowl with wooden spoon until creamy and well blended.
Mix together flour, oats, baking soda and salt, then add to creamed mixture.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Drop dough by tablespoons (rounded) about 2 inches apart onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool 1 minute before removing from cookie sheet.
Makes about 4 dozen cookies.

title: chicken and rice bake
directions: About 1 1/4 hours before serving:
In 13 x 9-inch baking dish, stir first 6 ingredients until mixed.
Arrange chicken, skin side up, over mixture.
Sprinkle chicken with paprika.
Cover pan tightly with foil.
Bake in 375°
oven 45 minutes.
Remove foil from pan.
Bake, uncovered, 20 minutes longer or until chicken and rice are tender with most of liquid absorbed, occasionally stirring rice with fork.
Garnish with celery leaves.
Makes 4 servings.

title: butter-fried chicken
directions: In large skillet, combine celery, onion, bay leaf, salt and 1 cup water.
Add chicken.
Bring to a boil, cover and simmer for 15 minutes.
Drain chicken; pat dry and let cool.
In deep fryer or skillet, slowly heat oil to 375°.

title: shrimp and crabmeat medley
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients except bread crumbs and place in individual sea shells or in one large casserole.
Sprinkle with buttered bread crumbs and bake in oven at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: apple, carrot, raisin bread
directions: This recipe is for a 1 1/2 pound loaf.
Follow instructions given by your bread machine.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Crush 1 pint of strawberries.
Add sugar mixed with cornstarch.
Cook until thick in double boiler.
Cool.
Place 1 pint strawberries, washed and stemmed, into pie shell.
Pour cooked strawberry mixture over this and serve with whipped cream.

title: thanksgiving dinner
directions: Depending on how far you have to drive (pack clothes for an overnight trip) get up early on Thanksgiving Day and go to your mother's house.

title: chocolate sauce
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and 1/3 cup cold water.
Mix until smooth.
Add milk and bring to boil on medium heat.
Boil 3 to 4 minutes, stirring constantly and stir in oleo.
Serve hot or cold.

title: cheesy cornbread
directions: Combine all ingredients, except cheese, in a large bowl.
Stir it until combined; do not mix.
Pour over half mixture into a 9-inch greased cake pan.
Place cheese over batter; pour remaining batter over cheese.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: macaroni with broccoli
directions: Cook macaroni.
Drain and reserve 3 cups liquid.
Set aside. Cook broccoli and set aside.
In a large saucepan, brown garlic with oil and pepper.
Add drained macaroni and broccoli with the 3 cups reserved liquid.
Simmer about 10 minutes.
Top with grated cheese.

title: salmon-noodle baked dish
directions: Cook noodles.
Combine the salmon and eggs with the noodles. Cook the butter, flour, milk and salt for a white sauce.
Pour the white sauce over the noodle mixture.
Mix well.
Put the mixture into a well-greased baking dish.
Bake 1 hour in moderate oven.

title: oriental casserole
directions: Mix hamburger and onion in casserole.
Microwave on High 9 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients except noodles.
Cover and microwave about 3 minutes.
Sprinkle noodles on and microwave another 2 minutes.

title: cheeseburger casserole
directions: In a deep casserole dish begin layering with French fries, then burger, onions, soup (by the spoon), then cheese.
Repeat until all ingredients are used.
Cover with wax paper or loosely with plastic wrap.
Microwave for 8 to 10 minutes or until cheese is melted.
Serve warm.
Can be made ahead and refrigerated before microwaving.

title: cutler farm dressing
directions: Put in quart jar and shake well.

title: mom's corned beef
directions: Put meat in pot; pour cold water to cover.
Add all other ingredients except potatoes.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 3 1/2 to 5 hours.
Approximately 45 minutes before meat is done, add potatoes.

title: baby food cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and beat.
Bake in greased tube pan at 350° until done.
Will be golden brown.

title: roast beef and gravy
directions: Place meat in roaster; sprinkle onion soup over meat.
Pour soup and water over roast.
Bake covered at 300° for 3 hours or until tender.
Potatoes and carrots may be added after an hour.

title: potato sourdough bread dough
directions: Use recipe for Sourdough Bread Dough (see recipe).

title: corned beef sandwiches
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Spread in rolls.
Wrap in foil; heat 20 minutes at 350°.
Yields 10 sandwiches.

title: date and nut balls
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar, gradually.
Add salt and vanilla.
Sift flour with baking powder.
Add dry ingredients to creamed mixture. Add dates and nuts.
Pour into well greased 8 x 8-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix butter and peanut butter; blend in vanilla and confectioners sugar.
Roll out into balls.
Place on wax paper and put in freezer until firm.
Melt chips and wax in double boiler. Using toothpicks, dip balls in chocolate and place on paper.

title: dirt pie
directions: *Use granola chunks, chocolate chips, peanut butter chips, chopped peanuts, pecans or a combination.

title: skillet potato supper
directions: In large skillet, over medium heat, cook bacon until brown and set aside to drain.
Remove all but 2 tablespoons fat and cook onion until transparent.
Add hot dogs and lightly brown.
Stir in undiluted soup and drained potatoes.
Add crumbled bacon.
Reduce heat to low, cover and simmer until heated through (5 to 10 minutes).

title: green chili stewmidland, texas
directions: Cut up onion real fine and saute in oil.
Cut meat into small pieces and brown with onions until meat looks grayish.

title: banana pops
directions: You will also need popsicle sticks.

title: italian cheese cake
directions: Refrigerate; don't leave out.

title: sweet and sour pork chops
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Salt and pepper the chops.
Place them in 1 layer in a large baking dish.
Mix the remaining ingredients and pour over the chops.
Bake, uncovered, 1 1/2 hours.
Do not baste.
Skim the fat from the sauce.
Serve with mashed potatoes and a watercress salad.

title: barbecue rub
directions: Mix or shake ingredients until well blended.
Makes 1 cup.

title: corn relish(taste-in dish)
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a bowl, stirring well. In a small saucepan, combine sugar and remaining ingredients. Bring to a boil; cover, reduce heat and simmer 2 minutes. Pour vinegar mixture over vegetables; toss gently. Cover and chill at least 2 hours. Especially nice served in a lettuce-lined glass dish. Serves 20. Must do ahead.

title: easy barbecue pork chops
directions: Brown pork chops and place in baking dish.
Mix other ingredients and pour over chops.
Cover for part of the baking time.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour or more until done.

title: diabetic vegetables-peas and celery
directions: In covered medium saucepan, over medium heat, cook celery with 1/2 cup of water for 5 minutes or until tender.
Add peas.
Cover and cook for 8 to 10 minutes.
Drain.
Sprinkle peas with thyme and salt.
Makes 4 servings.

title: sour cream salad dressing
directions: Mix and let stand in refrigerator to ripen at least 12 hours.

title: crabmeat dip
directions: Mix together onion, cream cheese, horseradish and milk.
Layer three times the crabmeat, cream cheese, mixture and cheese slices, ending with crabmeat on top.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: pinto bean pie
directions: Combine eggs, beans and vanilla in blender.
Blend well in a large bowl.
Combine sugar, margarine, coconut and nuts.
Add to bean mixture.
Stir thoroughly.
Pour into pie shells.
Bake 1 hour at 300°.
Makes 3 pies.

title: basil cream pasta
directions: Blend 1/4 cup
oil and garlic in blender.
Slowly add basil and additional 1/4 cup oil until it becomes a fine green paste.
In saucepan, add cream, basil paste, 3/4 cup cheese, salt and pepper.
Heat just until hot.
Cook and drain pasta.
Toss with sauce and garnish with remaining Parmesan cheese.

title: flour tortillas
directions: Mix dry ingredients and add shortening.
Blend in with pastry blender; add warm water to make a soft dough.
Turn onto floured board and knead.
Divide into 10 balls.
Roll out each ball until flat.
Cook on a dry hot griddle or in a dry hot skillet until bubbles form.
Turn and brown on other side.
Stack on warm plate. Serve hot.
May be doubled or halved without any problems.

title: preb's appetizer
directions: Wrap 1/2 slice bacon around 1 chestnut.
Hold together with toothpick, dip into beaten egg, then dip into bread crumbs.
Place in broiling pan.
Broil until bacon is done (crispy).

title: reuben sandwich
directions: Butter one side of bread.
Add all ingredients and grill buttered side down until bread is toasted.
Recipe is really great when doubled.

title: meat pie
directions: Fry hamburger, onions and seasonings.
Drain fat.
Place in 10 x 12 x 2-inch ungreased pan.
Spread the 2 cans of creamed corn on top of meat.
Spread the mashed potatoes over the top of the corn. Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Cut in squares and serve.

title: fresh coconut cake
directions: Mix cake mix as directed on package.
Bake as directed.
When done, remove from oven and stick with a fork.
Open evaporated milk and pour over cake.
Let cool.
Chill.
Spread 1 large box Cool Whip and 1 package frozen coconut on top.

title: nearly mushrooms
directions: Mix all together.
Drop by teaspoons into hot butter, oleo, or shortening.
Brown on both sides until crisp.

title: hanky panky
directions: Brown the ground beef and sausage.
Drain.
Add the garlic salt, oregano and Worcestershire sauce.
Mix all well in electric skillet. Add the cheese (chopped) and stir until cheese has melted in mixture.
Turn heat off. Spread on party rye bread.
If frozen, bake 10 minutes at 325°.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs.
Beat well.
Sift dry ingredients.
Add alternately to sugar mixture with buttermilk. Add coloring and vanilla.
Add soda/vinegar mixture and stir only to blend.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: risotto with asparagus(microwave)
directions: Cut asparagus into 1 1/2-inch pieces and boil or steam until tender.
Set aside.
In microwavable 3-quart casserole, combine onion, mushrooms, butter and oil.
Cover with lid or plastic wrap. Microwave on High 5 minutes.
Stir rice, broth, wine and turmeric into mixture.
Cover and microwave on High 15 minutes.
Stir rice mix.
Microwave uncovered 10 minutes longer.
Combine asparagus with rice.
Cover.
Return to microwave 5 more minutes.
Remove from microwave.
Add cheese.
Add salt and pepper.
Serves 6.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Beat all ingredients with mixer.
Stir in 2 more cups of flour.
Let rise for 1/2 hour.
Roll out like pie dough.
Spread melted oleo all over dough, then sprinkle cinnamon-sugar mixture over.
Roll up and cut into 1 to 1 1/2-inch pieces.
Place on cookie sheet and let them rise for 1/2 hour.
Bake at 400° until light golden brown.

title: stuffed bell pepper
directions: Cut off top of peppers and remove seeds.
Place in boiling water for 5 minutes.
Cook ground beef and onion in shortening and drain.
Add tomatoes, rice, salt and pepper; cover and simmer about 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Then fill peppers with mixture.
Put peppers into baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Put grated cheese on top.

title: pecan tarts
directions: Cream the cream cheese and butter.
Work in flour to make dough.
Divide into 24 pieces and press into miniature muffin tins.

title: pineapple shrimp rice bake
directions: In a large saucepan, bring broth to a boil.
Stir in rice. Reduce heat; Cover and simmer for 25 minutes or until tender. Meanwhile, in a large skillet, saute the garlic, onion and green pepper in oil until tender.
Stir in soy sauce and ginger.
Add shrimp, ham and pineapple.
Stir in rice.
Transfer to a greased 2 qt. baking dish.
Bake uncovered, at 350 degrees for 15 - 20 minutes or until heated through.
Stir before serving.
Yields:
8 servings.

title: b. j.'s broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli al dente and drain.
Mix eggs, mayo, cheese and onion soup and pour over cooked broccoli.
Cover with crushed crackers.
Place cubed butter on top.
Bake in a 350° oven for about 30 to 45 minutes until nice and brown.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Put chicken in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix soups and milk together; pour over top of chicken.
Mix herb seasoning and water together; spread over top of soup mixture and chicken.
Bake at 350° until bubbly hot.

title: sweet potato-cranberry casserole
directions: Cook potatoes in boiling water to cover, 20 minutes or until tender.
Let cool to the touch; peel and mash.
Stir in cranberry sauce and cinnamon.
Spoon into a lightly greased 2-quart casserole.
Combine flour, sugar and oats; cut in butter until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Spoon over sweet potato mixture. Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Top with marshmallows and bake until golden brown.
Makes 8 servings.

title: hot wings
directions: Rinse chicken pieces well in cool water.
Pat dry.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Place in single layer on foil lined cookie sheet. Coat pieces with Wings and Things hot sauce (remember the more sauce you use the hotter the wings).
Spoon barbecue sauce on pieces (mild sauce for milder wings, spicier sauce will warm them up more).
Turn wings after 1/2 hour.
Repeat sauce on second side. Cook for additional 1/2 hour.

title: wild rice salad with ham and avocados
directions: Toss avocado with lemon juice and tomato. Toss the rice with ham, avocado and tomato. Blend garlic salt, salt, dressing and mayonnaise. Gently fold this mixture into the rice mixture. Chill several hours to blend flavors. Serve on lettuce leaves.
Serves 4 to 6 main dish salads.

title: boston cream fudge
directions: Boil until soft ball stage.
Add nuts; pour into greased platter.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix together ingredients until blended.
Roll out spoonfuls into balls.
Place on cookie sheet and mash with a fork.
Bake in a 350° oven until light brown.

title: oven beef stew
directions: Combine all ingredients, except potatoes in 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Cover and bake at 350° for 3 1/2 hours (or until meat is tender).
Stir several times during cooking.
Mix potatoes in during last hour of cooking.

title: clyde's waffles
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Beat the egg yolks and whites separately.
Combine egg yolks, milk and butter.
Mix with dry ingredients, stirring only until the batter is smooth.
Fold in beaten egg whites.
Bake in a hot waffle iron until steaming has almost stopped.
Serve with syrup and bacon or sausage!

title: spanish kraut
directions: Cut 1 cabbage in medium size wedges; cook in water.
Drain and pour dressing over.

title: sauce for meat loaf
directions: Blend all ingredients well.
Pour over meat loaf.
Baste at 15 minute intervals.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour an oblong pan (13 x 9 x 2-inch) or two 9-inch or three 8-inch round layer pans.
Beat all ingredients in a large mixer bowl constantly for 30 seconds.
Beat on high speed, scraping bowl occasionally for 3 minutes.
Pour into pan(s).
Bake until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean, 45 to 50 minutes for oblong pan and 35 to 40 minutes for layers.
Cool.
Frost with Vanilla Butter Frosting, if desired.

title: caramel nut brownies
directions: Melt caramels with 1/3 cup of evaporated milk in a double boiler.
Mix cake mix and melted margarine until crumbly.
Put 1/2 of mixture into the bottom of a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pat out to make crust.
Bake at 325° for 6 minutes.
Cool slightly.

title: corn griddlecakes
directions: Into medium bowl, sift flour with sugar, baking powder and salt.
In small bowl, lightly beat egg.
Add milk and salad oil; beat until well blended.
Add to flour mixture all at once.
Beat just until smooth.
Stir in corn.
Slowly heat griddle or skillet. To test temperature, drop a little cold water onto hot griddle; water should roll off in drops.
For each griddlecake, spoon about 1/4 cup batter onto hot griddle, spreading to make a 5-inch circle.
Cook until bubbles form on surface.
Turn and cook until nicely browned on underside.
Serve hot with butter and hot maple syrup.
Makes nine 5-inch griddlecakes.

title: strawberry preserves
directions: Mix all ingredients; stir constantly while cooking, about 20 minutes over low heat.
Pour into jars and seal.

title: rice casserole
directions: Melt oleo.
Add onion and bell pepper.
Simmer until clear. Add rice, beef bouillon, mushroom pieces and pimento.
Put in baking dish and bake 1 hour at 400°.

title: chicken parisienne
directions: All ingredients go on top of chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Bake flat on pan with shiny side up.

title: chicken broccoli
directions: Lay cooked broccoli in a buttered Pyrex baking dish (9 x 13-inch).
Lay cooked chicken on top of broccoli.
Mix soup, mayonnaise, curry powder and lemon juice together and spread over chicken.
Put Cheddar cheese over soup mixture.
Mix bread crumbs with melted butter and sprinkle over cheese. Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: cinnamon twists
directions: Dissolve yeast and the tablespoon of sugar in warm water. Scald milk; add shortening, sugar and salt.
Cool to lukewarm.
Add 2 cups flour or enough to make soft dough.
Knead lightly and place in a greased bowl.
Cover and set in a warm place.
Let rise until double.
Punch dough down.
Roll out and cut in strips.
Mix cinnamon and sugar.
Tie in a knot.
Place in a buttered pan and let rise again.
Bake in 400° oven.

title: working girls' cobbler
directions: Pour melted margarine in pan.
Mix sugar and flour with milk. Pour into pan.
Pour in
hot
fruit
and
bake 30 to 40 minutes at 325°.

title: heavenly hash
directions: Mix cream cheese and salad dressing.
Beat whipping cream, then mix all ingredients together and chill.

title: baked corned beef
directions: Wash corned beef under running water to remove brine.
In large kettle, cover with cold water; bring to boiling.
Drain; cover with fresh water.
Bring to boiling; simmer until tender (about 3 hours).
Remove from kettle; place in baking dish. Insert cloves in meat, sprinkle with brown sugar and slowly pour sherry over meat.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) until brown. Baste occasionally with sherry syrup in bottom of pan until thickly glazed.
Serve hot or cold.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Cook sugar, butter and cream for 7 minutes.
Remove from heat and add vanilla.
Beat in Marshmallow Creme well, then beat in peanut butter and pour into greased dish.
Cool before cutting.

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Beat egg whites with salt until foamy.
Add sugar, 2 tablespoons at a time, beating thoroughly after each addition. Continue beating until mixture is very stiff.
Add and blend in vanilla and chocolate chips.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Mix in soup and green beans; heat. Pour into casserole dish and cover the first four ingredients with the prepared mashed potatoes.
Put under broiler until mashed potato peaks are brown.
Makes 4 to 6 large servings.

title: squash dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake 30 minutes in casserole dish at 350°.

title: chicken cordon bleu
directions: Flatten chicken breasts with rolling pin; add layer of ham, then cheese.
Roll up and secure with a toothpick.
Cover with soup.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake in a casserole at 350° for about 45 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Blend together all ingredients except corn.
Pop corn.
Cook candy and pour over corn, mix well.
Keep tossing until dry.

title: frozen fruit cubes
directions: Combine banana, pineapple and almonds.
Fold in mayonnaise. Whip cream; fold into fruit mixture.
Turn into 3-cup refrigerator tray.
Freeze 4 to 5 hours.
Remove salad from freezer.
Let stand at room temperature for 10 minutes.
Cut salad into cubes.
If desired, serve on lettuce and top with additional almonds.
Makes 6 servings.

title: mandarin orange salad
directions: Mix crackers and margarine.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan, saving some for the top.
On low mixer speed, blend Eagle Brand and undiluted orange juice.
Fold in Cool Whip and oranges. Spread in pan and top with remaining cracker crumbs.
Refrigerate.

title: creamy chicken primavera
directions: In a large skillet, brown chicken in butter.
Add vegetables and pasta and water.
Cover and simmer 7 to 9 minutes, until vegetables are crisp-tender, stirring occasionally.
Stir in sour cream.
Heat thoroughly.
Makes 4 servings.
Preparation time:
20 minutes.

title: manhattan chicken
directions: Precook chicken until tender.
Melt margarine in electric skillet.
Cook celery, onions and mushrooms until tender.
Stir in the soups and sherry; add the chicken.
Simmer for 30 to 45 minutes.
Serve on rice.

title: fried cornbread
directions: Mix the amount of ingredients as desired. Cook in skillet on top of stove and don't forget the grease.

title: orange sunshine salad
directions: Peel and section oranges.
Dice orange sections to make 1 cup. Reserve remaining orange sections for garnish.
Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Cool slightly.
Add carbonated beverage, grated orange rind and lemon rind.
Chill to consistency of unbeaten egg whites.
Chill Carnation in refrigerator tray until soft icy crystals form around edges of tray, 10 to 15 minutes.
Whip until stiff for about 1 minute.
Add lemon juice.
Whip very stiff for about 2 minutes longer.
Stir cottage cheese and diced orange sections into gelatin mixture.
Fold in whipped Carnation.
Pour into 6-cup mold.
Chill until firm, about 2 hours.
Unmold and garnish with reserved orange sections.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Unroll crescent roll dough into 13 x 9-inch or slightly larger pan, making into one large crust.
Bake according to directions on can.
Let cool.
Mix together sour cream, cream cheese and dressing mix.
Spread over crust.
Top with chopped vegetables and cheese.
Chill.

title: pepper steak
directions: Cut the steak into 1/2 x 3-inch strips.
Brown the meat in the hot oil, then add the green pepper, onion, soy sauce and garlic powder.
Cover and cook over low heat for 10 minutes.

title: salmon cake
directions: Flake salmon and combine with all remaining ingredients, but fat.
Shape into 6 patties and saute in fat until golden brown on both sides.

title: heath brickle coffee cake
directions: Blend the flour, butter and sugars.
Take out 1/2 the mixture. To the rest, add buttermilk, soda, egg, vanilla and Heath Brickle.
Blend well.
Bake in greased and floured 10 x 14 x 2-inch pan.

title: creamy cucumbers
directions: Mix together and blend well, then add 1/3 cup vinegar.
Pour over fresh peeled cucumbers.
Best after setting awhile.

title: barbecue for a crowd
directions: Mix ground beef, onions, catsup, mustard, soups and celery. Place in a large kettle.
Simmer for at least 2 hours.
Serve on buns.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: In large saucepan, cook zucchini in boiling salted water until tender, about 5 minutes.
Drain.
In medium skillet, cook bacon until crisp.
Remove form pan.
Add onion and garlic to skillet and saute until onion is tender.
Drain.
Preheat oven to 350°. Stir onion-bacon mixture into drained zucchini.
Add remaining ingredients except Parmesan cheese and toss until well coated. Spoon zucchini into a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake for 20 minutes or until bubbly.

title: macaroni and cheese deluxe
directions: Beat egg white and save.
Beat egg yolk.
Pour scalded milk over egg yolk.
Add bread crumbs, onion, salt and cooked macaroni. Put butter in baking dish.
Pour mixture in.
Stir in beaten egg white.
Set baking dish in pan of hot water in 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: easy pot roast
directions: Place thawed roast in slow cooker.
Sprinkle with dry onion soup mix.
Cover with mushroom soup. Cook 6 to 8 hours or until tender.

title: poppy seed batter bread
directions: 1. Measure water into a large warm bowl.
Sprinkle in yeast and stir until dissolved.
Add butter, 2 Tbsp. seeds, sugar, and salt. 2. Stir in 2 c. of the flour beating until well blended.
Stir in enough additional flour to make a soft dough. 3. Cover and let rise in a warm draft free place until double in bulk.
Stir dough down. Spread evenly in a greased 9 X 5-inch loaf pan. 4. Cover and let rise until double in bulk. 5. Combine egg white and water and carefully brush top of loaf.
Sprinkle with seeds. 6. Bake at 375° for about 45 minutes.

title: crab spread
directions: Mix all ingredients with mixer until well blended.
Chill overnight in a small covered bowl.
Just before serving, turn onto a serving plate and shape into a ball.
Cover with red cocktail sauce and serve with crackers.

title: chocolate zucchini cake
directions: Peel and grate zucchini.
Set aside to drain all water.
Cream together the butter, sugar, oil, eggs, sour cream and vanilla. Stir in remaining ingredients, except zucchini and chocolate chips. Fold in zucchini.
Pour into greased pan, 13 x 9 x 2-inch. Sprinkle mini chocolate chips over cake.
Bake at 325° for approximately 45 minutes.
Do not preheat oven!!

title: peaches and cream pie
directions: Combine flour, baking powder, salt, butter, egg, milk and vanilla pudding and beat for 2 minutes at medium speed.
Pour in pan.
Over batter, place peaches.
Beat 2 minutes on medium the cream cheese, 1/2 cup sugar and reserved peach juice.
Spoon to 1-inch of end of batter.
Mix 1 tablespoon sugar and cinnamon together and sprinkle over cream cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Refrigerate.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Boil chicken for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Debone and keep 1/2 pot of the broth.
Add soups, Ro-Tel tomatoes, onion and evaporated milk. Stir until well mixed.
Simmer about 20 to 30 minutes.
Put smashed Doritos in a bowl.
Pour chicken over chips; add cheese as desired.

title: salmon chowder
directions: Drain salmon, reserving liquid.
Break salmon into large pieces.
Dissolve bouillon cube in boiling water.
Cook onion, green pepper and garlic in butter until tender.
Combine all ingredients and cook for 15 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Remove bay leaf.
Serves 6.

title: banana sandwich
directions: Spread mayonnaise on bread.
Slice bananas on one slice of bread.
Put the other slice of bread on top of this.
It's good!

title: cheese soup
directions: Mix together all ingredients except chicken soup and cheese. Cook for 30 minutes.
Add chicken soup and chopped cheese.
Cook until cheese is melted and soup is hot enough to eat.

title: fannie's easy chicken soup
directions: Boil
chicken until tender.
Remove
all skin and bones and skim
all fat.
Add all the ingredients, except the rice. Simmer for 1 1/2 hours.
Last 15 minutes add rice.
Serve with hot French
bread.
Great
if you have a cold, even better if you don't!

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Brown sausage.
Drain fat and set aside.
Saute vegetables in oleo; set aside.
Prepare Minute rice according to package directions.
Add Italian seasoning and garlic powder to rice. Mix eggs together with Parmesan, salt and pepper. Combine sausage, zucchini, rice and egg mixture with tomato.
Crush nacho chips and place in bottom of two 9-inch pie dishes.
Divide mixture between dishes over chips.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup grated Mozzarella cheese over each dish.
Bake for 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: seasoned ritz crackers
directions: Stir until well coated.
Put on cookie sheet.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 250°.

title: stuffed baked apples
directions: Peel and core apples and set aside.
Combine in saucepan the sugar, water and cinnamon red hots.
Add 1 capful red food coloring.
Bring to a boil.
Add apples and cook on top of range until tender, turning carefully.
Remove apples to cool, then add stuffing and serve.

title: peppered tenderloin
directions: Mix dry spices.
On a large sheet of foil, roll meat in it until evenly covered.
Rub Kitchen Bouquet on meat.
Wrap tightly in foil.
Place in baking dish and bake at 350° for 2 to 3 hours until tender.

title: gingerbread cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add egg and dry ingredients. Chill dough.
Roll out on floured board to desired thickness; cut with "gingerbread" cookie cutters and bake on greased cookie sheet at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: cream cheese coffee cake
directions: Combine.
Sprinkle over first mixture.
Fold sides in toward center.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes, until brown.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: crunchy punch
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients into a syrup and then add the last 3 ingredients.
Freeze all.
When ready to use, add 2 bottles of ginger ale.

title: barbecue sauce for ribs
directions: Bring to a boil.
Brown ribs in a little oil.
Put in foil. Pour over sauce.
Bake at least 1 1/2 hours at 340°.

title: candied carrots
directions: Peel carrots and slice thin.
Place in pan with a little water.
Bring to a boil.
Add a couple tablespoons of brown sugar. Simmer until soft.
Add more water if necessary.

title: pumpkin cake a la marlys
directions: Add sugar, oil and pumpkin filling.
Beat well.
Add eggs, one at a time, and beat well.
Mix all dry ingredients, then add and beat well. Add nuts and raisins.
Mix well.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Do not open oven door under 1 hour. Sprinkle powdered sugar on top for a finishing touch.
You can use Bundt pan, tube pan or two loaf pans.

title: slam dunk crab dip
directions: In a mixing bowl, beat cream cheese and milk until smooth. Stir in the crab, onions, red pepper, curry powder and garlic salt. Refrigerate until serving. Serve with crackers.

title: corn salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.

title: taco salad dip
directions: Mix all 3 cheeses together.
Spread on the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish.
Drain salsa and pour over cheese.
Chop up lettuce, tomato and scallions.
Mix vegetables together and sprinkle on top of salsa.
Serve with nacho chips.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Prepare potatoes. Set aside. Chop onion and saute in skillet until just brown. Add hamburger meat. Brown and crumble. Add salt, pepper and garlic or garlic powder. Add vegetable soup or frozen vegetables (with beef bouillon cube). Add water to make a light sauce or add tomato sauce. Put in casserole. Cover top with mashed potatoes. Brush top with melted margarine. Bake at 350° about 30 to 45 minutes until potatoes are nice brown.

title: taffy dip
directions: Soften cream cheese and mix with brown sugar.
Add vanilla. Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: fast and easy lemon pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into ready made graham cracker crust pie shell.
Chill for 1 hour.

title: italian beef with peppers
directions: Place meat in a deep roaster and cover with all of the ingredients.
Cover tightly and bake at 200° for 10 hours (or overnight).
When cooked, shred meat with fork and let fall into liquid.
Serve on crusty rolls or bread.
Serves 15, cut in 1/2 for family.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix hamburger, seasoning and crackers thoroughly in large bowl.
Drain cans of corn, carrots and mixed vegetables.
Add the mixed vegetables and corn to hamburger mixture.
Add as much catsup as you like to the mixture.
Place mixture in a well-greased 13 x 5-inch casserole dish.
Before putting meat loaf in oven, put carrots all along top of meat loaf in rows, then add catsup to spread on top.
Cook at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes. Serves 2 to 6 people.

title: chicken nuggets
directions: Toss chicken and oil.
Mix remaining ingredients in plastic bag.
Shake about 6 pieces of chicken at a time in bag until coated.
Arrange chicken pieces in single layer microwave plate. Cover with wax paper and microwave on High 7 to 8 minutes rotating pie plate after 3 minutes, until done.

title: sweet potato dumplings
directions: Combine the sweet potatoes and water in a Dutch oven or large deep skillet. Cook until potatoes are fork tender but not mushy. Remove the potatoes using a slotted spoon. Measure the cooking liquid and add water, if needed, to make about 5 cups of liquid. Pour back into pan. Add sugar and spices and stir to mix. Make dumplings. I like to use my food processor to make the dough. Combine flour, shortening and the 1/3 cup of milk. Process until a dough is formed. Turn out onto floured surface and work more flour into the dough, if needed, to make a firm dough. Roll to a thickness of about 1/4 inch or less. Cut into strips. Bring the liquid to a rolling boil. Drop pieces of dumpling strips into pot. Cover and reduce heat to low. Cook about 6 minutes. Remove cover and add the 1/4 cup of milk and butter. Stir until butter melts. Add the sweet potatoes back to the pan and continue cooking for another 4 to 5 minutes or until slightly thickened.

title: jelled cranberry delight salad
directions: Drain pineapple and save 1 cup juice or use water to finish out to 1 cup.
Mix juices and water and bring to boil.
Stir in jello to dissolve. Break up cranberry sauce with fork and add to jello mixture.
Refrigerate until jello begins to set.
Stir in pineapple, celery and pecans.
Pour into mold or dish.
Chill.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Pour into an unbaked pie shell. Top with pie dough; trim around edges.
Bake in a 375° oven for 30 minutes or until crust browns.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Butter 3-quart casserole dish and put broccoli on bottom of dish.
Put chopped chicken on top.
Blend soup and sour cream and spread over the entire dish.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix milk and bread good in a large container. Add eggs and mix good. Add meat and beat until mixed. Add salt, onion, bell pepper and black pepper.
Pour into a baking dish and make like a loaf. Bake 1 hour at 350°. Put ketchup on when done.

title: o'brien's stew
directions: Combine soups, wine and meat in casserole dish.
Bake at 325° for 3 hours.
During the last hour, may add chopped onion, pepper, etc., per personal preference.
Serve over egg noodles or white rice.

title: guacamole
directions: Peel and mash avocados.
Add minced onion, lemon juice, mayonnaise and salt.
Serve on tomato slices.
Garnish with chips.

title: cheese cake
directions: Mix above; press on bottom and halfway up sides of 9-inch spring-form pan.
Prepare filling.

title: coconut balls
directions: Mash potatoes, let cool.
Then mix potatoes, sugar, coconut, and vanilla
together.
Mix until moist.
Form small balls and place on cookie sheet, place in refrigerator.
Melt chocolate and a little paraffin over medium heat in double boiler.
Dip balls when ready and place on wax paper on cookie sheet.
When chocolate has hardened candy is ready.
Store in cool place in tight container.

title: chipped ham barbecue
directions: Add first 3 ingredients into melted oleo.
Simmer 20 minutes, then add everything else (except chipped ham) and cook 30 minutes on low, stirring occasionally.
Add chipped ham, simmer for 10 more minutes.

title: one-pot italian spaghetti
directions: Brown hamburger with onion.
Add remaining ingredients, including uncooked spaghetti (but not grated cheese). Heat to boiling, stirring occasionally.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer over low heat about 15 minutes or until the spaghetti is tender.
Remove from heat and stir once. Sprinkle with grated cheese just before serving.

title: apple pudding
directions: Work butter, brown sugar, cinnamon and flour together until crumbly.
Place apples in buttered casserole dish.
Spread topping over apples.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until apples are tender.

title: ham and broccoli bake
directions: Cook broccoli as per package directions.
Drain very well. Cook onion in butter.
In very large bowl, stir together both soups, milk, cheese and drained pimentos.
Add drained, cooked broccoli, cooked onions, ham and uncooked rice and Worcestershire sauce.
Mix well. Divide into two casseroles.
Serves 20.

title: hot artichoke dip
directions: Chop chilies, peppers and artichokes coarsely.
Combine with mayo, Mozzarella and Parmesan.
Bake at 350° until bubbly (1/2 hour).
Serve with corn chips or taco chips.

title: reuben (dip) spread
directions: Mix all 4 ingredients in an oven-safe dish.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: easy dill pickles
directions: Pack quart jars with cucumbers and dill (can add a bud of garlic).
Make a brine with the water and salt.
Boil in large pan, then add vinegar.
Bring to a boil again.
Pour hot brine over pickles to fill jar.
Seal with double lid and let set for 6 to 8 weeks.

title: beulah's candy
directions: Cook sugar and milk 10 minutes or to soft ball stage.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter and marshmallow cream.
Beat until thick and creamy.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch buttered pan.

title: chili bake
directions: Prepare corn muffin mix as directed.
Set aside.
In a 12-inch skillet over medium heat, cook ground beef until well browned, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; spoon off fat.
Add chili powder, salt, garlic powder, tomato sauce and tomatoes and their liquid.
Pour mixture into a 13 x 9-inch baking dish; spread corn muffin mix evenly over mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes, until top is golden.
Serves 6.

title: fried rice
directions: Cook rice in 2 cups water until dry or cook ahead.
In skillet, heat oil; saute onions and add meat.
Cook about 2 minutes.
Break eggs into onion mixture; let this cook a little, then scramble.
Add salt and pepper, rice and soy sauce.
Heat through.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Drain shrimp and chop, not too fine.
Soften the onion flakes. Put bouillon cube in 1/3 cup hot water and stir until dissolved. Combine with cheese and blend until smooth.
Add remaining ingredients and shrimp.
Makes about 2 cups.

title: company chicken
directions: *I use half and half.

title: lloyd's fruit bars
directions: Cream sugar, shortening and eggs.
Add soda, salt and molasses, then add raisins and nuts.
Stir in flour.
Press out onto cookie sheets.
With hands, make a big flat sheet just up to edge of cookie sheet.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Bake at 350° for approximately 8 to 10 minutes.
Cut into bars.
If hard, they should soften in a couple days.
Shouldn't be soft when taken from oven.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Mix well.
Pour into unbaked pie crust.
Bake slowly at 350° for 1 hour, until crust is done.

title: apple pancakes
directions: In a blender container, put the milk, whipping cream, flour, baking powder, sugar, vanilla and egg yolks.
Beat the egg whites until stiff.
Fold them gently into the batter.
Melt a little butter in a 9-inch frying pan.
Pour in a thin layer of batter. As the pancake begins to bubble, arrange some of the apple slices on top, pushing them into the pancake.
When the bottom is browned, turn the pancake over.
Finish cooking.

title: chocolate balls
directions: Mix crumbs and peanut butter; add to the melted oleo and sugar. Shape into balls. Melt paraffin and chocolate. Dip balls into paraffin-chocolate mixture. Lay on wax paper to dry.

title: raisin pie
directions: Cream butter, sugar and egg yolks.
Stir in raisins.
Pour into 9-inch pie shell.
Bake at 350°.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: italian fried pastry
directions: Knead slightly until smooth.
Roll out and cut thin in 1-inch strips with cookie cutter, then cut in shorter strips or desired length.
Make bow ties.

title: dump soup
directions: Dump entire contents of all cans, ranch dressing mix and taco seasoning into a large pot and start to heat.
Brown ground beef, seasoning to taste with salt and pepper.
When ground beef is brown, add to the pot.
Serve over a bed of tortilla chips in bottom of bowl, with a spoonful of prepared Ranch Dip on top.

title: breakfast egg casserole
directions: Brown
sausage
links.
Arrange browned links in bottom of a large
baking
dish.
Spread
1 cup shredded cheese over links. Arrange Tater Tots over cheese.
Beat eggs with 2 cups milk
and mustard, then
pour
over
Tater
Tots.
Refrigerate overnight. The next day, combine 1/2 cup milk and soup.
Pour over egg mixture and spread with remaining 1 cup cheese.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: apple pie
