directions: Combine sugar, flour, cinnamon, nutmeg and salt.
Add to apples and mix lightly.
Heap into pastry lined 9-inch pie pan. Dot with butter.
Adjust top of crust over filling.
Flute edges and cut steam vents.
Bake in hot oven (425°) for 50 to 60 minutes or until apples are tender and crust is browned.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix ingredients in order and bake at 300° in an 8 x 4-inch bread tin for 1 hour.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix all together.
Spread on top of baked mixture and bake about 20 more minutes.

title: upside-down pizza
directions: Brown meat and onion in large frying pan.
Add sauce, garlic powder and oregano.
Mix and simmer for 5 minutes.
Pour into large baking dish.
Sprinkle 8 ounces cheese over top.
Set aside.
In small bowl mix eggs, milk, 1 tablespoon oil, salt and flour (it will be a thin batter).
Pour over meat and cheese evenly. Sprinkle 1/2 cup Parmesan cheese over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: bennett's fried fish
directions: Mix flour, cornmeal and seasonings in bowl.
Cut fish into serving size portions.
Roll fish in seasoned flour mix.
Deep fry at 375°.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together and shape into one large or two small balls.
Roll in paprika or chopped nuts.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Combine all dry ingredients.
Add to boiling water and cook until thick.
Cool.
Place chilled strawberries in baked pie shell and pour mixture over them.
Place in refrigerator.
Top with whipped cream, if desired.

title: busy day casserole
directions: Brown beef in a skillet.
Pour off the excess fat.
Add chopped onion to beef and simmer until tender.
Add soups and mix well.
Pour into casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.
Serve with cole slaw and rolls.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Mix; beat 2 minutes.
Bake in 2 loaf pans for 1 hour at 350°.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix cake mix as directed.
Pour 1/2 batter in greased 9 x 13-inch
pan.
Bake at
350° for 15 minutes.
Melt caramels, Eagle Brand
milk
and
oleo
in	double boiler, or microwave. Pour this mixture over cooled cake.	Sprinkle chocolate chips and nuts over
caramel
mixture.
Pour remaining half of cake batter over caramel and nut mixture.
Bake 25 minutes longer. Cool.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar.

title: potato soup
directions: Saute onion in butter in large pot.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer about 20 minutes, until potatoes are tender.
Cool completely.
Add 1 large container sour cream.
Reheat, but do not boil.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Cut meat in 3/4-inch cubes or strips and dredge in flour seasoned with salt and pepper.
Brown meat in hot shortening.
Add onions, mushrooms and garlic.
Mix sour cream with tomato soup, sauces and green pepper.
Pour over meat.
Cover, cook on high until steaming, reduce heat to simmer.
Takes about 45 minutes to cook.
Serve over spaghetti, noodles or other pasta or rice. Parmesan cheese sprinkled over top is optional.

title: spinach ricotta dumplings
directions: Mix ingredients with 2 beaten eggs.
This mixture is very sticky.
Shape into balls (as you would meatballs).
Roll lightly in flour; put on cookie sheet lined with wax paper and chill well. In large kettle, bring water to a boil.
Gently drop in dumplings, one at a time.
They sink to the bottom.
Reduce heat to simmer after dumplings rise to top, simmer about 10 minutes. Remove gently with slotted spoon to serving dish.
Cover with Quick Tomato Sauce and serve.

title: napa salad
directions: Mix cabbage and green onions and refrigerate overnight or at least 2 hours.
Break noodles into small pieces and saute them with the almonds and the sunflower seeds in the butter until lightly browned, then refrigerate.
Combine cabbage mixture and noodle mixture about 2 hours before serving.
Mix soy sauce, sugar, oil and vinegar and pour over salad about 15 minutes before serving.
This makes a very large salad.

title: taco dip
directions: Brown meat, onion, cumin and salt.
Mix beans with seasoning mix and Monterey cheese.
Layer in a square baking dish.
First layer, refried bean mixture.
Second layer, meat mixture.
Then layer chili peppers, Cheddar cheese and taco sauce.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Serve with chips.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix; bake at 350° for 15 minutes on sprayed cookie sheet.

title: pineapple delight
directions: Cut up marshmallows.
Add pineapple (not juice) and let stand overnight.
Whip cream; add sugar and vanilla.
Fold into pineapple mixture.
Chill thoroughly.

title: no peek chicken
directions: Lightly grease a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix the first 6 ingredients.
Place chicken on top.
Sprinkle chicken with onion soup.
Seal with foil.
Bake at 325° for 2 hours or until tender.

title: ham loaf
directions: In a large bowl, beat eggs.
Add milk, bread crumbs and pepper.
Cube ham and add along with ground pork.
Mix well and shape into a loaf.
Place in a shallow baking pan and insert a meat thermometer.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: orange pineapple congealed salad
directions: Bring pineapple to boil.
Remove from heat.
Add jello and dissolve.
Add buttermilk, coconut and nuts.
Cool.
Fold in whipped topping.
Pour into 13 x 9-inch dish and refrigerate.

title: german chocolate cake
directions: Grease oblong cake pan.
Spread 1 cup nuts mixed with 1 cup coconut in bottom of cake pan.
Put cake mix, pudding, water, eggs and oil in bowl; mix well.
Pour over nuts and coconut.
Blend together the margarine, cream cheese, powdered sugar and vanilla; spoon this over cake.
Bake at 325° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: 4-cheese mexican tortilla appetizer
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Place tortillas on baking sheets.
Bake for 3 to 4 minutes or until crisp.
Spread refried beans evenly on tortillas.
Spread 1 tablespoon taco sauce over beans.
Top with bell peppers, green onions and crushed red pepper.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake for 7 to 8 minutes or until cheese is melted.
Cut into wedges.
Serves 12.

title: golden potato bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook potatoes in boiling salted water until tender; drain.
Add carrots.
Mash at low speed with electric mixer.
Slowly beat in enough milk to make light and fluffy.
Stir in the butter and a little salt and pepper.
Put into a greased 2-quart casserole; dot with butter, if desired. Bake for 25 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: sopaipillas
directions: Stir together flour, baking powder and salt.
Cut in 1 tablespoon shortening with pastry blender.
Gradually add water, stirring with a fork.
Turn out on lightly floured board.
Knead into a smooth ball.
Divide in half; let stand 10 minutes.
Roll out each half to 10 x 12-inch rectangles. Cut into 2 x 3-inch rectangles.
Do not re-roll or patch dough.
Drop 1 at a time into hot oil.
Lightly brown.
Serve with honey or sugar.
Makes 20.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix together and refrigerate.
Can be used as salad or dessert.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Boil chicken; take off the bone.
Put chips in a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Mix Ro-Tel with chicken.
Pour over chips.
Top with cubed cheese.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.

title: lime jello salad
directions: Sprinkle dry jello over cottage cheese.
Fold in Cool Whip. Fold in drained pineapple and nuts.
Chill at least 2 hours before serving.

title: banana sherbet
directions: Whip all ingredients until smooth.
Pour into freezer trays. Freeze until mushy.
Whip again.
Freeze until firm.

title: spinach balls
directions: Mix. Chill and roll into balls. Freeze.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: pickled beets and eggs
directions: Put sugar , juice from beets, allspice, cinnamon sticks, salt and vinegar in pan and boil for 15 minutes hard.
Put sliced beets into mixture and boil slowly for 5 to 10 minutes.
Remove cinnamon sticks.

title: pasta gardena
directions: Cook pasta.
Drain well. Combine oil and vinegar in a jar. Shake vigorously.
In a large skillet, combine pasta, oil, vinegar and tomatoes. Cook over low heat, tossing gently.
Add spices. Heat through.
Sprinkle with Parmesan.

title: cranberry cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine peach pie filling and cranberry sauce in ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Combine dry cake mix, cinnamon and nutmeg in bowl.
Cut in butter with pastry blender or 2 knives; mix in nuts.
Sprinkle evenly over fruit in pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve with ice cream or whipped cream, if desired.
Makes 16 servings.

title: sour cream balls
directions: Place butter in small saucepan and bring to a boil.
Remove from heat and stir in sour cream and sugar.
Stir until melted and let cool to lukewarm.
Dissolve yeast in warm water (1/2 cup) in a large mixing bowl. Stir in sour
cream mixture and eggs. Combine flour and salt. Gradually add to yeast mixture, mixing well. Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: pineapple sunshine cake
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
Bake on 325° for 25 to 30 minutes in 2 round pans.
Cool.
Mix the next 3 ingredients, fold in Cool Whip and spread on cold cake.
Store cake in refrigerator.

title: apple cake
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix well with wooden spoon or hands. Pat into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 35 minutes. While still warm, sprinkle with cinnamon sugar.
Cake will be somewhat soft when done.

title: dressing or stuffing
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour turkey juice over it and stir.
Add water to make juicy enough so it won't get dry after cooking.
Bake at 350° for about 45 to 60 minutes.

title: cheesy rice and broccoli casserole
directions: In large bowl,
combine soups, milk and sour cream.
Stir in cheeses, rice, broccoli, onion, 3/4 teaspoon of paprika and pepper.
Coat 13 x 9-inch baking dish with nonstick cooking spray and transfer mixture.
Sprinkle with remaining paprika.
Cover and bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Uncover;
bake 5 to 10 minutes longer or until rice and broccoli are tender.
Serves 16 as a side dish.

title: tiny cream puffs
directions: Bring water and butter to a boil.
Add flour and salt; cook until mixture leaves sides of pan, stirring constantly.
Remove from flame.
Add unbeaten egg and beat thoroughly.
Drop from level teaspoons into 26 to 30 tiny balls on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 14 to 16 minutes.
Cool on cake rack.

title: crab newburg
directions: Place
margarine in a 1 1/2 quart casserole.
Microwave at High (100%) until melted, 30 seconds to 1 minute.
Stir in flour, salt,
paprika
and cayenne pepper.
Blend in half and half,
milk and sherry.
Microwave at Medium-high (70%) until thickened, 4 to	7 minutes, stirring with a wire whisk 2 to 3 times
during cooking.
Stir small amount of hot mixture into egg
yolks; return to mixture.
Microwave at Medium-high (70%) until thickened, 1 to 3 minutes, stirring once or twice.	Stir in
crabmeat.
Serve over
toast
points
or patty shells, if desired.

title: copper carrots
directions: Layer cooked carrots, green peppers and onions. Refrigerate. Combine tomato soup, sugar, salad oil, vinegar, mustard, Worcestershire, salt and pepper. Heat the mixture in a saucepan to boiling; pour hot mix over vegetables. Cover and store in refrigerator. Serve hot or cold.

title: date pie
directions: Bake pie crust first.
Mix ingredients in order given.
Boil on stove until thick enough to stick on spoon.
Pour in pie crust and bake until solid.
Top with whipped cream.

title: light jello cake
directions: Bake cake and let cool.
Prepare jello, dissolving in 1 cup boiling water.
Add 1/2 cup cold water.
Using a knife, poke holes all over cake and pour jello over cake and into holes.
Prepare vanilla pudding with cold milk and spread over cake.
Top with Cool Whip.
Refrigerate for at least 1 hour before serving.

title: chili and beans
directions: Saute beef and onion in a large, gallon-saucepot until meat is lightly browned.
Add all of the spices, beans, tomatoes and tomato juice; mix well.
Bring to a boil and simmer over low heat, covered, stirring occasionally for 1 hour.

title: barbecue cups
directions: Brown hamburg; drain grease.
Add remaining ingredients. Press biscuits in muffin pans.
Fill with filling.
Sprinkle with shredded cheese.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: christmas balls
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Gradually beat in sugar.
Fold in dates, nuts, coconut and extract; beat well.
Spread in an ungreased shallow pan (9 x 9 x 2-inch).
Bake for 20 minutes in a 300° oven.
Remove mixture from oven and turn out into bowl and add cherries.
Let mixture cool so it can be handled and form into little balls.
Roll each ball in granulated sugar.
Makes 30 balls.

title: bundt cake
directions: Allow eggs, butter and Crisco oil to set at room temperature overnight.
Add pinch of salt to flour.
Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Spray Baker's Joy in Bundt pan. Bake at 350°.

title: rice krispie bars
directions: Mix the cake mix, 1 egg and 1 stick oleo.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch pan; bake at 325° for 15 minutes.
Top with the marshmallows; return to oven to melt.
Remove from oven; slightly cool.
Mix together the corn syrup, 1 stick oleo, peanut butter chips and vanilla.
Fold in the Rice Krispies; melt all together in microwave.
Put on top of marshmallow layer; cool and cut in squares.

title: hershey's one bowl butter cream frosting
directions: Cream butter in small mixing bowl, then add cocoa and sugar alternately with milk; beat to consistency. Blend in vanilla.

title: bacon-tomato mini appetizers
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Separate each biscuit into 2 or 3 thinner biscuits each. Lay each biscuit over top of mini muffin cup. Press each biscuit into cup.
Sprinkle several bacon pieces to each cup. Chop the tomato and add to each cup.
Finely chop the onion
and mix with mayonnaise, cheese and basil.
Mound a small amount of cheese mixture on top of tomato in cups.
Sprinkle a few more bacon pieces on top. Bake 10 to 15 minutes until golden brown.
Makes 20 to 30 appetizers.

title: broccoli bread
directions: Mix
ingredients.
Spray
Baker's Joy into oblong Pyrex dish, and add batter.
Bake 20 minutes at 350° or until golden brown.

title: moms raw apple cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Grease and flour 9 x 13 baking dish.
Mix oil, sugar and eggs together and mix well and add chopped apples.
Let stand for 15 minutes and then add all dry ingredients mixing well.
Add chopped nuts.
Pour into prepared dish to bake for 45 minutes.

title: parmesan oven fried chicken
directions: Combine bread crumbs, cheese, parsley, pepper and garlic salt. Set aside.
Dip chicken in salad dressing.
Dredge in bread crumb mixture.
Place chicken in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan, coated with cooking spray.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 45 minutes or until tender.
Yields 6 servings.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream the cream cheese and sugar.
Add eggs.
Blend well.
Add bananas and stir.
Gently mix in biscuit baking mix.
Add nuts. Bake in a greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan in a preheated oven at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
A very good recipe.

title: ham and corn pudding
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Add flour, salt, pepper and sugar; blend.
Add milk gradually and cook over medium heat until mixture is thickened, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat, add onion, corn, ham and eggs; mix.
Turn into baking dish.
Place pan in pan of hot water and bake in moderate oven at 375° for 50 minutes or until mixture is set.

title: cheese balls
directions: Melt butter; cream in sugar and egg yolk.
Alternately add cheese and flour.
Roll on floured board and cut in desired shapes or roll in small balls and place on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: babci's kielbasi appetizer
directions: Cut kielbasi in bite size pieces.
Mix all ingredients in casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Baste periodically.

title: strawberry jello cake
directions: Mix ingredients in rotation.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.
Put a large pan of water under cake while baking.
It burns easily.

title: taco dip
directions: Spread can of refried beans on cookie sheet or pizza pan.
Mix taco seasoning with sour cream and spread on top of beans.
Spread salsa on top of sour cream mixture.
Sprinkle cheese all over top of salsa.
Sprinkle lettuce on top of cheese.
Sprinkle tomato on top of lettuce.
Sprinkle onion on top of tomato.

title: jam cake
directions: Combine ingredients, adding jam before sugar.
Bake at 350° until done.
Spray pans or cut oil paper for bottom.
Makes 2 layers.
I double recipe and make 3.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Grease casserole dish.
Pour pineapple chunks in.
Mix sugar, grated cheese and flour together and pour on top of pineapple. Melt butter and break the Ritz crackers into butter.
Put on top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: easy chinese chews
directions: Mix flour, sugar, dates and nuts in bowl. Add vanilla. Beat eggs, add eggs and butter together with ingredients. Pour into buttered oblong pan. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Cut into squares.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Layer sausage, potatoes, cheese, flour, salt and milk in casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes, covered. Uncover and bake for 10 to 15 minutes longer.

title: monkey bread
directions: Mix 3/4 cup sugar and 1 tablespoon cinnamon together.
Roll biscuits in the mixture.
Drop into greased Bundt pan.
Bring rest of ingredients together to a boil.
Pour over biscuits.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Remove from pan immediately.

title: sombrero dip
directions: Brown meat and 1/4 cup onions.
Add salt, chili powder and ketchup.
Add beans with juice.
Mix and heat.
Put mixture into chafing dish and top with remaining onions, cheese and sliced olives.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients, except strawberries and sugar.
Add the strawberries and sugar to other ingredients.
Put in refrigerator until it gets cold.
Very good with cake.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix
ingredients in order listed, adding all dry ingredients a
little
at a time.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each.
Grease one tube pan or 2 large loaf pans and pour
in batter.
Bake
at
for
one hour or until done (optional: add 1 cup chopped nuts to batter).	A cream cheese and
powdered sugar
icing,
tinted yellow, gives the look of autumn.

title: aunt wilma's ice cream
directions: Mix together the ingredients.
Complete filling of ice cream freezer can with whole milk.
Freeze as you would homemade ice cream with equal parts of ice cream salt and ice.

title: bacardi, one, two punch
directions: Mix all ingredients together in container and let chill for 2 hours.
Pour punch over block of ice in punch bowl.
Float mint, strawberries, orange, lemon and lime slices on top.
Serve in 6 ounce punch cups.
Makes 18 servings.

title: barbecued pumpernickel
directions: Cut bread in 1/2-inch thick slices, cutting to but not through bottom crust.
Combine butter, Parmesan cheese, seasoning sauce and parsley.
Spread mixture between every other slice of bread. Make 1 lengthwise slice down center of bread, cutting to but not through bottom crust.
Wrap loaf in foil.
Heat foil-wrapped bread over slow coals until warm through, 25 to 30 minutes.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: america samoa's peanut butter chicken
directions: Mix all ingredients and spread on chicken; broil or grill chicken until done.

title: scrambled egg casserole
directions: Saute ham and onion in 3 tablespoons butter in a large skillet until onion is tender.
Add eggs and cook over medium-high heat; stir to form large, soft curds.
When eggs are set, stir in Cheese Sauce (recipe follows).
Spoon eggs into greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Sprinkle with paprika and chill overnight.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until heated through.
Serves 8.

title: mexican fruitcake
directions: Combine all ingredients until thoroughly mixed.
Pour into a 13 x 9 x 2 pan.
Bake at 350° for 35-45 minutes.
Frost with cream cheese frosting.

title: creamy fruit and layered dessert
directions: Pour milk into medium bowl.
Add pudding mixes; beat with whisk for 1 minute.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Layer 1/2 of the cake cubes, fruit and pudding in 3-quart serving bowl.
Repeat layers once.
Refrigerate for 1 hour or until ready to serve.

title: baked bean casserole
directions: Saute onions and green peppers in 2 tablespoons of butter. Add beans, hot dogs, ketchup, chili sauce and brown sugar. Simmer 2 minutes.
Pour into casserole.
Split biscuits; place on beans.
Top with Cheddar cheese.
Put on other half of biscuits and sprinkle with corn chips and Parmesan.
Dot with butter. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until browned.

title: squash pineapple bread
directions: Beat eggs lightly in a large bowl.
Stir in applesauce, sugar, squash, pineapple and vanilla.
Sift together remaining dry ingredients.
Stir dry ingredients into egg mixture until well blended.
Spoon batter into an 8 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan coated with nonstick spray.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour or until centers of loaves spring back when touched.
Cool 10 minutes before removing loaves from pans.
Yields 20 servings per loaf.
One serving equals 130 calories.

title: orange frosty
directions: Place all ingredients in blender.
Mix until frosty and drink.

title: orange-butterscotch sauce
directions: Melt morsels over hot (not boiling) water.
Stir in evaporated milk and orange extract.
Blend mixture with a fork or wire whisk until smooth.
Serve warm over ice cream or cake.

title: spaghetti casserole
directions: Cook vermicelli according to package directions.
Brown meat. Cook spinach according to package directions.
In a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish, layer sauce with spaghetti, meat mixture, then Parmesan cheese, Ricotta cheese and spinach.
Top with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: roast and relaxation
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Shake flour in a large (4 x 20-inch) cooking bag to coat inside of bag.
Place in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Roll down top of bag.
Add tomato sauce, water, instant bouillon, salt and pepper.
Squeeze bag gently to blend. Trim fat from roast.
Place roast in bag.
Peel and quarter carrots and onions.
Add to bag with celery, red pepper and potatoes.
Turn bag gently to coat ingredients with sauce.
Close bag with tie. Make six 1/2-inch slits in top of bag.
Bake 1 3/4 to 2 1/4 hours or until tender.
To serve:
Spoon gravy from bag over roast and vegetables.

title: nana's chess pie
directions: Combine eggs, margarine, sugar and flour; mix well.
Stir in vanilla and milk.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes; reduce heat to 350° and bake 25 to 30 minutes longer or until set.

title: fresh christmas fruit cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar, then beat in the eggs.
Mix the dry ingredients, including the spices and stir this mixture in alternately with the milks into the butter mixture.
When well mixed, stir in the fruits, chopped nuts and jam.
Pour batter into 4 greased and floured cake pans.
Bake at 350° until done (about 30 minutes).

title: hot pot
directions: Grease baking pan.
Cut cabbage into baking pan.
Brown hamburger meat in skillet and add onion.
Pour off fat.
Add rice over cabbage.
Add hamburger meat, then add soup and water.
Salt to taste.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: mama's pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 350° until done.
Makes 1 deep dish pie.

title: sugar-free diet cake
directions: Cream the margarine. Add eggs and beat well.
Sift dry ingredients together. Add to creamed mixture. Stir in applesauce, banana, vanilla and sweetener.
Mix well. Add dates and pecans. Stir only until mixed.
Pour batter into an 8 x 8-inch baking pan that has been buttered or sprayed with Pam. Bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Cook noodles.
Brown hamburger, then add all other ingredients, except the cheeses and noodles.
Cook together for 5 minutes.
Mix well with noodles and layer this mixture with the cheeses.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes.

title: strawberry fig preserves
directions: Mix mashed figs and sugar; cook for 30 minutes.
Add 2 pkgs strawberry Jell-O and 2 pkg. of Sure Jell.
Cook 1 minute longer and put in jars; seal.
Yield:
6 pints.

title: dressing for spinach
directions: Combine and shake well.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Alternate layers of cooked macaroni, cheese, margarine, salt and pepper.
Beat eggs and milk.
Pour over ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: turkey-vegetable soup
directions: In 5-quart Dutch oven, cook onions over medium heat in oil until lightly browned and tender (about 10 minutes).
Add turkey, salt, sage, monosodium glutamate, pepper and 8 cups of water. Over high heat, bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer 45 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add vegetables; turn to high until boiling.
Reduce heat to low, cover and simmer 15 minutes. Add macaroni; heat to medium and cook 10 more minutes until macaroni is tender and vegetables are done.
Stir occasionally. Serve.

title: granny's peanut butter cookies(makes 7 dozen)
directions: Melt butter.
Beat together with the sugars, vanilla, peanut butter and eggs.
In a separate bowl, combine the flour, bran, oats and baking soda.
Stir mixture into butter mixture.

title: cotton pickin' cake
directions: Mix cake mix, oranges and juice, eggs and oil in mixer for 2 to 3 minutes.
Bake in two 9-inch greased and floured pans for 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.
Let cake cool before frosting.
Mix together the Cool Whip, pineapple and juice, coconut pie filling and vanilla.
Frost on cold cake.
Keep refrigerated.

title: new england turkey chowder
directions: In a 5-quart pan over medium heat, saute celery and onion in margarine until crisp and tender.
Add broth, potatoes, salt, pepper and cayenne pepper.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat to low. Once the mixture is at a simmer, cover and cook 8 to 10 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Stir in turkey.
In a medium bowl, gradually add milk to cornstarch, mixing all the time.
Stir mixture into soup.
Increase heat to medium.
Cook 6 to 8 minutes.

title: martha washington candy
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients and form small balls. Chill about 15 minutes.
In
a	double	boiler,
melt
the chocolate chips and paraffin. Dip balls with a toothpick into the melted chocolate mix.

title: strawberry trifle
directions: Prepare vanilla pudding with milk according to package directions; set aside.
In a separate bowl, combine strawberry gelatin and boiling water; stir in frozen strawberries.
In a clear glass bowl, layer half the crumbled cake, half strawberry gelatin mixture and half vanilla pudding.
Repeat layers.
Spread Cool Whip over top and garnish with sliced strawberries.
Keep chilled.

title: marinade mushrooms
directions: Cut each mushroom in half.
Combine remaining ingredients; put in jar.
Place in refrigerator at least 2 hours.
Stir occasionally.
Serve with toothpicks.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Put cubed Velveeta and 1/2 cup oleo in bottom of square casserole and spread broccoli on top.
Melt 1/2 cup oleo and mix with crackers.
Spread on top of broccoli. Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, milk and butter.
Heat until start of boil. Let cool 1 minute.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Drop onto wax paper by spoonfuls.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Combine sweet potato, butter, evaporated milk, sugar, brown sugar, cinnamon, mace, vanilla and eggs.
Beat at medium speed until smooth.
Put into pie shell.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes, then at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: bread pudding
directions: Grease 9 x 12-inch pan with margarine.
Tear bread into pieces and let them fall in pan.
Blend together remaining ingredients. Pour over bread.
Bake, uncovered, in oven preheated to 350°
for 45 minutes to 1 hour, or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Makes
8 servings.

title: frozen hot fudge delite
directions: 1st Layer:
Crush cookies with a rolling pin and mix with butter.
Press in a 13 x 9-inch pan and freeze for 30 minutes.

title: creamed turkey casserole
directions: Cook green pepper, onions and celery in margarine for 2 minutes.
Blend in flour.
Stir in milk gradually.
Cook, stirring constantly, until thickens.
Add seasonings, turkey, pimento and soup.
Pour into casserole.
Top with biscuits.
Bake at 350° to 375° until biscuits are done.

title: mom's orange salad
directions: Bring to boil the sugar and water; remove from heat.
Add jello and dissolve.
Pour over sour cream; mix well with wire whisk.
Add pineapple, juice and all.
Add drained can of mandarin orange sections and nuts.
Pour into mold; refrigerate until firm.

title: walnut torte cake
directions: Mix flour and nuts.
To yolks, add sugar, vanilla and water (heat).
Add to this flour and nut mixture.
Wash egg beaters; add to egg whites the cream of tartar and salt.
Beat to stiff peaks, then mix egg white mixture into egg yolk mixture.
Line bottom of tube pan with wax paper.
Bake in ungreased tube pan 50 to 60 minutes at 325°.
Cut around tube in middle and edge.
Remove from pan immediately when taken from oven.
Cool thoroughly before icing.

title: quick mustard chicken
directions: Cut each chicken breast in half. Set aside.
Combine mustard, oil, garlic and parsley and spread equal amounts of mustard mixture on both sides of each breast.
Set aside for 1 hour to marinate.
Broil
or grill breasts until cooked through and lightly browned.
Don't overcook. Serve hot or cold with fresh green vegetable.

title: sand cups
directions: You will also need 8 to 10 (7 ounce) plastic cups.

title: chicken chalupas
directions: In greased 9
x
13-inch baking dish, place 1/2 crushed chips. Saute onion;
add
soups,
milk
and taco sauce.
Cook until well blended.
Spoon
half
of
soup mixture over chips, then sprinkle with 1/2 chicken and 1/2 cheese.
Repeat layers. Bake at 350° about 25 minutes.

title: crab and potato hash
directions: Cut red potatoes into small thin cubes.
Microwave for 10 minutes.
Dice onion and green pepper in skillet.
Add all ingredients and cook on Low for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: creole shrimp
directions: Heat shortening in a heavy pan and blend in the flour.
Cook over medium-high heat until roux is golden brown, stirring constantly.
Add vegetables, parsley and cloves.
Cook and stir for 2 minutes.
Add water, tomato sauce, dry seasoning and lemon. Turn heat low.
Cover pan closely and simmer 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add shrimp and heat.
Serve over rice.
Makes 4 servings.

title: lazy day macaroni
directions: Blend all ingredients in a 2-quart casserole.
Bake 20 minutes in a 400° oven.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: french blueberry dessert
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients; press onto cookie sheet.
Bake 15 minutes at 375°.
Cool.
Crumble into baking dish.
Reserve small amount for top.

title: mexican meat loaf
directions: Brown ground beef.
Mix beef sauce and soup together.
Lay Doritos in bottom of pan.
Pour mixture over.
Spread cheese over top.
Bake at 350° until cheese melts.

title: hot pretzels(bridgette's favorite table scraps.)
directions: Pour warm water into measuring glass, sprinkle in yeast.
Pour into bowl; add sugar and salt.
Stir in flour.
Turn dough onto floured surface.
Knead until smooth, about 5 to 10 minutes. Divide into sections and shape into pretzels.
Put on greased cookie sheet.
Brush with egg and sprinkle with coarse salt.
Bake at 425° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes 1 dozen.

title: nut delights
directions: Beat egg white until frothy.
If white is beaten too much, it will not hold together.
Combine sugar and chopped nuts.
Add the egg white and mix well.
Drop by teaspoonfuls 2 inches apart on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 20 minutes.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni until tender.
Drain.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over macaroni in 8 x 10-inch casserole.
Bake 25 minutes at 375°.

title: monster cookies
directions: Cream butter, peanut butter and sugars together.
Add eggs, vanilla and corn syrup.
Add soda and oatmeal.
Add chocolate chips and M&M's.
Drop with tablespoon on floured cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: anne's manicotti
directions: Thaw spinach souffle.
Mix with cheese.
Spoon into raw noodles.
Cook ground beef, drain; add spaghetti sauce.
Thin consistency
is needed, so add about 1/3 cup water if necessary. Put a layer of sauce in bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Lay raw stuffed noodles on top. Pour remaining sauce over noodles until all covered.
Cover tightly with heavy foil.
Bake at 350°
for 1 hour.
Great to have in freezer for unexpected company.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: easy chewy brownies
directions: Melt butter and cocoa powder in saucepan.
Set aside to cool. Beat eggs, sugar and vanilla.
Stir in chocolate mixture.
Add flour, beat well.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan (spray bottom with cooking spray).
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: strawberry jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Add strawberries and pineapple. Mash bananas with fork and mix well.
Refrigerate to congeal.

title: tomato and lima bean salad
directions: Cut a slice from the top of each tomato and with a teaspoon remove the pulp.
To the beans (if very large, cut in halves) add the onion, parsley, nuts, celery and seasoning.
Mix a little French dressing with these ingredients and fill the tomatoes with the mixture.
Pour more dressing over the top or serve it separately.
Any dressing desired may be served.
The tomatoes may be peeled and cut in thick slices, and the other ingredients piled on them if preferred.

title: delicious cheese balls
directions: At room temperature, whip the cream cheese until creamy.
Add all other ingredients except 1 cup pecans.
Mix ingredients well. Roll into 2 balls, rolling remaining 1 cup pecans into balls. Place in aluminum foil overnight so onion and bell pepper taste won't be too strong.

title: celest salad
directions: Combine ingredients, except 1/2 almonds and 1/2 parsley.

title: cottage cheese dip
directions: Blend all ingredients, cover and chill.
Serve as is or add some of your favorite herbs and spices in small amounts.

title: s--- on the shingle(in memory of glen martin)
directions: Brown ground beef till done.
Put 2 qts. of water in a cooker and bring to a boil.
Add beef to water and add the margarine. Add enough milk or cream to make it white colored, then mix corn starch with milk or water (about 2/3 c.)
Pour in and stir to thicken.
Make it as thick as you like.
Add salt & pepper to taste.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: ham and cheese casserole
directions: Melt oleo; blend flour and slowly stir flour and oleo mixture and milk together.
Cook until thick.
Add Cheez Whiz.
Cook macaroni according to package directions.
Add to cheese sauce. Put macaroni and cheese mixture into greased casserole dish and top with mixture of chopped ham, horseradish and mustard.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: old-fashioned popcorn balls
directions: Place popcorn in large bowl or pan.

In heavy 2-quart saucepan, stir together corn syrup, vinegar, sugar and water. Stirring constantly, cook over medium heat until mixture boils. Continue cooking, stirring occasionally, until temperature reaches 265° on candy thermometer, or until small amount of mixture dropped into very cold water forms a ball which is hard enough to hold its shape, yet elastic.
Remove from heat; stir in margarine.
Slowly pour over popcorn, stirring with a long handled spoon.
When cool enough to handle, yet still quite warm, quickly shape into balls. Wrap each individually in plastic wrap.
Makes about ten 3-inch balls.

title: 6 week bran muffins
directions: Mix bran, flour, sugar, baking soda, spice and salt in a large bowl.
Add eggs, margarine, vanilla and buttermilk.
Mix well. Store in covered container in the refrigerator and use as desired.

title: cherry salad
directions: Blend milk and Cool Whip. Fold in other ingredients. Pour into glass bowl and chill.

title: cappuccino mix
directions: It is with love we dedicate this section to our beloved friends, family and church members who not only touched our hearts with their zeal for life, but passed on treasured family recipes which we have assembled in this section as a tribute to them. They loved not only cooking, but sharing and seeing people enjoy what they had prepared.
So, when you try one of the recipes, remember to add their basic ingredients of 1 extra large smile, 3 heaping tablespoonfuls of love, 1 cup of kindness and 4 tablespoons of joy.

title: campfire stew
directions: Brown beef; drain off fat.
Add onions, ABC soup, water, salt, pepper and chili powder.
Simmer about 30 minutes.

title: baked potato slims instead of fried
directions: Dip potatoes in vegetable oil, water and Tabasco sauce.
Shake off excess liquid. Add 1/4 cup grated Parmesan cheese to Shake 'n Bake. Place 8 to 10 potato strips at a time.
Shake until well coated.
Place in single layer on foil.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes in a 350° oven.
Makes 4 servings.

title: brunch egg casserole
directions: Cook bacon until crisp; drain.
In bottom of 10 x 5 x 1 3/4-inch baking dish combine croutons and cheese.
Combine slightly beaten eggs and next 5 ingredients.
Pour over crouton mixture in casserole dish.
Sprinkle bacon over top of casserole. Bake at 325° for 55 to 60 minutes, until eggs are set.
Garnish with bacon curls if desired.

title: company breakfast pizza
directions: Saute sausage until browned; drain well.
Separate crescent dough into 8 triangles.
Place in an ungreased 12-inch (must have high rim) pizza pan with points toward center.
Press over bottom and up sides to form a crust; seal perforations.
Spoon sausage over crust.
Sprinkle with potatoes.
Top with Cheddar cheese.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Combine margarine, cocoa, water and oil.
Bring to a boil.
Add this to the flour and sugar.
In a small bowl, mix the eggs, buttermilk, soda and vanilla.
Add to mixture.
Bake at 300° for about 20 minutes.
Top with icing.

title: holiday eggnog
directions: Pour eggnog into small punch bowl.
Drop remaining whipped cream in 4 or 5 mounds onto eggnog.
Sprinkle nutmeg on whipped cream mounds.
Serve immediately.
Immediately refrigerate any remaining eggnog.

title: quick skillet lasagna
directions: Cook beef, onion and garlic in heavy frypan.
Add tomatoes, paste, parsley, oregano and water; bring to a boil.
Stir in noodles and simmer until noodles are tender and sauce is thickened; about 25 minutes.
Stir only to prevent sticking.
Mix cheeses; drop by teaspoonfuls onto lasagna mixture.
Cover and heat 5 minutes.

title: whipped cake
directions: Beat egg yolks with water until it increases in volume to about a quart.
Gradually beat in sugar, then add flour, sifted with baking powder and salt.
Add the vanilla.
Fold in egg whites which have been beaten until stiff.
Pour batter into greased tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, or until done.
Leave in pan until cold.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Drain fat.
Pour in tomatoes, kidney beans, corn and taco seasoning mix.
Bring to boil; simmer 15 minutes.
Garnish with chips, sour cream and avocado.
Enjoy!

title: lasagne
directions: Brown sausage slowly; drain off fat.
Add tomatoes, tomato paste, basil, garlic and 1/2 teaspoon salt; simmer, uncovered, 30 minutes and stir occasionally.
Cook noodles in boiling salted water until tender; drain.

title: creamy mac and vegetables
directions: In skillet over medium heat in hot butter, cook broccoli and carrots until tender-crisp, stirring often.
Add soup, garlic powder, pepper and macaroni.
Heat through, stirring occasionally.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Cream the peanut butter and cream cheese.
Add sugar.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Put in pie crusts and chill at least 4 hours or overnight.

title: rocky road
directions: Combine chocolate chips, butterscotch and peanut butter in a bowl.
Microwave ingredients for 4 minutes.
Fold in bag of marshmallows and salted peanuts.
Spread mixture in a buttered 4 x 13-inch pan and refrigerate until set.

title: chocolate salad dressing cake
directions: Mix sugar, salad dressing, cocoa and soda.
Add warm water. Add sifted flour, salt and vanilla.
Beat by hand for best results. Bake in greased cake tins (two layers) for 20 minutes or a 13 x 9-inch pan for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: cranberry mold
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water.
Add pineapple syrup; chill until thick.
Add cranberries, nuts, apple and grapes; chill until set.

title: brisket
directions: Mix liquid smoke, 4 tablespoons Worcestershire, celery salt, garlic salt and onion salt together.
Pour over brisket and marinate overnight.
Cook covered brisket 1 hour per pound at 250°.
Slice and place in casserole dish.
Saute onion, margarine, brown sugar, 4 tablespoons Worcestershire sauce and catsup.
Pour over sliced brisket.
Bake for 1 hour at 250°.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all together and microwave for about 8 to 10 minutes or bake in oven at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: cream of celery soup
directions: In a heavy saucepan, melt 3 Tbsp. of butter.
Add celery, onion and garlic.
Saute about 10 minutes.	Add bay leaf, 1/2 cup wine and chicken broth.
Simmer 20 minutes, stirring occasionally. Discard bay leaf.
Puree cooked mixture and stir in remaining white wine, salt, pepper, basil and half & half.
In a small skillet melt remaining butter and stir in flour.
Cook for 1 minute.
Blend in 1 cup of soup and whisk to smooth.
Add butter and flour mixture to soup in saucepan.
Cook until soup thickens slightly.
Serve using celery leaves for garnish.

title: cranberry delight
directions: Add sugar to gelatin and fix according to directions (not a full cup).
Let partially congeal.
Grind cranberries and celery with food chopper.
Chop apple and pecans.
Add to gelatin and let congeal.
(Keeps for weeks in refrigerator).
Add 1 or 2 oranges if you like.
Grind it peel and all when you grind the cranberries and celery.
(You can add an extra pack of plain gelatin if you like to make it real firm.
You can double this recipe.)

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Blend liquid Butter Buds, flour and seasonings over low heat in a saucepan.
Stir and cook until bubbly.
Remove from heat and stir in broth and skim milk.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Boil and stir for 1 minute.
Add spaghetti, chicken and mushrooms.
Pour into a 9 x 11-inch casserole dish that has been sprayed with Pam.
Sprinkle both cheeses on top and bake, uncovered, for 30 minutes or until bubbly.
Place under broiler to brown.

title: crunchy cucumber pickles
directions: After draining pickles, pour this syrup over them and let stand overnight.
Cook about 45 minutes or until pickles are clear.
Pack in jars and seal.
Process at simmering temperature for 15 minutes.
Makes 13 pints.

title: five layer dinner
directions: Layer potatoes, beef, onions, pepper and tomatoes in this order in a 2-quart casserole dish.
Season each layer with salt and pepper.
Garnish with sliced green peppers.
Cover and bake 2 hours at 350°.

title: hot tamale casserole
directions: Put 1 can of chili in casserole dish. Put hot tamales on top. Then put the other can of chili on the hot tamales. Pour chopped onions on top of the chili, then sprinkle the grated cheese on top of the onions. Put the corn chips on top of the grated cheese and around the edges. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until the cheese melts.

title: beef chou-fleur
directions: Cut meat into 1/2-inch squares.
Brown on all sides in butter or margarine.
Add broth. Cover and simmer for 45 to 60 minutes or until almost tender. Add cauliflower, green pepper, soy sauce and garlic.

Stir lightly to coat vegetables with soy sauce. Cover and simmer until vegetables are barely tender, about 10 minutes. Blend cornstarch and sugar with a small amount of water. Add to meat mixture with green onions. Cook, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Serve over fluffy rice.
Serves 6.

title: crock-pot roast
directions: Put raost into crock-pot.
Mix remaining ingredients and put on top.
Cook all day on low.
(I put it on when i go to work and its ready when I get home.)
Save the juice for dipping or makes good gravy!

title: sand tarts
directions: Mix butter into flour and sugar.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Roll into balls the size of a small walnut.
Place on a lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375°
for approximately 10 minutes until lightly tan on the bottom.
Remove from cookie sheet and roll in powdered sugar.

title: creamy pralines
directions: Combine sugar and cream, then water and mix.
When mixture begins to cook, watch carefully as it burns quickly.
(It is safer to use a double boiler.)
When mixture will form soft ball when tested in water, remove from fire, beat until creamy and add butter.
Continue beating, then add pecans.
Drop by spoonfuls onto wax paper or buttered sauces.

title: marshmallow cream fudge
directions: Mix sugar, milk and butter.
Cook until mixture comes to a boil, stirring frequently.
Boil 5 minutes. (I cook a little longer.)
Remove from heat and stir in chocolate chips, marshmallow cream and vanilla.
Stir ingredients until mixture is creamy and smooth.
Add nuts.
Pour into buttered 9 x 9-inch pan.

title: cranberry tea
directions: Bring water and sugar to a boil.
Remove from heat add tea bags.
Cover.
Leave 6 minutes.
Remove bags and add cloves and cinnamon in a spice bag or strain later.
Leave 30 minutes. Remove spices.
Add jello.
Stir to dissolve.
Add cranberry juice, apple juice, orange juice and lemon juice.
Heat and serve.

title: hot bacon and mushroom dip
directions: Fry bacon in large skillet until crisp.
Drain and crumble, set aside.
Discard all but 2 tablespoons bacon drippings from skillet.
Add mushrooms and onions.
Cook until tender.
Mix in flour, salt, pepper, cream cheese, Worcestershire and soy sauce. Blend well.
Remove from heat.
Add crumbled bacon and sour cream. Serve warm with crackers.

title: crisp pecan cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Stir in flour and salt until blended.
Stir in pecans.
Chill for 30 minutes.
Shape into round balls and mash down with a fork.
Bake in 350° oven for 12 minutes.

title: prego supper
directions: Brown ground beef with onion and green pepper in skillet, stirring frequently.
Drain.
Add spaghetti sauce, mixing well. Stir in macaroni.
Spoon into baking dish.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.
Yields 10 servings.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain pineapple; put into a mixing bowl.
Add Cool Whip and stir.
Add jello mix and stir; add walnuts and stir.
If you like you may also add marshmallows, coconut or graham crackers.
Put into the refrigerator.
Cool.
Ready to serve and eat.

title: barbecue
directions: Cook together until done, 2 or so hours.
Mash meat until stringy.
Continue cooking until desired thickness.

title: olive risotto(microwave)
directions: In a 2-quart casserole dish, combine butter, onion, celery, rice, bouillon, salt and pepper.
Cover.
Microwave at High for 24 to 26 minutes, stirring after 10 minutes.
Add olives, mushrooms, pimientos and cheese.
Stir to mix well.
Microwave on High for 2 to 4 minutes.
Stir before serving.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Boil chicken and add rice.
Cook until gummy.
Mix chicken and rice, soup and olives together.
Place in large baking pan.
Add cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
It's good to use leftover chicken and rice.

title: potato soup
directions: Peel the potatoes, then "cube" them and place into a saucepan. Dice the onion; add to the potatoes.
Cover the potatoes with water.
Add salt, then cook the potatoes until they are tender. Remove from heat.
Add the milk and butter.
Pepper to taste. Serves 4.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Mix mayonnaise and sugar; set aside.
Layer lettuce with bell pepper.
Top with a second layer of lettuce and then onions.
Top with third layer of lettuce and follow with water chestnuts and peas.
Spoon mayo mixture around top and carefully spread with spoon, sealing with side of bowl.
Sprinkle with cheese and bacon before serving.

title: cream puffs
directions: Put butter in boiling water, when butter is melted, stir in pudding mix.
Take pan off stove and stir for about 5 minutes. Add eggs and stir another 5 minutes.
Drop on buttered cookie sheet 2-inches apart, fill with your favorite instant pudding. While baking pudding, add Cool Whip and beat until creamy.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: beef stir-fry
directions: Brown meat in margarine about 5 minutes.
Add cauliflower, green pepper, soy sauce and garlic.
Stir lightly to coat vegetables with soy sauce.
Cover pan and simmer until vegetables are barely tender, about 10 minutes.
Blend cornstarch and broth. Add to meat mixture with green onions.
Cook, stirring constantly, until heated and sauce is thickened.
Serve over a bed of fluffy rice.
Serve with steamed snow peas and baked mini egg rolls.

title: hot dip
directions: Use 10-inch glass pie plate. Spread softened cream cheese in pie plate.
Slice cheese and place on cream cheese.
Spread chili on top of cheese. Bake 20 minutes at 400° or until bubbly.
Serve with nacho chips.

title: taco salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.

title: enchiladas
directions: Fry tortilla shells just slightly on both sides.
Use enchilada sauce in recipe.
Brown the ground beef, salt, onion, chili powder and pepper.
Drain meat.
Spread each tortilla shell with sauce.
Add meat and sprinkle with onion and cheese.
Roll up and put side by side in a 9 x 12-inch baking pan.
Pour remaining sauce over top and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake 30 minutes in a 350° to 375° oven.

title: fish mightydamngood
directions: Wash and dry fish fillets and set aside.
In heavy saucepan, sprayed with cooking spray, saute onion, celery and green pepper until tender.
Add remaining ingredients.
Stir to chop up tomatoes and cook until sauce has reduced by approximately 1/3. (Sauce should not be thin and runny, but not quite as thick as a medium white sauce.)

title: broccoli and cheese casserole
directions: In a Dutch oven, saute broccoli and onion in butter until done.
Add soup and Cheez Whiz.
Over low heat stir until cheese is melted.
Add rice.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch dish at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: marinara sauce
directions: Saute onions and garlic.
Combine with remaining ingredients and simmer for 15 minutes.
Excellent over angel hair pasta.

title: crockpot cranberry applesauce
directions: Combine cranberries, apples and sugar in slow cooker.
Place cinnamon and cloves in center of 6-inch square of cheesecloth. Pull up around sides; tie to form pouch.
Place in pot.
Cover and cook on LOW 4-5 hrs or until cranberries and apples are very soft.

title: 7 up cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter together, beat until light and fluffy, add eggs one at a time, beat well.
Add flour, lemon extract and 7 up.
Fold batter into well greased and floured flute mold.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: beef macaroni soup
directions: Place boiling beef in 5-quart pan and fill 3/4 full with water.
Add other ingredients, except macaroni; cook beef until tender.
Take meat out and cool.
Break into small pieces and return to pan.
Boil the macaroni in separate pan to desired tenderness; drain and rinse well.
Add to soup broth and heat.

title: crock-pot chicken and dressing
directions: Mix together all ingredients, except margarine.
Put into crock-pot and place margarine on top.
Cook on high for 2 hours or cook for 3 to 4 hours on low setting.

title: chicken pasta sonora
directions: Cook pasta as package directs; drain.
Season chicken with salt and pepper.
In skillet, brown chicken in oil over medium-high heat; drain.
Stir in garlic; add tomatoes, tomato sauce and olives.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer, 10 minutes. Uncover; cook 10 minutes over medium-high heat or until thickened, stirring occasionally.
Add green pepper; cook 5 minutes.
Just before serving, spoon chicken and sauce over hot pasta.
Garnish with chopped cilantro, if desired.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: Combine flour, salt and pepper in plastic bag.
Add one piece of chicken at a time; shake to coat.
In a large skillet, heat 2 tablespoons oil.
Brown chicken on all sides.
Heat other oil and saute onion, bell pepper and garlic.
Stir in tomatoes, bouillon, oregano and bay leaf.
Add the chicken pieces and let simmer 20 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Discard bay leaf.
Serve over spaghetti, tossed with Parmesan cheese.

title: potluck potatoes(lightened version)
directions: Cook potatoes in boiling water for 10 to 12 minutes or until tender. Drain. Rinse with cold water. Drain again.
In a large mixing bowl, stir together the soup, sour cream, cream cheese and the dry butter flavor mix.
Add 1/4 cup of the shredded cheese, 3 tablespoons green onion, skim milk, parsley, garlic salt and pepper. Stir to combine. Stir in the cooked potatoes.
Place in 2-quart shallow casserole.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes. Sprinkle with remaining cheese and onion.
Makes 10 servings.

title: barbecue spareribs
directions: To barbecue, season ribs by rubbing them lightly with salt, black pepper and paprika and cook on grill.
You want the smoke to do the cooking.
Cook long and slow, 2 hours or so.
Heat bacon grease or butter in a large heavy saucepan over medium heat. Brown the onion for 5 minutes.
Add in all remaining ingredients. Bring to a boil, then simmer over low heat 20 minutes, uncovered. Baste ribs with sauce the last 15 to 20 minutes of cooking.

title: pie crust
directions: Mix all together and roll between wax paper.
Makes two double crust pies.

title: pork chop supreme
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Season chops well with salt; place in 13 x 9 1/2 x 2-inch pan.
Top each chop with an onion slice and a lemon slice.
Place 1 tablespoon brown sugar and 1 tablespoon catsup on each chop.
Cover and bake 1 hour.
Uncover and bake until chops are browned.

title: hot or cold shrimp pasta salad
directions: In a large saucepan, lightly saute the garlic in olive oil.
Do not brown.
Add shrimp and cook 1 minute.
Add sour cream, peas, thyme, salt and pepper and mix thoroughly.
When heated through (do not boil), either pour over hot, drained pasta or allow to cool and toss with cool cooked pasta.
Serve with a small green salad with herb vinaigrette dressing.
Serves 3.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Cream 2 cups sugar and 3/4 cup margarine until light and fluffy.
Blend in eggs and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Add combined flour and 2/3 cup cocoa; mix well.
Stir in nuts and coconut.
Pour into greased and floured 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until pick inserted in center comes out clean. Spread Marshmallow Creme over top of cake.
Cool.
Cream margarine; blend in vanilla.
Add combined sugar and cocoa alternately with milk, beating until light and fluffy.
Spread over Marshmallow Creme.

title: marinated iowa pork chops
directions: Place pork chops in Ziploc bag or in a shallow pan.
Poke with fork.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients except cracker crumbs.
Pour into 3 or 4-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Sprinkle crumbs on top and bake another 5 to 10 minutes.
Serves 10 to 12 people.

title: shrimp dip delight
directions: Boil, peel, devein and chop shrimp.
In a bowl, blend cream cheese with onions, celery, lemon juice, parsley, salt, cayenne and mayonnaise.
Fold in shrimp.
Cover and refrigerate.
Serve with crackers or fresh celery and carrot sticks.

title: oreo cookie dessert
directions: Mix melted margarine and all but 1/2 cup of crushed Oreo cookies. Press in bottom of large covered dish. Chill until firm. Combine cream cheese, half whipped topping and sugar. Mix until smooth. Spread over cookie crust. Mix instant pudding and milk until thick and smooth; spread over cream cheese mixture. Spread remainder of whipped topping on top of pudding; sprinkle reserved half cup of cookie crumbs on top. Refrigerate until time to serve.

title: german chicken 'n noodles
directions: Saute in butter, chicken, onion and mushrooms.
Cook until chicken is done.
Add 2 packages of demi-glace, milk and water. Stir and bring to a boil.
Turn down to simmer.
Boil noodles until done.
Drain.
Serve sauce over noodles.

title: three c bread
directions: Combine beaten eggs, oil and milk.
In large bowl, sift together flour, sugar, baking powder, soda, cinnamon and salt. Add egg mixture; mix just until thoroughly combined.
Stir in carrot, coconut, cherries, raisins and pecans.
Turn into 4 well-greased and floured 16 ounce fruit or vegetable cans.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 to 50 minutes.
Remove from cans and cool thoroughly.
Wrap and refrigerate overnight or until used.
Makes 4 small loaves.

title: crock-pot vegetable soup
directions: Mix all except barley in crock-pot and cook on low about 5 hours; add barley last 1/2 hour of cooking.

title: stuffed boneless chicken(for family of four)
directions: Mix stuffing as directed on box.
Cut whole breast in half; place 1/2 in baking pan.
Add some stuffing on top.
Place other half on top.
Repeat with rest of chicken breasts.
Bake covered 45 minutes or until just browning at 350°.

title: brenda's punch bowl cake
directions: Take a cup of friendship and a cup of thoughtfulness; cream together with a pinch of powdered tenderness, very lightly beaten. Add a bowl of loyalty, a cup of faith, one of hope and one of charity.
Be sure to add a spoonful each of gaiety that sings, the ability to laugh at little things and the sudden tears of heartfelt sympathy.
Bake in a good-natured pan and serve repeatedly.

title: country chicken and potato bake
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
In large roasting pan, toss potatoes, onion with chicken, salt, rosemary and pepper.
Arrange in the baking pan with the chicken pieces skin-side up; bake uncovered, 1 hour or until potatoes are done and the chicken runs clear juices when pierced with a fork.
Baste with pan drippings occasionally during cooking.

title: crescent casserole
directions: Separate crescent dough into two long rectangles.
Place in ungreased 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Press over bottom.
Brown meat and onion; drain.
Stir in 3/4 teaspoon garlic salt and oregano. Spoon meat mixture over dough.
Spoon tomato sauce over meat. Sprinkle with cheese.

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Using electric beater, beat egg whites until stiff.
Add sugar, vanilla and food coloring.
Beat until peaked.
Toss in chips.
Drop into greased cookie sheets (use cooking spray).
Turn oven off.
Leave in oven overnight or for 6 to 7 hours.

title: dorito pie
directions: Crunch taco chips and put in the bottom of a 9 X 13 glass pan. Set aside. Brown hamburger. Add cream of mushroom soup and taco salsa. Pour over chips and bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Remove from oven, top with cheddar cheese. Bake just until cheese is melted. Serve with lettuce, tomato and sour cream. Extra chips, too!

title: autumn's favorite rice and beans
directions: Put some beans on top of some rice.
Some sour cream on it. Salsa.
I want to sprinkle the cheese on myself.
Okay.

title: green fresh salsa
directions: Blend all in electric blender.
Makes 1 cup salsa.

title: cream cheese cake squares
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in a large mixing bowl; mix well. Press mixture into a lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: crab spread
directions: Melt butter and cream cheese in saucepan.
Stir to mix.
Add sealegs and mix.
Add remaining ingredients to taste.
Pour in small casserole.
Sprinkle with paprika and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Great with saltine crackers.

title: mom's oatmeal cookies
directions: Scoop dough by the heaping tablespoonfuls onto an ungreased cookie sheet about 2 inches apart.
Bake in a 350° oven for 13 to 15 minutes.
(Can also make into logs and slice.)
Makes a bunch!!

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients; beat together.
Add the apples, flour, cinnamon, soda and nuts.
Mix well.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: low-fat easy fudge brownies
directions: In a large mixing bowl, stir brownie mix, Hershey's syrup, Egg Beaters and water together until just moistened.
Spray casserole dish with nonfat cooking spray.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes. Let cool about 10 minutes and spread Braum's fudge lite topping on top.
Yields 24.
Fat:
0.5 g per serving.

title: blue ridge mountain corn bread
directions: In separate bowls, beat the egg whites and yolks.
To the egg yolks, add the sugar and beat well.
Add the corn meal, milk and flour.
Add the melted butter, beaten egg whites, baking powder and salt.
Pour into a greased iron skillet.
Bake at 450° in oven until golden and done.

title: baked beans
directions: Soak beans overnite in water, enough water to cover beans. Rinse in cold water.
Cover beans with water.
Cook on top of stove until tender.
Put chopped onions in while cooking beans. Add Karo syrup, salt, pepper and bacon, cut in pieces.
Bake at 350°.
When beans are a nice light brown, take out of oven.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Make cake according to directions; bake in 13 x 9 pan and cool.

title: egg custard pie
directions: Mix well.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: egg sauce for salmon loaf
directions: Cook, stirring constantly, until sauce thickens.
Add 1 or more hard-cooked eggs, sliced.

title: caramel corn
directions: Melt butter and stir in brown sugar, corn syrup and salt. Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Boil without stirring for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and add baking soda and vanilla.
Mix well.
Pour over popcorn.
You may add nuts, if desired.
Bake for 1 hour at 250°.
Stir every 15 minutes.
Enjoy!

title: crackling corn bread
directions: Put corn meal into bowl. Put salt, baking powder, buttermilk and flour. Mix well. Put in crackling. Pour into a greased pan. Put into a 450° oven for about 35 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: spoon rolls
directions: Place yeast in warm water.
Melt butter and cream with sugar. Add beaten egg, add yeast and then add flour.
Mix well.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes in greased muffin pans.

title: coconut cookies
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff peaks form; fold in sweetener.
Add cornflakes, coconut, chopped pecans and almond extract.
Drop from teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for about 12 minutes.
Yield:
4 dozen.
Carbohydrate 2.4 g, protein .3 g, fat 1.1 g, calories 24.
One cookie = 1/2 fat exchange.

title: barbecue chicken
directions: Saute onion in oil and add other ingredients.
Simmer 5 to 10 minutes.
Place chicken in a large baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Remove and pour barbecue sauce over chicken, brushing each piece well.
Bake for approximately 30 more minutes or until well done.

title: sweetened condensed milk
directions: Mix ingredients in a blender until all the sugar has dissolved and the mixture is smooth. A few drops of water can be added to the mixture, if necessary, to make it look like sweetened condensed milk.
Store in refrigerator.

title: bran cereal muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°
(hot).
Grease
muffin tins; stir bran cereal and milk together
in
a bowl.
Let stand a minute or two; add egg, oil and honey, and beat well.
Stir remaining ingredients together until well
mixed.
Add to liquid mixture and stir only until mixed.
Put
into muffin tins.
Bake about 20 to 25 minutes or
until
lightly
browned.
Makes 12 medium sized muffins.

title: chocolate zucchini bread
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs, 1 at a time, then vanilla.
Mix all dry ingredients together and include chips.
Add alternately with milk.
Stir in zucchini and nuts.
Grease well and flour a 10-inch tube pan or 2 large loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: buttermilk biscuits
directions: Bake at 450° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: the best potato salad ever
directions: Combine all ingredients and enjoy.

title: deer jerky
directions: Put all ingredients together and shake up.
Pour over meat overnight.
Works best if you have plenty of sauce for amount of meat.
Place on oven racks or cheesecloth.
Bake on lowest heat. Bake 4 to 8 hours until jerky will crack when bent.
Remove from oven.
Let cool and dry.
Put into jars.

title: apple-carrot salad
directions: Combine apples, carrots, raisins and walnuts.
Blend yogurt with honey and pour over the other ingredients, mixing thoroughly.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix cornstarch with water; stir well.
Add Jell-O and sugar. Cook until thick.
Cool.
Place strawberries (whole or sliced) in pie shell.
Pour Jell-O mixture over strawberries.
Chill.
Serve with Cool Whip on top.

title: hawaiian cake
directions: Combine cake mix with eggs, oil, sour cream and crushed pineapple.
Be sure to use juice.
Beat with electric mixer for a full 3 minutes.
Pour batter into well-greased 9 x 13-inch pan. (Use this size only.)

title: grandma's bread pudding
directions: Heat milk and butter until scalded. Grease a 1 1/2-quart casserole. Add remaining ingredients to scalded milk and butter and pour into greased casserole dish. Place casserole in pan of very HOT water and bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes or until a knife inserted 1-inch from edge comes out clean.

title: spiced tea
directions: Steep tea bag and cinnamon sticks for 20 minutes in 2 quarts boiling water. Add rest of ingredients to steeped tea. Serve hot on a cold night.

title: kahlua cake
directions: Mix all ingredients in large mixing bowl except chocolate chips.
Fold in chips by hand.
Spoon into greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: summer salad with poppy seed dressing
directions: Wash and dry spinach; discard stems and break leaves into a bowl. Add sliced strawberries. Toss with dressing right before serving. Serves 4-6.

title: cioppino
directions: For each serving fold a 12 x 16-inch sheet of aluminum foil lengthwise in half. Rum some of the butter on half of the foil. Top with a fish fillet and sprinkle fish with thyme.
Add broccoli spears, remaining butter and the wine.
Fold foil to cover ingredients. Seal edges tightly.
Place on baking sheet and bake at 425° about 15 minutes or until fish flakes easily with a fork.

title: dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients well and bake at 300° to 325°.

title: string bean casserole
directions: Drain both cans of string beans and rinse.
Let set for 5 minutes.
Combine other ingredients with beans.
Season to taste. Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: cider stew
directions: In large heavy pot, over medium-high heat, brown half the beef at a time in margarine.
Return beef to pot.
Stir in flour, gradually stir in water, cider and steak sauce.
Over high heat, bring to a boil; stir in thyme, pepper and bay leaf.
Reduce heat to low; cover and simmer for 2 hours.
Add potatoes, carrots, onion and beans.
Cover and cook for 30 minutes more or until vegetables are tender.
Discard bay leaf before serving.

title: chicken and dressing
directions: Cook hen; boil, reserving broth until tender.
Debone chicken. Cook cornbread as desired.
Use at least 2 eggs in cornbread. Crumble cornbread, crackers and stale bread chunks in large baking pan.
Add chicken broth, deboned chicken and 6 boiled eggs.
Stir; continue adding broth until desired consistency.
Add chopped onion.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: peachy oatmeal bars
directions: Melt margarine in a 13 x 9-inch pan while preheating oven. Stir in rolled oats, flour, sugar and baking powder until blended. Mixture will be crumbly; reserve 1/2 cup crumbs.
Pat remaining mixture in bottom of pan.
Spread preserves to within 1/2-inch of edges.
Sprinkle on coconut and remaining crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool in pan.

title: three bean salad
directions: Drain in colander until all moisture is gone.

title: sour cream yeast rolls
directions: Soften yeast in warm water.
Combine sour cream, sugar and salt.
Beat in 1 cup flour, yeast and cornmeal.
Stir in enough flour to make soft dough.
Knead 10 times.
Put in greased bowl and brush with butter.
Let rise 2 hours.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix together and chill overnight.
Delicious on raw vegetables, chips or crackers.

title: italian meat loaf
directions: Combine beef, eggs, milk, onion, bell pepper, saltines, salt and pepper.
Mix tomato sauce, basil, oregano, parsley and garlic. Pour 1/2 tomato sauce into meat mixture.
Mix well.
Mixture will be thin.
Pour into meat loaf pan.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes. Reduce heat to 375°; pour remaining sauce over meat and bake 1 1/2 hours.

title: pizza dough
directions: Dissolve yeast into 1/2 cup warm water.
Add sugar and let sit for 10 minutes.
Put yeast and all the remaining water into a large bowl.
Slowly add the flour and salt, kneading when mixture is too stiff to stir.
Add olive oil and keep kneading until the dough is smooth and elastic. Put dough in an oiled bowl and cover.

title: cinnamon-pecan honey pancake syrup
directions: Combine
all ingredients; stir well.
Pour mixture into an airtight container.
Store at room temperature.
Serve over waffles, pancakes or ice cream.
Yields
3 cups.

title: baked corn
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: cheese asparagus crisps
directions: Remove bread crust.
Mix cheese, peppers, horseradish and mayo together.
Spread cheese mixture on bread.
Roll bread around asparagus.
Cut in half.
Place on baking sheet.
Bake until brown, quickly.
Serve warm.
Makes about 40 small rolls.

title: turkey meat loaf
directions: Mix ingredients thoroughly.
Shape into loaf.
Place in shallow baking pan.
Bake
at
for
1 hour.
No need for extra salt since enough is in the soup mix.
You can cook this in crock-pot, but cook in crock-pot about 3 hours.

title: custard pie
directions: Mix together and pour into an uncooked pie shell.
Bake at 475°
for 5 minutes.
Reduce to 425°
for 10 minutes more just until a silver knife inserted 1-inch from side of filling comes out clean.
The center may look a bit soft but will set later. Serve slightly warm or cold.

title: toffee crunch bars
directions: Cream together shortening and brown sugar.
Beat in egg and vanilla.
Add four and salt.
Spread dough in two 8x8x2-inch pans. Bake in moderate oven for 15 minutes or until lightly browned. remove from oven, spread immediately with chocolate and sprinkle with nutmeats.
Cool.
Cut into bars or squares.
Makes 32 2-inch sqares.

title: tortilla crunch chicken fingers
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In a bowl combine soup mix and tortilla chips.
In a large bag or bowl, combine eggs and water; then add chicken, coating well.
Dip chicken into tortilla mixture, coating well.
In a casserole dish, arrange chicken and then sprinkle with butter.
Bake, uncovered, for 12 minutes or until chicken is done. Makes about 24 chicken strips.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Grate potatoes into colander.
Squeeze out juice and drain.
In large bowl, combine all ingredients, except oil.
Mix well.
Heat oil in frypan, 1/8-inch or so (pan hot, not smoking).
Drop 2 tablespoons ingredients in hot fat, flatten and fry 2 to 3 minutes on each side until golden brown.
Drain well on plate with paper towel.
Transfer to ovenproof pan and keep warm in 300° oven until served.

title: pumpkin spice cake
directions: Cake:
Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease two flan pans and line centers with parchment paper.
Prepare spice cake mix according to package directions.
Pour 2 1/2 cups batter into each flan pan. Bake for 25 to 30 minutes or until done.
Cool in pan for 10 minutes.
Loosen cake from edges of pan and turn out onto serving plate. Allow to cool completely before removing parchment paper.

title: chocolate icing
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Will ice 3 layers.

title: zucchini pie (quick)
directions: Mix zucchini, onion and Bisquick.
Mix eggs, oil, cheese, salt and pepper.
Combine the two mixtures.
Add milk; pour into buttered 9 x 13-inch dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes. Serve warm.

title: beef noodle casserole
directions: Brown ground meat and onion in oil.
Add cans of spaghetti sauce and salt.
Blend.
Cook noodles and drain.

title: milky way cake
directions: Melt Milky Way bars, margarine and pecans over low heat.
Let cool.
Mix sugar, buttermilk, soda, eggs, flour and vanilla.
Beat 2 minutes.
Fold in candy mix.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Frost with Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: super baked beans
directions: Mix and bake at 300° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: no name cake
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients very well and press in bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan. Now, mix chocolate chips, coconut, pecans, Eagle Brand milk and vanilla. Spread this mixture over the cake mixture. Bake 28 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: spicy oysters
directions: Mix the Abbits Cajun meal, black pepper and seasoned pepper. Cover oysters with mixture.
Deep fry for 2 to 3 minutes, until done.
Before serving, sprinkle red pepper over the oysters. Pepper quantities can be adjusted to suit taste.
This dish is only for people who like hot food!

title: grand glorious punch
directions: Dissolve one package cherry flavored gelatin in 1 cup boiling water.
Stir in one can frozen lemonade or pineapple-orange juice concentrate.
Add 3 cups cold water and 1 quart bottle cranberry juice chilled.
In a large punch bowl, place 2 trays of ice cubes or a molded ice ring.
Pour punch over ice.
Slowly pour in one quart of chilled ginger ale.
Fruit flavored sherbet may be added, if desired.
Makes about 25 servings.

title: veal marsala
directions: Over medium heat, brown veal (3 minutes per side) after you have coated it with spices.
Remove veal from skillet.
Add mushrooms; saute for 3 minutes.
Mix cornstarch and broth in bowl; stir with wire whisk.
Add this to mushrooms.
Add wine and cook 2 to 3 minutes until thickened and bubbling.
Pour over veal that you have kept warm.
Serves 4.

title: pineapple dump cake
directions: Grease a 13 x 9-inch baking pan lightly with butter.
Dump the entire can of pineapple chunks including juice into pan and spread evenly on the bottom.
Dump the bag of shredded coconut on top of pineapple and spread evenly.
Dump the entire package of dry yellow cake mix on top of coconut.
Smooth evenly with a spatula. Cover the entire surface with 1/2 pound butter, cut into thin squares.
Do not mix! Place pan in a preheated 350° oven for 45 to 50 minutes (until top is lightly browned).
Remove from oven, cool and cut into serving size squares.

title: sweet 'n sour green beans
directions: Fry bacon until crisp.
Remove bacon from drippings.
Add sugar and vinegar to drippings and green beans.
Simmer 25 minutes. Crumble bacon and sprinkle over top of beans.
Serve.

title: raisin pie
directions: Mix and beat first 4 ingredients, then add raisins, coconut, and nuts.
Mix well and pour in pie crust.
Bake 350° for 45 or 50 minutes.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large mixing bowl.
Heat 3 tablespoons oil in an iron skillet.
Pour batter into skillet and bake in a 375° oven for 45 minutes or until done.
Cool for 10 minutes in pan, then turn out onto a plate.
Cut into wedges and serve with butter.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Beat with electric mixer, potatoes, margarine, sugar and salt until mixture is smooth.
Remove any strings from the potatoes from the mixer beaters.
Add eggs, then milk and vanilla.
Beat 3 or 4 minutes at medium speed.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until firm.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and sprinkle 1/4 cup brown sugar and 1/2 cup flake coconut on top.
Bake in a long pan 45 minutes at 350°.

title: ham and asparagus bake
directions: Melt margarine; put in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Add bread. Put ham, then asparagus.
Add Swiss cheese.

title: easy black forest torte
directions: Sprinkle marshmallows in Pam sprayed 9 x 13 dish. Prepare cake according to directions on box. Pour batter over marshmallows. Spoon pie filling on top. Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Let cool. Frost with whipped topping. Store in fridge.

title: calico beans
directions: Fry bacon, meat, onion and pepper together until meat is done. Add other ingredients and simmer.

title: coconut prawns
directions: Combine coconut and panko. De-vein and butterfly prawns leaving tails on. Roll in flour then dip in buttermilk. Roll in panko mix until well coated. Deep fry until golden brown.

title: quick shrimp sauce #1
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Place in refrigerator to chill before serving.
Ideal for boiled shrimp.

title: onion casserole
directions: Mix onions, soup and cheese well.
Place in casserole dish, sprinkle top with more grated cheese and cover with crushed chips. Bake at 350° for approximately 10 to 15 minutes or until bubbly.

title: freshest-possible tomato sauce
directions: Set 1 gallon of water to boil.
Just as it begins to boil, heat olive oil in heavy skillet until a bit of bread dropped into it browns at once.
Add tomatoes to the olive oil and simmer briefly to combine.
Add parsley, basil, garlic, salt and pepper. Cook gently just until herbs go limp.
Remove from flame.
By now, water will be at full boil; toss in pasta and cook for 2 minutes. Drain, then toss with 2 tablespoons of sauce.
Serve on a round platter topped with rest of sauce and fresh basil leaves.
Pass Romano cheese.
Serves 4 as a first course.
Double recipe for a light main course.

title: chinese salad
directions: Mix together the first 3 ingredients.
(Some prefer the noodles uncooked.)
Mix together the next 5 ingredients.
Toast the sesame seed and almonds 4 or 5 minutes at 350° and add to the last mixture and pour over the cabbage and noodles.

title: potato carrot bake(easy holiday fixings)
directions: Scrub potatoes and boil until cooked.
Peel.
Meanwhile, boil carrots until tender.
Mash carrots and potatoes together with butter or margarine, sour cream and salt and pepper to taste.

title: turkey burgers
directions: Preheat broiler.
In a large bowl combine turkey and 1/4 cup salsa.
Shape into 4 (1/2 inch thick) patties.
Place on rack in broiler pan.
Broil patties 8 to 10 minutes (turning once) or until there is no pink in center.

title: sour cream dip
directions: Mix all together well and refrigerate before serving.

title: cornbread casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake in greased quiche pan for 1 hour at 350°.

title: cheese icebox wafers
directions: Cream butter; add cheese, flour, salt and pepper and mix until blended.
Shape dough into two 6-inch rolls.
Wrap in wax paper; chill for 2 hours.
Unwrap and cut into 1/4-inch slices; place cut side down on ungreased baking sheets.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes or until lightly browned.
Top each wafer with a pecan half. Sprinkle with paprika.
Let cool on wire rack.
Yields about 4 dozen.

title: white chocolate cookies
directions: Mix peanut butter and Marshmallow Creme together.
Spread a generous layer between 2 crackers.
Place a sheet of wax paper on a cookie sheet.
Melt coating in microwave according to package directions.
(Use 9-inch square Pyrex dish.)
Dip cookies into coating; turn with fork.
(Long fingernails help to hold, too.) Scrape some of coating from bottom of cookie with knife and place on wax paper.
Refrigerate to harden.
Makes between 40 and 50 cookies.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Break lettuce apart and put in salad bowl. Layer onion, black olives, peas and bacon. Sprinkle sugar over salad. Cover with mayonnaise. Salad is best if it is left to stand overnight. Top with cheese before serving.

title: squash casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients except dressing and margarine in 9 x 13-inch pan.
