Top with the dressing mixed with margarine.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: potato donuts
directions: Cook potatoes then mash.
Add sugar, margarine, eggs and beat well.
Add salt, nutmeg and vanilla.
Mix flour and baking powder to mixture alternating with milk.
Roll out dough on floured surface. Cut out. Cook in oil.

title: cheese ball
directions: Combine first four ingredients. Form into two balls. Roll in nuts. Serve on party crackers.

title: one-dish chicken 'n broccoli bake
directions: Mix 2 cups of the cheese, chicken, onion and broccoli in greased pie plate (10 x 1 1/2-inch).
Beat remaining ingredients except cheese until smooth (15 seconds in blender) on high or for 1 minute with hand beater.
Pour into plate.
Bake until knife inserted in center comes out clean (25 to 35 minutes).
Top with remaining cheese.
Bake just until melted, 1 or 2 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes.
(Heat oven to 350°.)
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: bisquick breakfast
directions: Pam a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Crumble sausage or ham into pan.
Mix eggs, milk and Bisquick.
Add Cheddar cheese.
Pour over sausage or chopped ham.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: caramel dip
directions: Blend all ingredients.
Use for dipping fruit.

title: peanut butter creams
directions: Beat egg slightly.
Add 1 cup sugar, vanilla, peanut butter and butter.
Stir until smooth, add second cup of sugar.
If needed, add more sugar until you're able to shape into balls. Make 1 inch balls and roll in chopped peanuts.
Refrigerate. Small children love to help make these for presents for parents.

title: delicious banana pudding
directions: Combine pudding mix and milk; beat until thick.
Add sour cream and Cool Whip (save enough Cool Whip for top of pudding). Line a large dish with vanilla wafers.
Alternate layers of pudding mix and bananas until all the mix is used.
Top with Cool Whip.
Refrigerate.

title: blueberry plate pie
directions: Mix egg, flour and sugar together.
Add berries to mixture and mix well.
Pour in unbaked pie crust and cover with other crust. Cook at 350° for 1 hour.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Beat butter and shortening at medium speed with an electric mixer about 2 minutes or until soft and creamy.
Gradually add sugar, beating well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Combine flour and soda; add to creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk, beginning and ending with flour mixture.
Mix after each addition.
Stir in vanilla, coconut and 1 cup pecans.
Spoon batter into 3 greased and floured 9-inch round cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 23 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pans on wire rack 10 minutes.
Remove from pans and let cool on wire racks.
Spread Italian Cream Frosting between layers and on top and sides of cake sprinkling 1/2 cup pecans between layers and on top.
Garnish, if desired.
Store in refrigerator.

title: orange cake
directions: Place
orange
juice
and
margarine on low heat.
Beat eggs well;
add	sugar
gradually
and
beat
on medium speed. Slowly on lowest speed, add flour, 1/2 cup at a time.
Add hot orange juice and
melted
margarine;
continue
mixing
on low speed. Lastly, add
salt,	baking	powder	and vanilla.
Pour into 2 baking pans or 13
x 9-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 40 minutes.
Let cool and use Orange Icing to complete.

title: cheese potato soup
directions: In 3 cups boiling water, cook potatoes until tender. Add cheese mixture from box. Put in crock-pot and add remaining ingredients. Turn on low and simmer 2 to 3 hours, stirring occasionally.

title: baked spaghetti
directions: Saute onions in hot oil until tender.
Add beef and cook until redness disappears.
Stir in salt, pepper, tomatoes, chiil powder, garlic salt and water.
Simmer 30 minutes.
Heat oven to 325°. Break half of uncooked spaghetti into 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Pour on half of sauce, sprinkle with half of cheese and break in rest of spaghetti.
Add rest of sauce and cheese.
Bake, covered, for 35 minutes.
Uncover and bake additional 15 minutes.

title: no bake pumpkin pie
directions: Beat eggs slightly. Add sugar and continue beating until well blended and thick. Transfer to top of a double boiler and stir in pumpkin, milk, salt and spices. Cook until thick, stirring frequently.

title: cheese ball
directions: Cube ham in small pieces.
Chop green onions (also the green tops).
Let cream cheese soften.
Mix all together.
Shape in a ball.
It's best to set overnight before using.
Serve with crackers.

title: hot fruit compote
directions: Arrange fruit in a long casserole dish using enough liquid to cover.
Dot with butter or margarine.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°, uncovered.
Syrup will thicken. Serve in chafing dish, if desired.

title: spicy burgers(serves four)
directions: Mince garlic and shallot.
Mix ground hamburger, soy sauce, teriyaki sauce, Mexican sauce, minced garlic and minced shallot in large mixing bowl.
Preheat skillet to 350°.
Form mixture into 4 patties.
Fry 3 to 5 minutes per side, or until done.
Add large slice onion and pepper when burgers are half cooked.
Drain well on paper towels before serving with ketchup or hot sauce (or a mixture of ketchup and hot sauce).
Can be eaten with rolls or without.
If served by self, garnish serving plate with fresh vegetable.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Beat eggs, add sugar and oil.
Mix well.
Add rest of ingredients.
Mix thoroughly.
Pour into greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake 60 minutes in a 350° preheated oven.
Makes 2 large loaves or 3 smaller loaves.
Delicious by itself but doubly delicious if frosted with Cream Cheese Frosting.
Frost when cool.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients, using pastry blender.
Blend mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Stir in water, bananas and eggs just until blended.
Pour into greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 325° for 55 minutes or 1 hour.
Servings: 20 (3 loaves).

title: oven-fried chicken
directions: Preheat oven at 375°.
Line baking sheet with foil.
Make breading.
Place peeled garlic cloves in a blender and process until finely chopped.
Add bread, Parmesan, salt and pepper; process the machine pulsing on and off until bread is finely crumbled.
Add sage to mixture and process to distribute evenly. Cut butter into small pieces; add to bread crumbs and process until butter is completely mixed.
Transfer breading to a bag. Dip chicken into the milk and shake in bag of bread until well coated.
Bake until crisp and juice run clear, 40 to 45 minutes.

title: ribbon sandwich
directions: Mix all ingredients together and divide in 1/2.
Use color of choice.
Use 3 slices of bread and trim edges off.
Spread one color on first slice, use second color on second slice and put third slice on top.
Then slice in 4 pieces and repeat.

title: waffles
directions: Beat egg yolks.
Add milk, sugar and melted shortening.
Sift dry ingredients together and combine with the first mixture.
Mix well.
Fold in beaten egg whites and bake in hot waffle iron. Time:
2 to 4 minutes.

title: angel food cake dessert
directions: Tear cake in small bite-size pieces and place in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Beat pudding mix with milk and add ice cream.
Mix together and pour over cake pieces.
Chill for 2 to 3 hours.

title: spicy black-eyed pea dip
directions: In a medium saucepan combine bell pepper, celery, onion, black pepper, hot pepper sauce, catsup, salt, boullion cubes, nutmeg and cinnamon.
Over low heat, cook and stir until boiling and cubes are dissolved completely.
Add peas, tomatoes, garlic and sugar and simmer 30 minutes.
Combine bacon drippings with flour and stir into peas.
Cook 10 minutes.
Stir well and serve hot with large corn chips.
This is unique and delicious way to insure good luck for the coming year by eating black-eyed peas on New Year's Day or you could leave out the bacon drippings and flour and serve as a vegetable.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, butter and milk together.
Cook for 1 minute (on damp days, cook for 2 minutes).
Add oatmeal, raisins, coconut and chopped nuts.
Drop by teaspoon onto wax paper.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients well.
Add rest.
Chill 1 hour. Shape dough into 1-inch balls; place 3 inches apart.
Flatten crisscross with fork.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes at 375°, or until set, but not hard.

title: creme de menthe frappe
directions: Soften ice cream.
Beat all ingredients in a mixer.
Place in ice trays; let stand for 10 to 12 hours.
Serve in champagne glasses.
Serves 6.

title: vidalia onion pie
directions: Spray deep dish pie plate with Pam.
Slice 1 onion and layer bottom of plate with onion.
Chop the other onion and layer over other onion, filling in between slices.
Mix flour and half and half; pour over onions.
Put crackers in Ziploc bag and crush. Spread over milk and onions.
Slice 1/2 stick oleo over crackers. Cover with cheese.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Delicious hot.
Very good cold with vegetables and meats.
I use Pet evaporated milk. It works just as well.
Very good with peas and beans.

title: bonbons #2
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients in large mixing bowl (use hands if necessary).
Shape into balls smaller than a walnut; let set about 1 hour.
Melt the chocolate chips with the paraffin wax over hot water.
Dip balls and place on waxed paper.
(Use round toothpick to dip balls.)
Leave the chocolate over warm water while you dip. After chocolate has started to set, go back and fill toothpick holes with chocolate.
Do not refrigerate.
Yields 11 dozen bonbons.

title: vegie bars
directions: Roll out both rolls of crescent rolls in a jelly roll pan. Press out seams.
Prick dough all over with fork.
With a pastry brush, spread egg on dough liberally.
Bake exactly 12 minutes. Let cool.
While it's cooling, mix cream cheese and mayonnaise together.
Then add Ranch-style dressing.
Blend throughly. Spread mix over crust (it'll be thick).
Mix in bowl fine chopped veggies, then sprinkle on cream cheese mixture.
After that, sprinkle cheddar cheese over all.
Cover with plastic and chill for a minimum of 2 hours.
Can be frozen for 1 week.
Thaw for 24 hours before serving.
Cut into bars.

title: tortilla soup
directions: Brown meat with onion in 3 qt. saucepan; drain well. Drain and chop tomatoes, reserving juice. add tomatoes and juice to saucepan with beans, tomato sauce, water, picante sauce and cumin. Bring to a boil; reduce heat. Cover and simmer 10 minutes. ladle into soup bowls. Top with tortilla chips, cheese, lettuce and sour cream to taste.

title: soda cracker fudge
directions: Bring sugar and canned milk to a boil and boil 3 minutes. Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter, vanilla and crushed crackers.
Stir well and pour into 8-inch square pan or glass dish.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: graham praline cookies
directions: Grease cookie sheet.
Line cookie sheet with graham crackers. Heat butter and brown sugar until it bubbles, then cook 2 minutes.
Spread over graham crackers hurriedly.
Then sprinkle chopped nuts over top.
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes.
Cool on cookie sheet, but re-mark or cut while still warm.
These are very tasty and good for a party.
(Pastor John likes these.)

title: frosty strawberry squares
directions: *If use frozen berries, reduce sugar to 2/3 cup.

title: sunset salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin and salt in boiling water.
Add undrained pineapple and lemon juice.
Chill about 10 minutes.
Add carrots and nuts.
Put in 1-quart mold.
Chill until firm.

title: pineapple raisin cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, pineapple, raisins and nuts.
Sift together flour, salt, soda and baking powder.
Add to first mixture.
Drop
on baking sheet.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes at 375°.

title: chili-cheese straws
directions: Combine cheese and butter, stirring until blended.
Gradually add remaining ingredients, stirring until mixture is no longer crumbly and will shape into a ball.
tags: shredded Monterey Jack cheese with peppers

title: ham rolls
directions: Mix cheese, Worcestershire sauce and garlic salt until creamy. Spread onto each ham slice.
Place 6 olives on each ham slice at edge and roll up carefully.
Fill ends with cream cheese mixture. Secure each olive with toothpicks and slice between toothpicks.

title: pickled beets
directions: Mix beets and juice and rest of ingredients together.
Bring to boil.
Let cool.
Serve.

title: cindy's stew
directions: Brown the stew meat and onion in Dutch oven.
Add tomato juice, following with remaining ingredients.
Simmer 30 minutes or until vegetables are tender.

title: whole wheat pasta salad
directions: Cook spaghetti for 10 to 12 minutes.
Steam broccoli 5 to 8 minutes.
Drain and place in large serving bowl.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Combine in a large mixing bowl:
chicken breasts (cooked, boned and diced), grated Monterey Jack cheese (with jalapenos, if desired), diced onion, diced green chilies and sour cream.
Add 1/2 can cream of mushroom soup; mix.

title: rose petal tea
directions: Mix together and store in a covered container.
Steep 1 1/2 teaspoons per cup of boiling water.
Also good with ice.

title: brunch casserole
directions: Brown sausage; drain on paper towels over heavy brown grocery bag.
Pat excess grease off with paper towels.
Beat eggs well. Add milk, salt to taste and mustard and beat again.
Combine egg mixture with sausage, bread and cheese.
Stir and pour into casserole.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 4 or 5.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Cook syrup, sugar and water until it reaches a hard boil. Add peanuts and cook until golden brown.
Add butter and vanilla flavoring.
Stir until well mixed.
Add baking soda and do not stir long.
Pour into a buttered pan.

title: fish chowder
directions: Combine vegetables.
Cover with water.
Add salt and pepper. Boil until done.
Add fish; boil about 10 minutes.
Reduce heat below boil.
Add milk and butter, stir while adding.
Bring back to boil.
Remove from heat.
Serve hot.
Add 1 teaspoon butter to bowl when serving.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Beat softened cream cheese; add sugar, peanut butter and milk. Fold in Cool Whip.
Place ingredients in graham cracker crust and cover with the lid from the crust.
Freeze overnight.
Place pieces of pie in microwave for 10 seconds before serving.
Keep leftovers in freezer.

title: salsa
directions: Mix ingredients to desired taste.

title: holiday yam bake
directions: Drain yams and mash well.
Drain pineapple, adding juice to yams.
Add sugar and butter.
Beat well.
Stir in pineapple and pecans.
Coat inside of 1 1/2-quart casserole with butter or spray oil coating.
Spoon mixture into dish.

title: zucchini appetizers
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease rectangular 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Mix all ingredients and spread in pan.
Bake until golden brown, about 25 minutes. Cut into rectangles, approximately 2 x 1-inch. Refrigerate any remaining appetizers.
Yields 4 dozen.

title: quick chicken pie
directions: Put a layer of chicken, soup, eggs and broth in bottom of casserole.
Top with frozen pie crust and punch holes in crust so juices can cook through.
Layer rest of ingredients in the same way.
Top with second pie crust, slit crust and pour about 1/4 cup of broth on top.
Cook at 375° for 30 minutes or longer.

title: spaghetti casserole
directions: Fry and drain hamburg, onion and pepper.
Mix all together. Put in casserole. Top with 1 cup grated sharp Cheddar cheese. Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes or until brown on top.

title: skillet pizza
directions: Grease a 12-inch electric or stove-top skillet.
Prepare pizza crust according to package directions.
Line bottom and 1/2 inch up the sides of the skillet with dough.
Combine tomato sauce, Italian seasoning and oregano; spread over dough.
Layer pepperoni, onion, green pepper and olives over sauce; sprinkle with cheese.
Cover and cook over medium heat (set electric skillet to 375°).

title: cloud nine
directions: Use graham crackers, melted butter and sugar for a graham cracker crust.
Don't pack as hard as you would for a pie crust.

title: taffy apple salad
directions: Mix marshmallows and pineapple.
Refrigerate overnight.
Mix pineapple juice, sugar, flour, vinegar and egg.
Microwave for 6 to 8 minutes.
Stir halfway through cooking time, then refrigerate.
Next day, mix with apples, peanut butter and peanuts.

title: broccoli corn bread
directions: Mix and bake in 9x13 inch pan at 350 degrees for 30-40 minutes.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: gambas al ajillo(tio pepe's shrimp in garlic)
directions: Combine parsley, lemon juice, thyme, red pepper and salt.
Add shrimp and stir to coat.
Cover and let stand for 1 to 2 hours, stirring occasionally.
In 10-inch skillet, cook garlic in oil until lightly browned.
Add shrimp and cook over medium heat for 3 minutes.
Add sherry and Worcestershire; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer for 2 to 3 minutes.
Serve immediately and with a good crusty bread or rolls!

title: no peek casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a 1 1/2 qt. casserole.
Cover and bake in 300° oven for 3 hours.
Do not peek until done. Serve over rice, noodles or mashed potatoes.

title: hot bacon dressing
directions: Fry bacon.
Add flour to grease; let cool.
Beat together sugar, eggs, vinegar, water and salt.
Add to cooled mixture and bring to a boil.
Serves 6.

title: venison steaks
directions: Marinate venison 2 to 3 hours in milk; sprinkle with tenderizer and pound lightly; dredge in flour, salt and pepper.
Panfry in oil until just brown on each side (do not overcook).
This will be almost fork-tender with no strong flavor.

title: christmas strufflers(honey balls)
directions: In large 6 to 8-quart stainless steel bowl, beat eggs.
Slowly add sugar, melted butter or margarine, baking powder and vanilla. Beat in 1 cup of flour at a time.
Dough will be sticky.
Keep adding flour until dough can be removed from bowl.
Now, knead on floured table.
Keep kneading and adding flour until dough can be rolled.
Cut into slices and roll strips like a snake.
Cut into square pieces.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Drain berries and pineapple.
Measure liquid to equal one cup.
Stir in liquid, berries and pineapple.
Pour in long dish.
Chill until firm.

title: joyce's cheater lasagna
directions: Spray 9 x 12-inch pan with Pam.
Put one layer noodles in pan. Brown ground beef with onion and drain.
Layer 1/2 beef mixture, followed by 1/2 jar sauce, 1/2 carton Ricotta and 1/2 of Mozzarella.
Add second layer noodles, meat, sauce and cheeses. Pour water into spaghetti jar.
Shake to make "tomato juice" and pour over mixture.
Heat in 350°
oven for 45 minutes until bubbly.

title: kephtethes(meatballs, greek style)
directions: Place minced onion in small saucepan, together with about 1/4 cup water.
Simmer gently until the onion is tender, about 10 minutes.
All of the water will have evaporated by now.
Remove the pan and set on one side for a few minutes.
Watch onion.
In a small, dry saute pan or saucepan, gently heat the ground cumin for a few minutes or until it begins to give out an aroma.
This is proof that the heat is releasing the essential oils of the cumin. Set on one side for a few minutes.
In a large mixing bowl, place the meat, onion, chopped tomato, parsley, cumin, mint and bread crumbs.
Add some salt and plenty of pepper, as well as about half of the cumin.
Taste the mixture and be prepared to add the rest of the cumin (or even more).
Add egg and more salt.
Refrigerate meat for 1/2 hour.
Have a large plate ready, covered with flour. Lightly flour your hands with some of it.
Form the mixture into small balls, the size depending entirely on your preference.

In Greece, they are usually the size of a silver dollar and slightly flattened if served as a main course and about the size of a half dollar (and again, slightly flattened) if being used as a first course.
Heat some olive oil in a large saute pan.
Prepare your grill or oil a baking sheet for the oven.
Cook the Kephtethes in your preferred way (the oven should be about 375° for small or 400° for large), turning them very carefully after they have been browned on one side.
Baking sheet should be heated.
Serve hot, cold or somewhere in between as they do in Greece, decorated with a little chopped parsley or mint.
Don't overcook.

title: pound cake
directions: Have all ingredients at room temperature.
Cream together well butter and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time and beat well.
Sift together dry ingredients and add alternately with milk and vanilla.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: mock zucchini pineapple
directions: Peel and seed zucchini, grind or shred and drain.
Simmer all ingredients 20 minutes.
Pack hot in jars with 1 1/4 inch headspace.
Process in hot water bath 25 minutes.
Just like crushed pineapple.

title: jiffy jambalaya
directions: Saute onion and green pepper in butter in Dutch oven until softened, about 5 minutes.
Add garlic; cook 30 seconds.
Add flour; cook, stirring, 1 minute.
Pour in tomatoes, tomato juice, clam juice, parsley, Worcestershire sauce, thyme, red pepper seasoning, salt and pepper.
Bring to boiling.
Lower heat to simmer.
Add ham and rice.
Cook, covered, 15 minutes.
Add shrimp; cook, covered, 5 minutes longer or until shrimp are cooked through.

title: cabbage patch soup
directions: Fry bacon in 3-quart saucepan over medium heat until crisp, about 6 minutes.
Remove with slotted spoon and drain on paper towels.
Drain all but 2 tablespoons drippings from saucepan.
Add onion and celery to drippings and saute over medium heat 5 minutes or until tender.
Blend in flour, salt and pepper.
Gradually stir in chicken broth.
Cook over high heat, stirring constantly until mixture comes to boil, about 3 minutes.
Add cabbage, carrots and bay leaf.
Reduce heat to low.
Cover and simmer 10 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Stir in peas and cook 3 minutes more or until tender.
(Stir some of the hot mixture into sour cream. Then stir sour cream mixture back into saucepan.
Remove from heat.)
Serve garnished with parsley and bacon.
Range top:
27 minutes cooking time.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream shortening.
Add sugar and egg.
Add well mashed bananas.
Sift flour, soda and salt; add to mixture.
Mix thoroughly.
Bake at 350° to 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: bean salad
directions: Mix beans; set aside.
Mix vinegar and sugar, then add onion and bell pepper.
Pour over beans and mix well.
Chill.

title: carol's casserole
directions: Cook carrots for 20 minutes; drain.
Cook broccoli and cauliflower for 10 minutes.
Drain.
Melt butter, flour, cream, pepper, salt, mustard and cheese in a saucepan until cheese is melted.
Place veggies in casserole.
Pour sauce over top.
Top with Ritz crackers that have been crushed and mixed with 1 1/2 sticks butter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: glazed red raspberry pie
directions: Wash and drain berries.
Crush 1/2 quart of the berries and combine with the sugar, cornstarch, water and lemon juice in saucepan.
Bring to a boil and cook 2 minutes, or until clear; add butter and enough red coloring to make bright color.
Strain out the seeds.
Place the remaining quart of berries into the baked pie shell.
Spoon the glaze over the berries.
Chill.
Garnish with whipped cream, if desired.

title: a man's barbecued chicken
directions: Early in the day or day before make barbecue sauce by combining in saucepan, salt, pepper, tomato juice, cayenne, mustard, bay leaf, Worcestershire, vinegar, sugar, garlic, butter. Simmer, uncovered, 10 minutes.
Refrigerate.
About 1 hour and 30 minutes before serving.
Start heating oven to 425°. Arrange chickens, skin sides down, in single layer in shallow open pan. Sprinkle lightly with some salt and pepper.
Arrange onions on chicken, tucking a few slices under wings. legs.
Pour on barbecue sauce.
Bake, uncovered, basting often.
1/2 hour.
Turn and bake, basting often.
45 minutes or until fork can be inserted easily into legs.
Make 4 to 6 servings. For 2: Use 1 1/2 pound broiler - fryer and same amount of sauce.

title: quick and easy beef tips
directions: Tenderize beef tip in pressure cooker or parboil.
Melt butter in skillet over low heat.
Slice onion very thin and saute in butter until tender.
Add mushrooms and saute for an additional 3-4 minutes.
Stir beef tips and stir-fry until brown over medium heat.
Add mushroom gravy and stir well.
Add dry onion soup mix. Stir well and add 1 Cup water.
Cook covered, for 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Serve over egg noodles or rice.

title: apple stuffed ham
directions: Saute celery and onion in butter until golden.
In bowl, combine celery, onion, apples, stuffing and parsley.
Slowly add 1/2 cup melted margarine.
In roasting pan, layer stuffing mix between ham slices.
Spread jam on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Makes 6 servings.

title: garlic pasta
directions: * Weight before cooking.

title: saucy zucchini
directions: Cook zucchini and onion in a small amount of boiling water until tender; drain and set aside.
In a saucepan, melt butter. Blend in flour, salt and pepper.
Add milk, all at once.
Cook, stirring constantly until mixture thickens and bubbles.
Combine the sauce with the cooked vegetables and pour into a 10 x 6 x 1 3/4-inch baking dish.
Top with cheese and then with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for about 25 minutes.

title: butterscotch ice-cream topping
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Stir until boiling and simmer for 3 minutes.

title: swiss almond party spread(appetizer)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients.
Mix well. Spread into 9-inch pie plate or quiche dish.
Bake for 15 minutes; stir after 8 minutes.
Garnish with additional almonds, if desired.
Serve with assorted crackers.

title: rhubarb custard
directions: Cream sugar and butter, then add eggs (yolks) and mix well. Add milk.
Spread finely cut rhubarb in bottom of unbaked 9-inch pie shell.
Add stiffly beaten egg whites to the custard mixture, then pour it over the rhubarb in the pie shell.
Bake in 350° oven for 60 minutes or until point of knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: texas corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients, except Cheddar cheese. Pour 1/2 of the batter into a
large prepared iron skillet. Sprinkle on the Cheddar cheese.
Pour in remaining batter.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: black-eyed pea salsa
directions: Cook peas to tender.
Rinse under cold water; drain well. Combine peas, tomatoes and all other ingredients.
Let stand at room temperature for about 30 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
(It's good with chicken breasts and brown rice.)

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: In a large bowl, combine cheese, soup, sour cream, onion, 1/4 cup butter, salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Fold in thawed potatoes. Turn mixture into a greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Toss the cornflake crumbs and 1 tablespoon butter and sprinkle over the potato mixture.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour or until golden brown and the potatoes are tender.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: ham and corn chowder
directions: Fry the salt pork until browned.
Remove the salt pork from the pan and set aside.
Saute the onions in the fat.
Cook the potatoes in salted boiling water until soft.
Drain the cooked potatoes, saving about 1 1/2 cups of the liquid.
In large soup pot or Dutch oven, combine the salt pork, sauteed onion, potatoes, potato water, and the corn.
Bring to a boil and immediately reduce the heat and simmer gently for 5 to 10 minutes.
Season to taste with salt and black pepper.
Add the cream slowly.
Add the ham and simmer for another 5 to 10 minutes.
After the chowder is spooned into the serving bowls, sprinkle with paprika, if desired.

title: tuna mold
directions: Dissolve gelatin in 1/4 cup water.
Heat soup and add gelatin mixture to warm soup.
Pour over softened cream cheese and mix. Add drained tuna, onion and mayonnaise.
When well mixed, pour into buttered or oiled mold.
Chill until firm.

title: macaroni casserole
directions: Cook macaroni; drain.
Add all other ingredients.
Mix well. Pour into greased casserole dish.
Sprinkle top with bread crumbs. Bake at 425° for 30 minutes.

title: italian cream cheese cake
directions: Stir soda into buttermilk; set aside.
Cream the shortening, oleo and sugar.
Add egg yolks, one at a time, beating well after each.
Alternately add milk and flour.
Stir in vanilla.
In a clean bowl, with clean beaters, beat egg whites to stiff peaks; fold into mixture.
Fold in coconut and nuts.
Pour into 1 (9 x 13-inch) pan or 2 round layer pans which have been prepared with shortening and flour or Baker's Joy.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 30 minutes (toothpick test).

title: 5-hour oven beef stew
directions: Mix meat and vegetables together in large casserole.
Add spices and tomato juice.
Stir to mix.
Cover and bake at 250° for 5 hours.
Better if stirred once or twice during baking.

title: aunt marion's monkey faces
directions: Combine first 9 ingredients.
Chill several hours.
Roll out to 1/8-inch thick.
Cut out 2 1/2-inch circles.
Combine and cook last five ingredients until thick.
Cool.
Drop by tablespoon onto cut out circle.
Cover with second circle and press edges together.
Cut out three half moons with edge of spoon.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: mustard glazed pork loin
directions: In a small bowl, combine corn syrup, brown sugar and mustard. Place pork in a small roasting pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours (30 minutes per pound), or to desired doneness.
Brush with glaze several times during last 30 minutes of cooking.
Yield: 4 to 6 servings.

title: rum custard pudding
directions: In saucepan, combine eggs, brown sugar and cornstarch. Gradually add milk.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Add rum.
Pour into serving dishes and chill.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Spread biscuit dough into baking dish.
Spread apple butter onto dough.
Heat together sugar, water and flour on medium heat until thick.
Pour mixture over apple butter.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: neiman-marcus bars
directions: Mix together the cake mix, egg and butter.
Press into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Beat the rest of the ingredients and pour over cake mix evenly.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes. Sprinkle powdered sugar on top.
Let cool thoroughly, then cut into squares.

title: harvest carrot salad
directions: Combine carrots, apricots, raisins, celery, salad dressing and walnuts.
Mix lightly.
Chill.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: shipwreck casserole
directions: Arrange onions in bottom of pan, then sliced new potatoes.
Add ground beef, celery, rice (uncooked), kidney beans and soup last. Cover and simmer about 2 hours.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Reserve 1/4 cup cheese for top.
Cook broccoli and chicken separately.
Cube the chicken.
Place in flat casserole dish the broccoli, chicken, cheese, soup, bread crumbs and and 1/4 cup cheese topping.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: lime parfait pie
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Stir in peel and lime juice.
Add ice cream by spoonfuls, stirring until melted, with wire beater.
Chill until mixture mounds slightly when spooned. Pour into cooled pastry shell.
Chill until firm.
Trim with whipped cream (if desired).

title: creamy fettuccine toss(makes 6 to 8 servings)
directions: In saucepan, melt margarine; stir in flour and seasonings. Gradually add half and half and milk.
Cook and stir until slightly thickened, about 15 minutes.
Remove from heat; add cheese,
In large bowl, pour sauce over hot fettuccine; stir to coat.
Garnish with parsley, walnuts and bacon; serve immediately. Refrigerate leftovers.

title: homemade summer sausage
directions: Slowly mix all ingredients in a large container.
Cover. Refrigerate.
Next day, mix again.
On third day, roll into 5 rolls, 2 1/2-inches in diameter.
Cook in oven at 150° for 8 hours.
Turn every 2 hours.
Spoon off grease or use broiler pan. If preferred, cook 4 hours and smoke 8 hours at 150° using wet hickory chips.

title: virginia gooher cookies
directions: Mix first ingredients, then add chocolate chips and remaining ingredients.
Roll into balls and press down fork on top of dough ball.
Place on greased pan.
Cook at 350° in preheated oven for 7 minutes.

title: southern peach cobbler
directions: Melt margarine.
Add sugar, milk and fruit.
Mix well.
Add flour and mix until well blended.
Pour over fruit mixture.
Bake at 375° until top is golden brown, about 1 hour.

title: hot dog casserole
directions: Saute onions and hot dogs in little butter or oleo.
Drain. Add to cooked noodles that are drained.
Put in casserole dish with soup and water.
Bake until hot, approximately 1/2 hour at 350°.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add oil and eggs.
Mix thoroughly.
Add carrots and mix again.
Add nuts and mix again.
Bake in a tube pan or long 5 x 16-inch pan for 1 hour and 30 minutes at 350°. Delicious topped with ice cream.
Can be frozen.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions; drain well. Add the remaining ingredients. Mix well, chill and serve.

title: miniature fruit cakes
directions: Pour hot water over dates and soda; set aside to cool.
Cream sugar and oleo.
Add egg.
Add flour and cinnamon alternately with date mixture.
Add walnuts, pineapple and cherries.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. In a large bowl, stir all ingredients together until well mixed. Drop from teaspoon on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake 10 to 12 minutes.

title: apple and squash
directions: Leave squash whole (pierce).
Cook in microwave on High for 8 to 10 minutes or until they feel soft to the touch.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Cut in half and remove seeds.
Place, cut side up, in shallow baking dish.
Sprinkle with salt.
Fill with apples. Top each half with 2 tablespoons brown sugar, 1 tablespoon butter and a dash of cinnamon. Cook, covered, with waxed paper 4 to 5 minutes on High or until apples are tender.
If desired, add 1 tablespoon raisins with apples to each squash half.

title: country fried chicken
directions: Mix flour, salt, paprika and pepper.
Coat chicken with flour mixture.
Heat oil 1/2-inch deep in chicken fryer until hot.
Cook chicken in oil until light brown on all sides about 10 minutes, then reduce heat.
Cover and simmer turning twice until thickest pieces are done, about 35 minutes.
Take cover off last 5 minutes to crisp chicken.

title: overnight chicken
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put into large casserole dish; refrigerate overnight.
Remove from refrigerator and mix well. Top with bread crumbs, potato chips or Chinese noodles.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: twinkie cake
directions: Layer Twinkies in pan.
Cover with strawberries, then cover with pudding.
Top with Cool Whip.
Add cherries on top, if desired.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Mix all ingredients except margarine.
Melt margarine in 2-quart casserole.
Pour in batter.
Put fruit in center of mixture.
Bake 35 minutes or until brown at 350°.
Any fruit can be used.

title: orange chiffon pie
directions: Mix all ingredients with a wire whisk in a large bowl.
Pile high into a 9-inch graham cracker pie shell.
Refrigerate 4 hours. Garnish with nutmeg or additional whipped topping and candy orange slices.
Makes 8 to 12 servings.

title: cherry bread
directions: Mix flour, salt and baking powder together.
Mix in sugar and butter.
Add egg mixture and vanilla.
Add nuts and cherries.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: delicious dried beef dip
directions: Mix first 8 ingredients together.
Put in small round baking dish.
Saute pecans in butter.
Pour on top of mixture.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Serve with crackers.

title: easy banana nut bread
directions: Blend first 5 ingredients in blender about 15 seconds.
Sift together 3 dry ingredients.
Add walnuts.
Pour blended ingredients over dry ingredients.
Mix.
Pour in greased loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: pasta salad
directions: Drain pineapple reserving 1/4 cup juice.
Mix the pineapple and 1/4 cup juice with remaining ingredients in a large bowl. Toss to coat.

title: fluffy white frosting
directions: Sprinkle gelatin over cold water in a saucepan; let stand 1 minute.
Add corn syrup; cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, just until mixture comes to a boil and gelatin dissolves.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla.
Beat egg whites and cream of tartar in a medium bowl at high speed of an electric mixer until foamy.
Slowly add corn syrup mixture; continue beating until stiff peaks form and frosting is of spreading consistency (about 10 minutes).
To serve, spread frosting over cake layers or cupcakes.
Yields 2 1/2 cups.

title: sausage pie
directions: Line bottom and sides of pie pan with 4 rolls to make crust (stretch and mold, it doesn't have to be perfect).
Make sure bottom of pan is covered.
Fry sausage and drain.
Put sausage in crust.
Shred Mozzarella cheese and mix with other ingredients. Pour on top of sausage.
Stretch other 4 rolls to cover the pie. Beat another egg and spread over pie.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: hot cha-cha pasta
directions: Boil pasta to an "al dente" stage and drain.
Melt margarine on pasta and mix well.
Add picante sauce and cheese; stir well and serve.

title: juicy rib steaks
directions: Quickly rinse steaks.
Pat dry.
Rub a teaspoon of cornstarch on each steak.
Rinse and slice leek.
In a skillet, heat butter. Add leek.
Reduce heat.
Saute, stirring, until leek is soft. Remove from pan.
Set aside.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients in deep microwave casserole. Cook on High for 7 to 8 minutes or until light brown.
Remove and stir in vanilla and butter.
Microwave on High 2 minutes (or until hard crack stage).
Remove. Add soda.
Stir quickly and pour onto greased cookie sheet. Cool and break into pieces.
Makes 1 pound.

title: molasses cake
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Mix and sift flour, salt, cinnamon, soda and baking powder.
Combine the two mixtures.
Pour into a greased and floured 8 x 12-inch pan.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°. This cake is much better served hot with butter.

title: caribbean chicken
directions: Cook macaroni according to directions.
Add chicken and other ingredients and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: icebox gingerbread
directions: Mix butter or margarine with sugar.
Add beaten eggs and molasses.
Mix sifted dry ingredients with sour milk.
Add nutmeats and raisins.
Put in covered bowl in refrigerator or bake immediately.
Bake as much as needed at one time in greased and floured pan at 350°.
Will keep 2 weeks, refrigerated.
Very good.

title: hospitality punch
directions: Mix all ingredients just before serving and pour over ice ring in punch bowl.

title: lemon lush
directions: Melt butter in pan; stir in flour.
Press into 9 x 11-inch pan.
Bake for approximately 15 minutes at 350° or until golden brown.
Cool.

title: easy cherry cobbler
directions: Mix flour, sugar and milk together.
Melt 1 stick butter in the bottom of a Pyrex bowl.
Pour dough mixture in bowl and add cherries.
Chop other stick of butter on top and bake until golden brown.
Sprinkle with sugar last 3 or 4 minutes.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate until thick. Serve.

title: dilly salmon loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, combine all ingredients except Lemon Dill Sauce; mix well.
Shape into loaf.
Place in greased shallow baking dish.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.
Serve with Lemon Dill Sauce.
Garnish as desired.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: banana nut cookies
directions: Cream shortening, vanilla, lemon and eggs.
Sift dry ingredients together and mix with creamed ingredients.
Add bananas and nuts.
Drop and bake in 350° oven until browned. Makes 40 cookies.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix soups, butter and milk and reserve 1/2 cup of mixture. Mix rest with rice.
Place in buttered casserole dish (13 x 9 x 2-inch).
Add seasoned chicken on top and pour remaining sauce over this.
Bake at 275° for 3 hours.

title: gooey blonde brownies
directions: Melt butter and brown sugar together over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Heat until bubbly; cool.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Stir in flour, salt and nuts.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes, until the edges are slightly browned.

title: apple crisp
directions: Grease a 10 inch pie plate with butter.
Fill with sliced apples (I use McIntosh and a couple of Granny Smith).
Mix together the sugar, flour, cinnamon, nutmeg and margarine.
Spread over apples and pour orange juice over all.
Bake at 375° for 40-45 minutes.
Serve with ice cream if desired.
Excellent fall/winter dessert!

title: pumpkin bread on cake
directions: Cream together sugar and Crisco oil.
Add eggs, pumpkin and water (liquid mixture).
Mix dry ingredients; add to liquid mixture.
Bake for 45 to 60 minutes at 350° in Bundt pan.

title: ham and cheese ball
directions: Mix cream cheese and chopped ham together.
Add dressing. Form into a ball.
Chill for 1 hour.
Serve with crackers.

title: cherry cheese desserts
directions: Put Keebler vanilla wafer in mini cupcake holder (flat side up).
Put some of mixture in each.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Top with cherry pie filling.
Makes 35 desserts.

title: crab pie
directions: Mix egg and cream. Drain crab and rinse well. Add other ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: neiman-marcus cake
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and press into a 13 x 9-inch cake pan. Mix the remaining ingredients and spread on cake.
Bake 1 hour at 300°.

title: banana split cake
directions: Make crust:
Melt 1/2 cup margarine; mix with graham crackers.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan for first layer.

title: kaylyn's favorite cream cheese pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease and flour pan.
I use large Bundt pan.
Cream together butter, cream cheese and sugar.
Add salt and vanilla.
Beat in eggs, 1 at a time.
Stir in flour. Pour in pan and bake for 1 1/2 hours.
